English Sentences: And the LORD spake unto Moses in the wilderness of Sinai, in the tabernacle of the congregation, on the first day of the second month, in the second year after they were come out of the land of Egypt, saying,
Wolaitta Sentences: Siinaa Bazzuwan, Xoossaa Dunkkaaniyaa giddon, Israa7eela asai Gibxxe biittaappe kiyido naa77antto laittan, naa77antto aginan, he aginau koiro gallassan, GODAI Muusa hagaadan yaagiis;

English Sentences: Take ye the sum of all the congregation of the children of Israel, after their families, by the house of their fathers, with the number of their names, every male by their polls;
Wolaitta Sentences: "Israa7eela asaa ubbaa eta yaran yaraaninne keettan keettan qoodada, attuma asaa eta sunttan sunttan xaafa.

English Sentences: From twenty years old and upward, all that are able to go forth to war in Israel: thou and Aaron shall number them by their armies.
Wolaitta Sentences: Neeninne Aarooni yelettoosappe laatamu laittanne hegaappe bollaara de7iya Israa7eelata, olaa baanau danddayiyaageeta ubbata, eta citan citan qoodite.

English Sentences: And with you there shall be a man of every tribe; every one head of the house of his fathers.
Wolaitta Sentences: Zariyaappe zariyaappe issi issi asi ba keettaa asau halaqa gididi, inttena maaddo.

English Sentences: And these are the names of the men that shall stand with you: of the tribe of Reuben; Elizur the son of Shedeur.
Wolaitta Sentences: Inttena maaddana asatu sunttai hagaappe kaallidi de7iyaagaa: Zariyaa Keettaa Asaa Halaqaa Roobeela SHade7uura na7aa Eliixuura

English Sentences: Of Simeon; Shelumiel the son of Zurishaddai.
Wolaitta Sentences: Simoona Xuriishadaaya na7aa SHalumi7eela

English Sentences: Of Judah; Nahshon the son of Amminadab.
Wolaitta Sentences: Yihudaa Aminadaaba na7aa Na7asoona

English Sentences: Of Issachar; Nethaneel the son of Zuar.
Wolaitta Sentences: Yisaakoora Xu7aara na7aa Nataani7eela

English Sentences: Of Zebulun; Eliab the son of Helon.
Wolaitta Sentences: Zaabiloona Heloona na7aa Eli7aaba

English Sentences: Of the children of Joseph: of Ephraim; Elishama the son of Ammihud: of Manasseh; Gamaliel the son of Pedahzur.
Wolaitta Sentences: Efireema Amihuuda na7aa Elishamaa7a Minaase Padaaxuura na7aa Gamaali7eela

English Sentences: Of Benjamin; Abidan the son of Gideoni.
Wolaitta Sentences: Biniyaama Giidi7oona na7aa Abidaana

English Sentences: Of Dan; Ahiezer the son of Ammishaddai.
Wolaitta Sentences: Daana Amishadaaya na7aa Ahi7eezera

English Sentences: Of Asher; Pagiel the son of Ocran.
Wolaitta Sentences: Aseera Okiraana na7aa Paagi7eela

English Sentences: Of Gad; Eliasaph the son of Deuel.
Wolaitta Sentences: Gaada Da7u7eela na7aa Eliyasaafa

English Sentences: Of Naphtali; Ahira the son of Enan.
Wolaitta Sentences: Nifttaaleema Enaana na7aa Ahiraa7a

English Sentences: These were the renowned of the congregation, princes of the tribes of their fathers, heads of thousands in Israel.
Wolaitta Sentences: Ha asati bantta aawatu keettaa asatuppe kaalettanau doorettidaageeta; eti Israa7eela yaratuyyo halaqata" yaagiis.

English Sentences: And Moses and Aaron took these men which are expressed by their names:
Wolaitta Sentences: Yaagin Muuseenne Aarooni sunttai xeesettido ha asata efiidosona.

English Sentences: And they assembled all the congregation together on the first day of the second month, and they declared their pedigrees after their families, by the house of their fathers, according to the number of the names, from twenty years old and upward, by their polls.
Wolaitta Sentences: Naa77antta aginan koiro gallassi kumetta maabaraa xeesidi, issippe shiishshidosona. SHiishshin asai ba yaran yaraaninne ba keettan keettan odidi, yelettoosappe laatamu laittanne hegaappe bollaara de7iya attumaasatu ubbaa sunttai muleera xaafettiis.

English Sentences: As the LORD commanded Moses, so he numbered them in the wilderness of Sinai.
Wolaitta Sentences: GODAI a azazidoogaadan, Muusee eta Siinaa Bazzuwan qoodiis.

English Sentences: And the children of Reuben, Israel's eldest son, by their generations, after their families, by the house of their fathers, according to the number of the names, by their polls, every male from twenty years old and upward, all that were able to go forth to war;
Wolaitta Sentences: Olau baanau danddayiya attumaasati ubbai, laatamu laittanne hegaappe bollaara de7iyaageeti qoodettidi, huuphiyan huuphiyan xaafettidosona. Eti bantta yaran yaraaninne bantta keettan keettan shaahettidi, hagaappe kaallidi de7iya qoodan mazggafettidosona. Zariyaa Olanchchatu Qoodaa Roobeela Yaaqooba na7aa bairaa 46,500

English Sentences: These are those that were numbered, which Moses and Aaron numbered, and the princes of Israel, being twelve men: each one was for the house of his fathers.
Wolaitta Sentences: Muusee, Aarooninne tammanne naa77u Israa7eela zaretu halaqati qoodido asai hagaa.

English Sentences: So were all those that were numbered of the children of Israel, by the house of their fathers, from twenty years old and upward, all that were able to go forth to war in Israel;
Wolaitta Sentences: Olau baanau danddayiya attumaasati ubbai laatamu laittanne hegaappe bollaara de7iyaageeti bantta aawaa keettan keettan qoodettidosona.

English Sentences: Even all they that were numbered were six hundred thousand and three thousand and five hundred and fifty.
Wolaitta Sentences: Hegeeti muleera 603,550.

English Sentences: But the Levites after the tribe of their fathers were not numbered among them.
Wolaitta Sentences: SHin Leewa zareti ha qoodettida asaara qoodettibookkona.

English Sentences: For the LORD had spoken unto Moses, saying,
Wolaitta Sentences: Aissi giikko, GODAI Muusa hagaadan yaagiis;

English Sentences: Only thou shalt not number the tribe of Levi, neither take the sum of them among the children of Israel:
Wolaitta Sentences: "Leewa zareta qoodoppa; eta attida Israa7eelatu qoodan yeggoppa.

English Sentences: But thou shalt appoint the Levites over the tabernacle of testimony, and over all the vessels thereof, and over all things that belong to it: they shall bear the tabernacle, and all the vessels thereof; and they shall minister unto it, and shall encamp round about the tabernacle.
Wolaitta Sentences: Leewata Xoossaa Dunkkaaniyaa bollaaninne a giddon de7iya miishshatu ubbaa bollan halaqa oottada suntta. Eti he Dunkkaaniyaanne a giddon de7iya miishshata tookkona; eti a giddon oottonanne a yuushuwan dunkkaanona.

English Sentences: And when the tabernacle setteth forward, the Levites shall take it down: and when the tabernacle is to be pitched, the Levites shall set it up: and the stranger that cometh nigh shall be put to death.
Wolaitta Sentences: Xoossaa Dunkkaanee shodettiyo wode Leewati shoddona; Xoossaa Dunkkaanee eqqiyo wodekka Leewati essona. Etappe harai ooninne akko shiiqikko, haiqqo.

English Sentences: And the children of Israel shall pitch their tents, every man by his own camp, and every man by his own standard, throughout their hosts.
Wolaitta Sentences: Israa7eela asati ubbai bantta armman armmaaninne bantta citan citan shaahettidi, bantta dunkkaaniyaa dunkkaanona.

English Sentences: But the Levites shall pitch round about the tabernacle of testimony, that there be no wrath upon the congregation of the children of Israel: and the Levites shall keep the charge of the tabernacle of testimony.
Wolaitta Sentences: SHin GODAA hanqqoi Israa7eela maabaraa bolli wodhdhenna mala, Leewati Xoossaa Dunkkaaniyaa yuushuwan bantta dunkkaaniyaa dunkkaanona; Leewati Xoossaa Dunkkaaniyan aawatona" yaagiis.

English Sentences: And the children of Israel did according to all that the LORD commanded Moses, so did they.
Wolaitta Sentences: Israa7eelati hagaa ubbaa GODAI Muusa azazidoogaadan oottidosona.

English Sentences: And the LORD spake unto Moses and unto Aaron, saying,
Wolaitta Sentences: GODAI Muusanne Aaroona hagaadan yaagiis;

English Sentences: Every man of the children of Israel shall pitch by his own standard, with the ensign of their father's house: far off about the tabernacle of the congregation shall they pitch.
Wolaitta Sentences: "Israa7eela asai bantta baggaa baggaa erissiya armmaanne bantta yaraa yaraa erissiya banddiraa kaallidi, Xoossaa Dunkkaaniyaappe guuttaa haakkidi, a yuushuwan dunkkaanona.

English Sentences: But the Levites were not numbered among the children of Israel; as the LORD commanded Moses.
Wolaitta Sentences: SHin GODAI Muusa azazidoogaadan, Leewati hara Israa7eelatuura qoodettibookkona.

English Sentences: And the children of Israel did according to all that the LORD commanded Moses: so they pitched by their standards, and so they set forward, every one after their families, according to the house of their fathers.
Wolaitta Sentences: Israa7eelati GODAI Muusa azazidobaa ubbabaa oottidosona. Simmi eti bantta banddiraa kaallidi, hegaadan dunkkaanidosona; qassi bantta yaraa yaraanne bantta so asaa asaa kaallidi, hegaadan kiyidosona.

English Sentences: These also are the generations of Aaron and Moses in the day that the LORD spake with Moses in mount Sinai.
Wolaitta Sentences: GODAI Siinaa Deriyaa bollan Muuseera haasayido wode de7iya Aaroonanne Muuse keettaa asai hagaappe kaallidi xaafettidaagaa.

English Sentences: And these are the names of the sons of Aaron; Nadab the firstborn, and Abihu, Eleazar, and Ithamar.
Wolaitta Sentences: Aaroona attuma naatu sunttai bairai Nadaaba, Abiiha, El77aazaranne Itaamaara.

English Sentences: These are the names of the sons of Aaron, the priests which were anointed, whom he consecrated to minister in the priest's office.
Wolaitta Sentences: He Aaroona attuma naati ubbai qeese gididi oottanau tiyettidi sunttettidosona.

English Sentences: And Nadab and Abihu died before the LORD, when they offered strange fire before the LORD, in the wilderness of Sinai, and they had no children: and Eleazar and Ithamar ministered in the priest's office in the sight of Aaron their father.
Wolaitta Sentences: SHin eta giddoppe Nadaabinne Abiihu Siinaa Bazzuwan GODAI azazibeenna tamaa yarshshidi, GODAA sinttan haiqqidosona; etau na7i baawa. Hegaa gishshau, eta aawai Aarooni paxa de7ido laitta ubban El77aazaranne Itaamaara xalaalai qeese gididi oottidosona.

English Sentences: And the LORD spake unto Moses, saying,
Wolaitta Sentences: GODAI Muusa hagaadan yaagiis;

English Sentences: Bring the tribe of Levi near, and present them before Aaron the priest, that they may minister unto him.
Wolaitta Sentences: "Leewata haa ekkada ya; ehaada qeesiyaa Aaroona maaddana mala, eta a sintti shiishsha.

English Sentences: And they shall keep his charge, and the charge of the whole congregation before the tabernacle of the congregation, to do the service of the tabernacle.
Wolaitta Sentences: Eti Aaroonaunne Israa7eela maabarau ubbau Xoossaa Dunkkaaniyaa sinttan dumma dumma oosuwaa oottona.

English Sentences: And they shall keep all the instruments of the tabernacle of the congregation, and the charge of the children of Israel, to do the service of the tabernacle.
Wolaitta Sentences: Eti Xoossaa Dunkkaaniyan de7iya miishsha ubbaa aawatettaa ekkona; ekkidi Israa7eela asaa gishshaa Xoossaa Dunkkaaniyan ooso ubbaa eti oottona.

English Sentences: And thou shalt give the Levites unto Aaron and to his sons: they are wholly given unto him out of the children of Israel.
Wolaitta Sentences: Neeni Leewata Aaroonanne a attuma naata maaddanaadan suntta; eti Israa7eela giddoppe muleera Aaroonayyo imettidosona.

English Sentences: And thou shalt appoint Aaron and his sons, and they shall wait on their priest's office: and the stranger that cometh nigh shall be put to death.
Wolaitta Sentences: Aaroonanne a attuma naata qeese oottada suntta. Etappe hara asi ooninne Xoossaa Dunkkaaniyaakko shiiqikko, haiqqo" yaagiis.

English Sentences: And the LORD spake unto Moses, saying,
Wolaitta Sentences: Qassi GODAI Muusa hagaadan yaagiis;

English Sentences: And I, behold, I have taken the Levites from among the children of Israel instead of all the firstborn that openeth the matrix among the children of Israel: therefore the Levites shall be mine;
Wolaitta Sentences: "Taani Israa7eelatu maccaasai baira yeliyo attuma naatu ubbaa gishshaa Israa7eelatu giddoppe Leewata ekkaas. Leewati tabaa;

English Sentences: Because all the firstborn are mine; for on the day that I smote all the firstborn in the land of Egypt I hallowed unto me all the firstborn in Israel, both man and beast: mine shall they be: I am the LORD.
Wolaitta Sentences: aissi giikko, baira yelettida ubbai tabaa. Taani Gibxxe biittan baira yelettidabaa ubbaa worido gallassan, Israa7eelatun baira yelettidabaa ubbaa, asa gidin, mehe gidin, taayyo dummayaas; eti tabaa gidana. Taani GODAATTENNEE" yaagiis.

English Sentences: And the LORD spake unto Moses in the wilderness of Sinai, saying,
Wolaitta Sentences: Qassikka GODAI Muusa Siinaa Bazzuwan,

English Sentences: Number the children of Levi after the house of their fathers, by their families: every male from a month old and upward shalt thou number them.
Wolaitta Sentences: "Neeni Leewata eta so asan asaaninne eta yaran yaran qooda; yelettoosappe issi aginanne hegaappe bollaara de7iya attumaageeta ubbaa qooda" yaagiis.

English Sentences: And Moses numbered them according to the word of the LORD, as he was commanded.
Wolaitta Sentences: Yaagin GODAI azazidoogaadan, Muusee eta qoodiis.

English Sentences: And these were the sons of Levi by their names; Gershon, and Kohath, and Merari.
Wolaitta Sentences: Leewa attuma naati Gershshoona, Qahaatanne Maraara.

English Sentences: And these are the names of the sons of Gershon by their families; Libni, and Shimei.
Wolaitta Sentences: Gershshoona attuma naati Liibinanne SHim77a.

English Sentences: And the sons of Kohath by their families; Amram, and Izehar, Hebron, and Uzziel.
Wolaitta Sentences: Qahaata attuma naati Amiraama, Yixihaara, Kebroonanne Uzzi7eela.

English Sentences: And the sons of Merari by their families; Mahli, and Mushi. These are the families of the Levites according to the house of their fathers.
Wolaitta Sentences: Maraara attuma naati qassi Maahilanne Musha. Leewatu maizza aawati hageeta.

English Sentences: Of Gershon was the family of the Libnites, and the family of the Shimites: these are the families of the Gershonites.
Wolaitta Sentences: Liibina yaratinne SHim77a yarati Gershshoona zareta.

English Sentences: Those that were numbered of them, according to the number of all the males, from a month old and upward, even those that were numbered of them were seven thousand and five hundred.
Wolaitta Sentences: Etappe qoodin, yelettoosappe issi aginanne hegaappe bollaara de7iya attumaageeti muleera 7,500.

English Sentences: The families of the Gershonites shall pitch behind the tabernacle westward.
Wolaitta Sentences: Gershshoona yarati Xoossaa Dunkkaaniyaappe guyye arggo baggaara dunkkaanoosona.

English Sentences: And the chief of the house of the father of the Gershonites shall be Eliasaph the son of Lael.
Wolaitta Sentences: Gershshoona yaratu so asaa halaqai Laa7eela na7aa Eliyasaafa.

English Sentences: And the charge of the sons of Gershon in the tabernacle of the congregation shall be the tabernacle, and the tent, the covering thereof, and the hanging for the door of the tabernacle of the congregation,
Wolaitta Sentences: Gershshoona yarati Xoossaa Dunkkaaniyaa, Dunkkaaniyaa kammiyoobata geliyoosa magalashuwaa,

English Sentences: And the hangings of the court, and the curtain for the door of the court, which is by the tabernacle, and by the altar round about, and the cords of it for all the service thereof.
Wolaitta Sentences: dabaabaa magalashota, Xoossaa Dunkkaaniyaanne yarshshiyoosaa yuushuwan de7iya dabaabaa geliyoosan magalashuwaa, wodorotanne eta go77aara gaittiyaabata ubbabaa aawatettaa ekkoosona.

English Sentences: And of Kohath was the family of the Amramites, and the family of the Izeharites, and the family of the Hebronites, and the family of the Uzzielites: these are the families of the Kohathites.
Wolaitta Sentences: Amiraama yarati, Yixihaara yarati, Kebroona yaratinne Uzzi7eela yarati Qahaata zareta.

English Sentences: In the number of all the males, from a month old and upward, were eight thousand and six hundred, keeping the charge of the sanctuary.
Wolaitta Sentences: Yelettoosappe issi aginanne hegaappe bollaara de7iya attumaageeti muleera 8,600. Qahaata yarati Xoossaa Dunkkaaniyaa aawatettaa ekkoosona.

English Sentences: The families of the sons of Kohath shall pitch on the side of the tabernacle southward.
Wolaitta Sentences: Qahaata yarati Xoossaa Dunkkaaniyaappe tohossa baggaara dunkkaanoosona.

English Sentences: And the chief of the house of the father of the families of the Kohathites shall be Elizaphan the son of Uzziel.
Wolaitta Sentences: Qahaata yaratu so asaa halaqai Uzzi7eela na7aa Elxxaafaana.

English Sentences: And their charge shall be the ark, and the table, and the candlestick, and the altars, and the vessels of the sanctuary wherewith they minister, and the hanging, and all the service thereof.
Wolaitta Sentences: Eti Taabootaa, xaraphpheezaa, xomppiyaa wottiyo ballaa, yarshshiyoosaa, ixaanaa cuwayiyo saaxiniyaa, oottiyo wode go7ettiyo Xoossaa Dunkkaaniyaa miishshata, magalashuwaanne eta go77aara gaittiyaabata ubbabaa aawatettaa ekkoosona.

English Sentences: And Eleazar the son of Aaron the priest shall be chief over the chief of the Levites, and have the oversight of them that keep the charge of the sanctuary.
Wolaitta Sentences: Leewatu halaqatu halaqai qeesiyaa Aaroona na7aa El77aazara; Geeshsha Sohuwaa aawatiyaageetu bolli i sunttettiis.

English Sentences: Of Merari was the family of the Mahlites, and the family of the Mushites: these are the families of Merari.
Wolaitta Sentences: Maahila yaratinne Musha yarati Maraara zareta.

English Sentences: And those that were numbered of them, according to the number of all the males, from a month old and upward, were six thousand and two hundred.
Wolaitta Sentences: Etappe qoodin, yelettoosappe issi aginanne hegaappe bollaara de7iya attumaageeti muleera 6,200.

English Sentences: And the chief of the house of the father of the families of Merari was Zuriel the son of Abihail: these shall pitch on the side of the tabernacle northward.
Wolaitta Sentences: Maraara yaratu so asaa halaqai Abihaila na7aa Xurii7eela. Maraara yarati Xoossaa Dunkkaaniyaappe huuphessa baggaara dunkkaanoosona.

English Sentences: And under the custody and charge of the sons of Merari shall be the boards of the tabernacle, and the bars thereof, and the pillars thereof, and the sockets thereof, and all the vessels thereof, and all that serveth thereto,
Wolaitta Sentences: Maraara yarati Dunkkaaniyaa xagaageta, hiraqota, tuussata, gedeta, he oosuwaassi koshshiya miishshata ubbaanne eta go77aara gaittiyaabata ubbaa aawatettaa ekkoosona.

English Sentences: And the pillars of the court round about, and their sockets, and their pins, and their cords.
Wolaitta Sentences: Hegaa bollikka gujjidi, yuushuwan de7iya dabaabaa tuussatanne eta gedeta, xishetanne wodorota aawatettaa ekkoosona.

English Sentences: But those that encamp before the tabernacle toward the east, even before the tabernacle of the congregation eastward, shall be Moses, and Aaron and his sons, keeping the charge of the sanctuary for the charge of the children of Israel; and the stranger that cometh nigh shall be put to death.
Wolaitta Sentences: Qassi Xoossaa Dunkkaaniyaappe sintta arshsho baggaara Muusee, Aarooninne a attuma naati dunkkaanoosona. Eti Israa7eelatu gishshaa Xoossaa Dunkkaane giddon oottiyo oosuwaa aawatettaa ekkoosona. Hara asi Xoossaa Dunkkaaniyaakko shiiqikko, haiqqo.

English Sentences: All that were numbered of the Levites, which Moses and Aaron numbered at the commandment of the LORD, throughout their families, all the males from a month old and upward, were twenty and two thousand.
Wolaitta Sentences: GODAI azazin, Muuseenne Aarooni qoodido attuma Leewati, yelettoosappe issi aginanne hegaappe bollaara de7iya attumaageeti muleera 22,000.

English Sentences: And the LORD said unto Moses, Number all the firstborn of the males of the children of Israel from a month old and upward, and take the number of their names.
Wolaitta Sentences: GODAI Muusa, "Israa7eelatu baira attuma naata, yelettoosappe issi aginanne hegaappe bollaara de7iyaageeta ubbaa qooda; qoodada eta sunttaa xaafa.

English Sentences: And thou shalt take the Levites for me (I am the LORD) instead of all the firstborn among the children of Israel; and the cattle of the Levites instead of all the firstlings among the cattle of the children of Israel.
Wolaitta Sentences: Israa7eelatun baira yelettida ubbaa gishshaa Leewata taayyo ekka; qassi Israa7eelatu mehiyan baira yelettida ubbaa gishshaa Leewatu mehiyaa taayyo ekka. Taani GODAATTENNEE" yaagiis.

English Sentences: And Moses numbered, as the LORD commanded him, all the firstborn among the children of Israel.
Wolaitta Sentences: Yaagin Muusee GODAI a azazidoogaadan, Israa7eelatun baira yelettida ubbaa qoodiis.

English Sentences: And all the firstborn males by the number of names, from a month old and upward, of those that were numbered of them, were twenty and two thousand two hundred and threescore and thirteen.
Wolaitta Sentences: Yelettoosappe issi aginanne hegaappe bollaara de7iya baira yelettida attumaageeti, sunttaikka xaafettidoogeeti muleera 22,273.

English Sentences: And the LORD spake unto Moses, saying,
Wolaitta Sentences: GODAI Muusa qassikka hagaadan yaagiis;

English Sentences: Take the Levites instead of all the firstborn among the children of Israel, and the cattle of the Levites instead of their cattle; and the Levites shall be mine: I am the LORD.
Wolaitta Sentences: "Leewata Israa7eela attumaageetu ubbaa gishshaa ekka; Leewatu meheta Israa7eelatu mehetu gishshaa ekka; Leewati tabaa gidana. Taani GODAATTENNEE.

English Sentences: And for those that are to be redeemed of the two hundred and threescore and thirteen of the firstborn of the children of Israel, which are more than the Levites;
Wolaitta Sentences: Leewatu qoodaappe dariya 273 baira gididi yelettida Israa7eela attuma naata wozanau,

English Sentences: Thou shalt even take five shekels apiece by the poll, after the shekel of the sanctuary shalt thou take them: (the shekel is twenty gerahs:)
Wolaitta Sentences: issuwaassi issuwaassi ichchashu xaqara biraa Xoossaa Dunkkaaniyan eriyo meezaanaa likkiyan ekka.

English Sentences: And thou shalt give the money, wherewith the odd number of them is to be redeemed, unto Aaron and to his sons.
Wolaitta Sentences: Palahida Israa7eelata woziyo he miishshaa Aaroonayyoonne a attuma naatuyyo imma" yaagiis.

English Sentences: And Moses took the redemption money of them that were over and above them that were redeemed by the Levites:
Wolaitta Sentences: Yaagin Muusee, Leewatun wozettidaageetuppe palahidaageeta woziyo miishshaa shiishshiis.

English Sentences: Of the firstborn of the children of Israel took he the money; a thousand three hundred and threescore and five shekels, after the shekel of the sanctuary:
Wolaitta Sentences: Baira yelettida Israa7eelatuppe 1,365 xaqara biraa Xoossaa Dunkkaaniyan eriyo meezaanaa likkiyan i shiishshiis;

English Sentences: And Moses gave the money of them that were redeemed unto Aaron and to his sons, according to the word of the LORD, as the LORD commanded Moses.
Wolaitta Sentences: shiishshidi GODAI azazido azazuwaadan, Muusee woziyo miishshaa Aaroonayyoonne a attuma naatuyyo immiis.

English Sentences: And the LORD spake unto Moses and unto Aaron, saying,
Wolaitta Sentences: GODAI Muusanne Aaroona hagaadan yaagiis;

English Sentences: Take the sum of the sons of Kohath from among the sons of Levi, after their families, by the house of their fathers,
Wolaitta Sentences: "Leewa zaretun Qahaata yarata eta dabbuwan dabbuwaaninne eta so asan asan shaakkada qooda;

English Sentences: From thirty years old and upward even until fifty years old, all that enter into the host, to do the work in the tabernacle of the congregation.
Wolaitta Sentences: yelettoosappe laittai hasttamaappe biidi ishatamaa gakkido attumaasa ubbaa, Xoossaa Dunkkaaniyaa giddon oottanau yiyaageeta qooda.

English Sentences: This shall be the service of the sons of Kohath in the tabernacle of the congregation, about the most holy things:
Wolaitta Sentences: Qahaata yarati Xoossaa Dunkkaaniyaa giddon oottana oosoi hagaa: eti ubbaappe aadhdhida geeshsha miishshatun aawatoosona.

English Sentences: And when the camp setteth forward, Aaron shall come, and his sons, and they shall take down the covering vail, and cover the ark of testimony with it:
Wolaitta Sentences: "Asai dunkkaanidosaappe baanau haniyo wode, Aarooninne a attuma naati Xoossaa Dunkkaaniyaa giddo gelidi, Taabootaa sintta magalashuwaa kaquwaappe wottona; wottidi he Maachchaa Taabootaa an kammona.

English Sentences: And shall put thereon the covering of badgers' skins, and shall spread over it a cloth wholly of blue, and shall put in the staves thereof.
Wolaitta Sentences: He kammidoogaa bollikka qassi irppaniyaa kammona; hegaa bollikka qassi gujjidi, salo milatiya carqqiyaa kammona; kammidi tookkiyo kasota eta sagaayotun aattona.

English Sentences: And upon the table of shewbread they shall spread a cloth of blue, and put thereon the dishes, and the spoons, and the bowls, and covers to cover withal: and the continual bread shall be thereon:
Wolaitta Sentences: "Aattidi GODAA sintti shiishshiyo oittaa wottiyo xaraphpheezaa bollan salo milatiya carqqiyaa hiixxona; hiixxidi a bolli saineta, cilppata, xuu7atanne ushshaa yarshshuwau go7ettiyo otota wottona; qassi oittai ubba wodekka a bollappe xayoppo.

English Sentences: And they shall spread upon them a cloth of scarlet, and cover the same with a covering of badgers' skins, and shall put in the staves thereof.
Wolaitta Sentences: Hegaa bollan zo7o carqqiyaa hiixxidi, irppaniyaa qassi a bolli kammona; kammidi tookkiyo kasota sagaayotun aattona.

English Sentences: And they shall take a cloth of blue, and cover the candlestick of the light, and his lamps, and his tongs, and his snuffdishes, and all the oil vessels thereof, wherewith they minister unto it:
Wolaitta Sentences: "Aattidi eti salo milatiya carqqiyaa ekkidi, xomppiyaa wottiyo ballata xomppetuura, toissiyo qaphetuura, eta wottiyoobatuuranne zaitiyaa tigiyo xaarotuurakka ubbaa kammona.

English Sentences: And they shall put it and all the vessels thereof within a covering of badgers' skins, and shall put it upon a bar.
Wolaitta Sentences: Yaatidi akka miishshata ubbaakka irppaniyan kammidi, tookkiyo halaa bollan wottona.

English Sentences: And upon the golden altar they shall spread a cloth of blue, and cover it with a covering of badgers' skins, and shall put to the staves thereof:
Wolaitta Sentences: "Wottidi ixaanaa cuwayiyo worqqa saaxiniyaa bollan salo milatiya carqqiyaa hiixxona; hiixxidoogaa qassi irppaniyan kammona; kammidi tookkiyo kasota eta sagaayotun aattona.

English Sentences: And they shall take all the instruments of ministry, wherewith they minister in the sanctuary, and put them in a cloth of blue, and cover them with a covering of badgers' skins, and shall put them on a bar:
Wolaitta Sentences: Hegaadankka, qassi Xoossaa Dunkkaaniyaa giddon go7ettiyo miishshata ubbaa ekkidi, salo milatiya carqqiyaa xaaxona; xaaxidoogaa irppaniyan kammidi, tookkiyo halaa bollan wottona.

English Sentences: And they shall take away the ashes from the altar, and spread a purple cloth thereon:
Wolaitta Sentences: "Yaatidi nahaasiyaappe oottido yarshshiyoosaa bolli de7iya bidinttaa diggona; diggidi a bolli ochchaa teera milatiya carqqiyaa hiixxona.

English Sentences: And they shall put upon it all the vessels thereof, wherewith they minister about it, even the censers, the fleshhooks, and the shovels, and the basons, all the vessels of the altar; and they shall spread upon it a covering of badgers' skins, and put to the staves of it.
Wolaitta Sentences: Hiixxidi a bolli yarshshiyoosan go7ettiyo miishshata ubbaa, tama cooceta, ashuwaa qaphiyo qapheta, akaafatanne araciyo kuixaarota wottona. Wottidi irppaniyan kammona; kammidi tookkiyo kasota eta sagaayotun aattona.

English Sentences: And when Aaron and his sons have made an end of covering the sanctuary, and all the vessels of the sanctuary, as the camp is to set forward; after that, the sons of Kohath shall come to bear it: but they shall not touch any holy thing, lest they die. These things are the burden of the sons of Kohath in the tabernacle of the congregation.
Wolaitta Sentences: "Aarooninne a attuma naati, geeshshabatanne geeshsha miishshata ubbaa kammidi makkobarenne dunkkaanidosaappe denddiyo wodee gakkobare, hegaa ubbaa tookkanau Qahaata yarati yoona. SHin geeshsha miishshata eti bochchoppona; bochchikko haiqqona. Xoossaa Dunkkaaniyaa giddon de7iya he miishshaa Qahaata yarati tookkona.

English Sentences: And to the office of Eleazar the son of Aaron the priest pertaineth the oil for the light, and the sweet incense, and the daily meat offering, and the anointing oil, and the oversight of all the tabernacle, and of all that therein is, in the sanctuary, and in the vessels thereof.
Wolaitta Sentences: "Qeesiyaa Aaroona na7ai El77aazari xomppiyaa zaitiyaassi, sawiya ixaanaassi, hachchi hachchi yarshshiyo kattaa yarshshuwaassinne tiyiyo zaitiyaassi, qassi Xoossaa Dunkkaaniyaa muliyaanne a giddon de7iya dumma geeshsha miishshata ubbaa bolli aawato" yaagiis.

English Sentences: And the LORD spake unto Moses and unto Aaron, saying,
Wolaitta Sentences: Qassi GODAI Muusanne Aaroona hagaadan yaagiis;

English Sentences: Cut ye not off the tribe of the families of the Kohathites from among the Levites:
Wolaitta Sentences: "Qahaata yarati Leewa zaretuppe haiqqidi xayenna mala xeellite.

English Sentences: But thus do unto them, that they may live, and not die, when they approach unto the most holy things: Aaron and his sons shall go in, and appoint them every one to his service and to his burden:
Wolaitta Sentences: Ubbaappe aadhdhida geeshsha miishshaa mati shiiqiyo wode, eti haiqqennan paxa attidi de7ana mala, etayyo hagaadan oottite: Aarooninne a attuma naati Xoossaa Dunkkaaniyaa giddo gelona; gelidi Qahaata yarati ubbai huuphiyan huuphiyan oottana oosuwaanne tookkana toohuwaa shaakki shaakkidi gishona.

English Sentences: But they shall not go in to see when the holy things are covered, lest they die.
Wolaitta Sentences: Qahaata yarati haiqqennaadan, ubbaappe aadhdhiya geeshshabata qeeseti xaaxishin be7anau giddo geloppona" yaagiis.

English Sentences: And the LORD spake unto Moses, saying,
Wolaitta Sentences: GODAI Muusa hagaadan yaagiis;

English Sentences: Take also the sum of the sons of Gershon, throughout the houses of their fathers, by their families;
Wolaitta Sentences: "Gershshoona yaratakka eta dabbuwan dabbuwaaninne eta so asan asan shaakkada qooda;

English Sentences: From thirty years old and upward until fifty years old shalt thou number them; all that enter in to perform the service, to do the work in the tabernacle of the congregation.
Wolaitta Sentences: yelettoosappe laittai hasttamaappe biidi ishatamaa gakkido attumaasa ubbaa, Xoossaa Dunkkaaniyaa giddon oottanau yiyaageeta qooda.

English Sentences: This is the service of the families of the Gershonites, to serve, and for burdens:
Wolaitta Sentences: "Gershshoona yarati oottiyo oosoinne tookkiyo toohoi hagaa:

English Sentences: And they shall bear the curtains of the tabernacle, and the tabernacle of the congregation, his covering, and the covering of the badgers' skins that is above upon it, and the hanging for the door of the tabernacle of the congregation,
Wolaitta Sentences: eti Xoossaa Dunkkaaniyaa magalashota, Xoossaa Dunkkaaniyaa, a kammiyoobatanne bollaara kammiyo irppaniyaa, Xoossaa Dunkkaaniyaa geliyoosan kaqqiyo magalashuwaa tookkona;

English Sentences: And the hangings of the court, and the hanging for the door of the gate of the court, which is by the tabernacle and by the altar round about, and their cords, and all the instruments of their service, and all that is made for them: so shall they serve.
Wolaitta Sentences: qassi Xoossaa Dunkkaaniyaanne yarshshiyoosaa yuuyi aadhdhida dabaabaa magalashota, dabaabaa geliyoosaa magalashuwaa, wodorotanne etayyo go77iya miishshata ubbaa tookkona. Gershshoona yarati ha miishshatun oottanau bessiya ooso ubbaa oottona.

English Sentences: At the appointment of Aaron and his sons shall be all the service of the sons of the Gershonites, in all their burdens, and in all their service: and ye shall appoint unto them in charge all their burdens.
Wolaitta Sentences: Tookkiyoobaa gidin, hara ooso gidinkka eti oottiyo ooso ubbai Aarooninne a attuma naati eta azazin oosettona. Neeni eti tookkanau bessiyaabata ubbaa eta aawatettaa aawatettaadan etau gisha.

English Sentences: This is the service of the families of the sons of Gershon in the tabernacle of the congregation: and their charge shall be under the hand of Ithamar the son of Aaron the priest.
Wolaitta Sentences: Xoossaa Dunkkaaniyaa giddon Gershshoona yarati oottana oosoi muleera hagaa. Eti oottana ooso ubbai qeesiyaa Aaroona na7aa Itaamaara aawatettaa garssaana gidana.

English Sentences: As for the sons of Merari, thou shalt number them after their families, by the house of their fathers;
Wolaitta Sentences: "Maraara yarata eta dabbuwan dabbuwaaninne eta so asan asan shaakkada qooda;

English Sentences: From thirty years old and upward even unto fifty years old shalt thou number them, every one that entereth into the service, to do the work of the tabernacle of the congregation.
Wolaitta Sentences: yelettoosappe laittai hasttamaappe biidi ishatamaa gakkido attumaasa ubbaa, Xoossaa Dunkkaaniyaa giddon oottanau yiyaageeta qooda.

English Sentences: And this is the charge of their burden, according to all their service in the tabernacle of the congregation; the boards of the tabernacle, and the bars thereof, and the pillars thereof, and sockets thereof,
Wolaitta Sentences: "Eti Xoossaa Dunkkaaniyaa giddon oottana oosoti hageeta: eta Dunkkaaniyaa xagaageta, hiraqota, tuussatanne gedeta,

English Sentences: And the pillars of the court round about, and their sockets, and their pins, and their cords, with all their instruments, and with all their service: and by name ye shall reckon the instruments of the charge of their burden.
Wolaitta Sentences: qassikka dabaabaa yuushuwan eqqiya tuussata, he tuussatu gedeta, toliyo xisheta, wodorota, hegeetussi koshshiya miishshata ubbaanne he miishshatuura gaittiyaabata ubbaa tookkona. Issi issi uraassi i tookkanabaa shaakkada gisha.

English Sentences: This is the service of the families of the sons of Merari, according to all their service, in the tabernacle of the congregation, under the hand of Ithamar the son of Aaron the priest.
Wolaitta Sentences: Xoossaa Dunkkaaniyaa giddon Maraara yarati oottana oosoi muleera hagaa. Eti oottana ooso ubbai qeesiyaa Aaroona na7aa Itaamaara aawatettaa garssaana gidana" yaagiis.

English Sentences: And Moses and Aaron and the chief of the congregation numbered the sons of the Kohathites after their families, and after the house of their fathers,
Wolaitta Sentences: Muusee Aarooninne maabaraa halaqati Qahaata yaratu attumaasaa eta dabbuwan dabbuwaaninne eta so asan asan shaakkidi qoodidosona.

English Sentences: From thirty years old and upward even unto fifty years old, every one that entereth into the service, for the work in the tabernacle of the congregation:
Wolaitta Sentences: Yelettoosappe laittai hasttamaappe biidi ishatamaa gakkido attumaasati ubbati, Xoossaa Dunkkaaniyaa giddon oottanau yiyaageeti,

English Sentences: And those that were numbered of them by their families were two thousand seven hundred and fifty.
Wolaitta Sentences: eta so asan asan qoodin muleera 2,750.

English Sentences: These were they that were numbered of the families of the Kohathites, all that might do service in the tabernacle of the congregation, which Moses and Aaron did number according to the commandment of the LORD by the hand of Moses.
Wolaitta Sentences: Qahaata yaratun Xoossaa Dunkkaaniyaa giddon oottida asaa qoodai hagaa. GODAI Muuse baggaara azazidoogaadan, Muuseenne Aarooni eta qoodidosona.

English Sentences: And those that were numbered of the sons of Gershon, throughout their families, and by the house of their fathers,
Wolaitta Sentences: Gershshoona yaratikka bantta dabbuwan dabbuwaaninne bantta so asan asan shaahettidi qoodettidosona.

English Sentences: From thirty years old and upward even unto fifty years old, every one that entereth into the service, for the work in the tabernacle of the congregation,
Wolaitta Sentences: Yelettoosappe laittai hasttamaappe biidi ishatamaa gakkido attumaasati ubbati, Xoossaa Dunkkaaniyaa giddon oottanau yiyaageeti,

English Sentences: Even those that were numbered of them, throughout their families, by the house of their fathers, were two thousand and six hundred and thirty.
Wolaitta Sentences: eta so asan asan qoodin muleera 2,630.

English Sentences: These are they that were numbered of the families of the sons of Gershon, of all that might do service in the tabernacle of the congregation, whom Moses and Aaron did number according to the commandment of the LORD.
Wolaitta Sentences: Gershshoona yaratun Xoossaa Dunkkaaniyaa giddon oottida asaa qoodin hagaa. GODAI Muuse baggaara azazidoogaadan, Muuseenne Aarooni eta qoodidosona.

English Sentences: And those that were numbered of the families of the sons of Merari, throughout their families, by the house of their fathers,
Wolaitta Sentences: Maraara yaratikka qassi dabbuwan dabbuwaaninne bantta so asan asan shaahettidi qoodettidosona.

English Sentences: From thirty years old and upward even unto fifty years old, every one that entereth into the service, for the work in the tabernacle of the congregation,
Wolaitta Sentences: Yelettoosappe laittai hasttamaappe biidi ishatamaa gakkido attumaasati ubbati, Xoossaa Dunkkaaniyaa giddon oottanau yiyaageeti,

English Sentences: Even those that were numbered of them after their families, were three thousand and two hundred.
Wolaitta Sentences: eta so asan asan qoodin muleera 3,200.

English Sentences: These be those that were numbered of the families of the sons of Merari, whom Moses and Aaron numbered according to the word of the LORD by the hand of Moses.
Wolaitta Sentences: Maraara yaratu qoodai hagaa. GODAI Muuse baggaara azazidoogaadan, Muuseenne Aarooni eta qoodidosona.

English Sentences: All those that were numbered of the Levites, whom Moses and Aaron and the chief of Israel numbered, after their families, and after the house of their fathers,
Wolaitta Sentences: Hegaa oottidi Muusee, Aarooninne Israa7eela halaqati Leewata ubbaa, eta yaran yaraaninne eta so asan asan shaakkidi qoodidosona.

English Sentences: From thirty years old and upward even unto fifty years old, every one that came to do the service of the ministry, and the service of the burden in the tabernacle of the congregation,
Wolaitta Sentences: Yelettoosappe laittai hasttamaappe biidi ishatamaa gakkido attumaasati ubbati, Xoossaa Dunkkaaniyaa giddon oosuwaa oottanaunne ayyo go77iya miishshata ubbaa tookkanau yiidaageeti

English Sentences: Even those that were numbered of them, were eight thousand and five hundred and fourscore.
Wolaitta Sentences: muleera 8,580.

English Sentences: According to the commandment of the LORD they were numbered by the hand of Moses, every one according to his service, and according to his burden: thus were they numbered of him, as the LORD commanded Moses.
Wolaitta Sentences: GODAI Muuse baggaara azazidoogaadan, eti huuphiyan huuphiyan oottana oosoi woikko tookkana toohoikka etau odettiis. GODAI Muusa azazidoogaadan, eti ubbaikka qoodettidosona.

English Sentences: And the LORD spake unto Moses, saying,
Wolaitta Sentences: GODAI Muusa hagaadan yaagiis;

English Sentences: Command the children of Israel, that they put out of the camp every leper, and every one that hath an issue, and whosoever is defiled by the dead:
Wolaitta Sentences: "Neeni Israa7eelata, Intte giddon hanttaara goga harggee oiqqido uraa, woikko bollaappe aibakko uzuuziyo uraa, woikko ahaa oiqqidi tunida uraa oonakka intte dunkkaanidosaappe kessirggite yaagada azaza.

English Sentences: Both male and female shall ye put out, without the camp shall ye put them; that they defile not their camps, in the midst whereof I dwell.
Wolaitta Sentences: Hegee maccaa attumaa gidinkka kessona. Taani eta gidduwan de7iyo eti dunkkaanidosaa hegeeti tunissenna mala, eta dunkkaanidosaappe kessa yedda" yaagiis.

English Sentences: And the children of Israel did so, and put them out without the camp: as the LORD spake unto Moses, so did the children of Israel.
Wolaitta Sentences: Yaagin GODAI Muusa azazidoogaadan, Israa7eelati eta ubbaa dunkkaanidosaappe kessidi yeddidosona.

English Sentences: And the LORD spake unto Moses, saying,
Wolaitta Sentences: Hegaappe guyyiyan, GODAI Muusa hagaadan yaagiis;

English Sentences: Speak unto the children of Israel, When a man or woman shall commit any sin that men commit, to do a trespass against the LORD, and that person be guilty;
Wolaitta Sentences: "Neeni Israa7eelata hagaadan yaaga; Issi attumaasi woikko issi maccaasi ai ogiyaaninne hara asa naaqqikkonne hegan GODAASSI ammanettennan ixxikko, he urai mooranchcha.

English Sentences: Then they shall confess their sin which they have done: and he shall recompense his trespass with the principal thereof, and add unto it the fifth part thereof, and give it unto him against whom he hath trespassed.
Wolaitta Sentences: Hegaa gishshau, i ba oottido nagaraa paaxo; paaxidi ba mooridobaa kumettaa zaaridi qanxxo; hegaa bollikka ichchashantta kushiyaa gujjidi, ba naaqqido uraassi edato.

English Sentences: But if the man have no kinsman to recompense the trespass unto, let the trespass be recompensed unto the LORD, even to the priest; beside the ram of the atonement, whereby an atonement shall be made for him.
Wolaitta Sentences: SHin he naaqettida uri haiqqidaba gidikkonne, edaa ekkanau au mata dabboi xayikko, he edai GODAASSA. He edatiyo edai naaqqida urai maarettanau yarshshuwaassi immiyo dorssa orggiyaara issippe qeesiyaayyo imetto.

English Sentences: And every offering of all the holy things of the children of Israel, which they bring unto the priest, shall be his.
Wolaitta Sentences: Qassi Israa7eelati qeesiyaassi immiyo geeshsha imo ubbai he qeesiyaassa.

English Sentences: And every man's hallowed things shall be his: whatsoever any man giveth the priest, it shall be his.
Wolaitta Sentences: Issi issi asi immiyo imotai he immida uraabaa; shin qeesiyaassi i immiyo imotai he qeesiyaassa yaaga" yaagiis.

English Sentences: And the LORD spake unto Moses, saying,
Wolaitta Sentences: Hegaappe guyyiyan GODAI Muusa,

English Sentences: Speak unto the children of Israel, and say unto them, If any man's wife go aside, and commit a trespass against him,
Wolaitta Sentences: "Neeni Israa7eelatussi hagaadan yaagada yoota; Issi uraa keettaayyiyaa kare hemettada, ayyo ammanettennan ixxada,

English Sentences: And a man lie with her carnally, and it be hid from the eyes of her husband, and be kept close, and she be defiled, and there be no witness against her, neither she be taken with the manner;
Wolaitta Sentences: hara attuma asaara zin77ikko, qassi hegaa a ba keettaawaappe qosikko, markkai bainnabaa gidikkonne, a shaaramuxaidda ohettennan attikko,

English Sentences: And the spirit of jealousy come upon him, and he be jealous of his wife, and she be defiled: or if the spirit of jealousy come upon him, and he be jealous of his wife, and she be not defiled:
Wolaitta Sentences: a tunido gishshau, i keettaawai o siriyaagaa gidanau danddayees; woikko a tunennan de7ishin, i ba keettaayyiyo siriyaagaa gidanau danddayees.

English Sentences: Then shall the man bring his wife unto the priest, and he shall bring her offering for her, the tenth part of an ephah of barley meal; he shall pour no oil upon it, nor put frankincense thereon; for it is an offering of jealousy, an offering of memorial, bringing iniquity to remembrance.
Wolaitta Sentences: Yaatikko, he bitanee ba keettaayyiyo qeesiyaakko efo; qassi i gishshau yarshshanau issi kilo giraame banggaa xiilliyaa efo. SHin xiilliyaa bolli zaitiyaa tigoppo, woikko ixaanaa a bolli wottoppo; aissi giikko, he xiillee i ba keettaayyiyo sirido gishshau yarshshiyo kattaa yarshsho; qassi i mooruwaa qonccissiya yarshsho.

English Sentences: And the priest shall bring her near, and set her before the LORD:
Wolaitta Sentences: "Hegaappe guyyiyan, qeesee he mishiriyo shiishshidi, GODAA sinttan esso.

English Sentences: And the priest shall take holy water in an earthen vessel; and of the dust that is in the floor of the tabernacle the priest shall take, and put it into the water:
Wolaitta Sentences: Essidi anjjettida haattaa kuixaaruwan ekko. Hegaappe guyyiyan, Xoossaa Dunkkaaniyaa wuigen de7iya buhiyaa ekkidi, he haattan gujjo.

English Sentences: And the priest shall set the woman before the LORD, and uncover the woman's head, and put the offering of memorial in her hands, which is the jealousy offering: and the priest shall have in his hand the bitter water that causeth the curse:
Wolaitta Sentences: Gujjidi he mishiriyo GODAA sinttan esso; hegaappe guyyiyan, he mishiree huuphiyaa birshsho; birshshidi sirido gishshau yarshshiyo i mooruwaa qonccissiya kattaa yarshshuwaa i kushiyan wotto; qassi he qeesee ba kushiyan qanggettaa ehiya camo haattaa kuixaaruwaara oiqqo.

English Sentences: And the priest shall charge her by an oath, and say unto the woman, If no man have lain with thee, and if thou hast not gone aside to uncleanness with another instead of thy husband, be thou free from this bitter water that causeth the curse:
Wolaitta Sentences: Oiqqidi mishiriyo hagaadan yaagidi caaqetto; "Neeni hara attumaasaara zin77abeennaba gidikkonne, ne keettaawaa aggada kare hemettada tunabeennaba gidikko, qanggettaa ehiya ha camo haattai neeyyo gometoppo.

English Sentences: But if thou hast gone aside to another instead of thy husband, and if thou be defiled, and some man have lain with thee beside thine husband:
Wolaitta Sentences: SHin neeni ne keettaawaa aggada kare hemettada tunidobaa gidikkonne, hara attuma asaara zin77idaba gidikko,

English Sentences: Then the priest shall charge the woman with an oath of cursing, and the priest shall say unto the woman, The LORD make thee a curse and an oath among thy people, when the LORD doth make thy thigh to rot, and thy belly to swell;
Wolaitta Sentences: GODAI ne yelo keettaa gunddissiyoogaaninne ne uluwaakka puurissiyoogan, ne asan nena qanggisso.

English Sentences: And this water that causeth the curse shall go into thy bowels, to make thy belly to swell, and thy thigh to rot: And the woman shall say, Amen, amen.
Wolaitta Sentences: Ha qanggettaa ehiya haattai ne ulo giddo gelo; gelidi ne uluwaa puurisso; ne yelo keettaakka gunddisso" yaagidi caaqetto. "Mishiriyaakka, "Amin77i; amin77i" yaagu.

English Sentences: And the priest shall write these curses in a book, and he shall blot them out with the bitter water:
Wolaitta Sentences: "Hegaappe guyyiyan, qeesee ha qanggettata xaaxettida maxaafan xaafo; xaafido qanggettata camo haattaa giddo meecco.

English Sentences: And he shall cause the woman to drink the bitter water that causeth the curse: and the water that causeth the curse shall enter into her, and become bitter.
Wolaitta Sentences: Yaatidi qanggettaa ehiya he camo haattaa mishiriyo ushsho; qanggettaa ehiya haattai mishiree uluwan gelidi, o camo sahuwaa sakkana.

English Sentences: Then the priest shall take the jealousy offering out of the woman's hand, and shall wave the offering before the LORD, and offer it upon the altar:
Wolaitta Sentences: Qeesee mishiree kushiyaappe sirido gishshau yarshshiyo kattaa yarshshuwaa ekkidi, he yarshshuwaa GODAA sinttan wuxaawuxidi, yarshshiyoosaa eho.

English Sentences: And the priest shall take an handful of the offering, even the memorial thereof, and burn it upon the altar, and afterward shall cause the woman to drink the water.
Wolaitta Sentences: Ehiidi qeesee kattaa yarshshuwaappe zolliyaagaa ekko; ekkidoogaa mooruwaa qonccissiya yarshsho oottidi, yarshshiyoosan xuuggo. Hegaappe guyyiyan, mishiriyo he haattaa ushsho.

English Sentences: And when he hath made her to drink the water, then it shall come to pass, that, if she be defiled, and have done trespass against her husband, that the water that causeth the curse shall enter into her, and become bitter, and her belly shall swell, and her thigh shall rot: and the woman shall be a curse among her people.
Wolaitta Sentences: Haattaa o ushshidoogaappe guyyiyan, hagaadan hanana: a ba keettaawaassi ammanettana xayada tunidabaa gidikko, qanggettaa ehiya haattai i uluwan gelidi, o camo sahuwaa sakkana; i uloikka puurana; i yelo keettaikka gunddana. A ba asan qanggettidaaro gidana.

English Sentences: And if the woman be not defiled, but be clean; then she shall be free, and shall conceive seed.
Wolaitta Sentences: SHin a tunabeenna xillo maccaasa gidikko, a saro attada naata yelana.

English Sentences: This is the law of jealousies, when a wife goeth aside to another instead of her husband, and is defiled;
Wolaitta Sentences: "Issi asi ba keettaayyiyo siriyo wode oottana wogai hagaa. A kare hemettada tunikko,

English Sentences: Or when the spirit of jealousy cometh upon him, and he be jealous over his wife, and shall set the woman before the LORD, and the priest shall execute upon her all this law.
Wolaitta Sentences: woikko issi asi ba keettaayyiyo sirikko, GODAA sinttan o esso; essidi qeesee ha wogaa ubbaa i bolli polo.

English Sentences: Then shall the man be guiltless from iniquity, and this woman shall bear her iniquity.
Wolaitta Sentences: Polobare keettaawai mooro ubbaappe saro attana; shin maccaasiyaa ba nagaraa gaasuwan yiyaabaa tookkana yaaga" yaagiis.

English Sentences: And the LORD spake unto Moses, saying,
Wolaitta Sentences: GODAI Muusa hagaadan yaagiis,

English Sentences: Speak unto the children of Israel, and say unto them, When either man or woman shall separate themselves to vow a vow of a Nazarite, to separate themselves unto the LORD:
Wolaitta Sentences: "Neeni Israa7eela asaassi hagaadan yaagada yoota; Attuma asi woikko macca asi Naaziraawe gididi, bana GODAAYYO dummayanau geppikko,

English Sentences: He shall separate himself from wine and strong drink, and shall drink no vinegar of wine, or vinegar of strong drink, neither shall he drink any liquor of grapes, nor eat moist grapes, or dried.
Wolaitta Sentences: woiniyaa eessaanne hara mattoyiya ushshaa uyoppo; woiniyaa aifiyaappe agettiya caalabaanne mattoyiyaabaa uyoppo; woiniyaa teeraa gum77idoogaa uyoppo. Woikko woiniyaa teeraa shuguwaa gidin, melaa gidinkka mooppo;

English Sentences: All the days of his separation shall he eat nothing that is made of the vine tree, from the kernels even to the husk.
Wolaitta Sentences: i bana dummayido wodiyan ubban, woine turaappe beettiyaabaa ubbaa, woiniyaa zerettaa gidin, woikko woiniyaa poquwaa gidinkka mooppo.

English Sentences: All the days of the vow of his separation there shall no razor come upon his head: until the days be fulfilled, in the which he separateth himself unto the LORD, he shall be holy, and shall let the locks of the hair of his head grow.
Wolaitta Sentences: "I bana GODAAYYO dummayanau geppido wodiyan ubban, a huuphee meedettoppo woikko qanxxettoppo. I ba huuphiyaa binnaanaakka adussidi dichcho. I bana GODAAYYO dummayido wodee polettana gakkanaassi, geeshsha gidanau koshshees.

English Sentences: All the days that he separateth himself unto the LORD he shall come at no dead body.
Wolaitta Sentences: "I bana GODAAYYO dummayido wodiyan ubban ahaakko shiiqoppo.

English Sentences: He shall not make himself unclean for his father, or for his mother, for his brother, or for his sister, when they die: because the consecration of his God is upon his head.
Wolaitta Sentences: Harai attin a aawai, woikko a aayyiyaa, woikko a ishai, woikko a michchiyaa haiqqikkokka, i bana tunissoppo. Aissi giikko, i bana Xoossaassi dummayidoogaa erissiyoi ba huuphiyaana.

English Sentences: All the days of his separation he is holy unto the LORD.
Wolaitta Sentences: I bana GODAAYYO dummayido wodiyan ubban i GODAASSI geeshsha.

English Sentences: And if any man die very suddenly by him, and he hath defiled the head of his consecration; then he shall shave his head in the day of his cleansing, on the seventh day shall he shave it.
Wolaitta Sentences: "Asi a matan akeekennan haiqqin, GODAAYYO dummayido a huuphee tunikko, laappun gallassaa gam77idi, ba geeyiyo he laappuntta gallassi ba huuphiyaa meedetto.

English Sentences: And on the eighth day he shall bring two turtles, or two young pigeons, to the priest, to the door of the tabernacle of the congregation:
Wolaitta Sentences: Hosppuntta gallassan naa77u haraphpheta woikko naa77u mara haraphpheta Xoossaa Dunkkaaniyaa pengge qeesiyaayyo eho.

English Sentences: And the priest shall offer the one for a sin offering, and the other for a burnt offering, and make an atonement for him, for that he sinned by the dead, and shall hallow his head that same day.
Wolaitta Sentences: Ehin qeesee haraphphetuppe issuwaa nagaraa yarshshuwau, issuwaa qassi xuuggiyo yarshshuwau yarshsho. Aissi giikko, ahai a mati shiiqido mooruwaa gishshau, ayyo atto giissanaassa. He gallassi i ba huuphiyaa wogaadan geeshsho;

English Sentences: And he shall consecrate unto the LORD the days of his separation, and shall bring a lamb of the first year for a trespass offering: but the days that were before shall be lost, because his separation was defiled.
Wolaitta Sentences: i bana kase geppido wodiyaa keenaa bana GODAAYYO dummayanau koshshees. Yaatidi yelettoosappe issi laitta gidiyo attuma dorssaa naaquwaassi immiyo yarshsho oottidi yarshsho. SHin hegaappe kase i bana GODAAYYO dummayido gallassati qoodettokkona; aissi giikko, i bana dummayido he wodetu giddon bana tunissirggiis.

English Sentences: And this is the law of the Nazarite, when the days of his separation are fulfilled: he shall be brought unto the door of the tabernacle of the congregation:
Wolaitta Sentences: "Ba gefaa wodiyaa wurssido wode bana GODAAYYO dummayida Naaziraawiyaa wogai hagaa: Xoossaa Dunkkaaniyaa pengge i shiiqo;

English Sentences: And he shall offer his offering unto the LORD, one he lamb of the first year without blemish for a burnt offering, and one ewe lamb of the first year without blemish for a sin offering, and one ram without blemish for peace offerings,
Wolaitta Sentences: shiiqiiddi GODAAYYO tilla bollaara de7iya issi laitta attuma dorssaa xuuggiyo yarshshuwau, tilla bollaara de7iya issi laitta dorssiyo nagaraa yarshshuwaunne tilla bollaara de7iya dorssa orggiyaa issippetettaa yarshshuwau he sohuwaa eho.

English Sentences: And a basket of unleavened bread, cakes of fine flour mingled with oil, and wafers of unleavened bread anointed with oil, and their meat offering, and their drink offerings.
Wolaitta Sentences: Qassi kattaa yarshshuwaanne ushshaa yarshshuwaa etaara issippe yarshshanau eho; he kattaa yarshshoi irshshoi gelibeennaagaa gido; qassi zaitiyan munaqqido liiqo xiilliyaa komppotanne zaitiyaa tiyido lee7e lichchakkota masoofiyan eho.

English Sentences: And the priest shall bring them before the LORD, and shall offer his sin offering, and his burnt offering:
Wolaitta Sentences: "Ehin qeesee hegaa ubbaa shiishshidi, nagaraa yarshshonne xuuggiyo yarshsho oottidi, GODAAYYO a gishshaa yarshsho.

English Sentences: And he shall offer the ram for a sacrifice of peace offerings unto the LORD, with the basket of unleavened bread: the priest shall offer also his meat offering, and his drink offering.
Wolaitta Sentences: Qeesee dorssa orggiyaa, irshshoi gelibeenna komppotanne lichchakkota issippetettaa yarshsho oottidi, GODAASSI yarshsho. Qassi hegaara issippe kattaa yarshshuwaanne ushshaa yarshshuwaa yarshsho.

English Sentences: And the Nazarite shall shave the head of his separation at the door of the tabernacle of the congregation, and shall take the hair of the head of his separation, and put it in the fire which is under the sacrifice of the peace offerings.
Wolaitta Sentences: Hegaappe guyyiyan, Naaziraawee GODAAYYO dummayido ba huuphiyaa Xoossaa Dunkkaaniyaa penggen meedetto; meedettido binnaanaa efiidi, issippetettaa yarshshuwaappe garssa baggaara de7iya taman yeggo.

English Sentences: And the priest shall take the sodden shoulder of the ram, and one unleavened cake out of the basket, and one unleavened wafer, and shall put them upon the hands of the Nazarite, after the hair of his separation is shaven:
Wolaitta Sentences: "Bana GODAAYYO dummayida Naaziraawee ba huuphiyaa meedettidoogaappe guyyiyan, qeesee doisettida dorssa orggiyaa missaa, irshshoi gelibeenna issi komppuwaanne issi lee7e lichchakkuwaa ekkidi, ha Naaziraawiyaa kushiyan wotto.

English Sentences: And the priest shall wave them for a wave offering before the LORD: this is holy for the priest, with the wave breast and heave shoulder: and after that the Nazarite may drink wine.
Wolaitta Sentences: Wottidi qeesee eta wuxaawuxo yarshsho oottidi, GODAA sinttan wuxaawuxo. Yaatobare hegeeti wuxaawuxido anggaasuwaaranne yarshshido gedaara geeshshanne qeesiyaassa. Hegaappe guyyiyan, GODAAYYO bana dummayida Naaziraawee woiniyaa eessaa uyana giikko uyo.

English Sentences: This is the law of the Nazarite who hath vowed, and of his offering unto the LORD for his separation, beside that that his hand shall get: according to the vow which he vowed, so he must do after the law of his separation.
Wolaitta Sentences: "Simmi GODAASSI bana dummayanau geppida Naaziraawiyaassi wotto wogai hagaa: bana GODAASSI yarshshanau koshshiya yarshshotuppe aadhdhiyaabaa immanau geppidabaa gidikko, i ba geppido gefaa keenaa gattanau koshshees yaaga" yaagiis.

English Sentences: And the LORD spake unto Moses, saying,
Wolaitta Sentences: GODAI Muusa hagaadan yaagiis;

English Sentences: Speak unto Aaron and unto his sons, saying, On this wise ye shall bless the children of Israel, saying unto them,
Wolaitta Sentences: "Aaroonassinne a attuma naatussi hagaa yoota; Israa7eela asaa intte hagaadan yaagidi anjjite;

English Sentences: The LORD bless thee, and keep thee:
Wolaitta Sentences: "GODAI inttena anjjonne inttena naago;

English Sentences: The LORD make his face shine upon thee, and be gracious unto thee:
Wolaitta Sentences: GODAI intteyyo ba som77uwaa poo7issonne intteyyo qaretto;

English Sentences: The LORD lift up his countenance upon thee, and give thee peace.
Wolaitta Sentences: GODAI inttena ba keha aifiyan xeellonne intteyyo sarotettaa immo" yaagidi anjjite yaaga.

English Sentences: And they shall put my name upon the children of Israel; and I will bless them.
Wolaitta Sentences: "Eti Israa7eela asaa ta sunttan anjjiyo wode, taani eta anjjana" yaagiis.

English Sentences: And it came to pass on the day that Moses had fully set up the tabernacle, and had anointed it, and sanctified it, and all the instruments thereof, both the altar and all the vessels thereof, and had anointed them, and sanctified them;
Wolaitta Sentences: Muusee Xoossaa Dunkkaaniyaa tolidi makkido wode, he Dunkkaaniyaanne a miishshaa ubbaa tiyidi geeshshiis; qassi yarshshiyoosaanne a miishshaa ubbaakka tiyidi geeshshiis.

English Sentences: That the princes of Israel, heads of the house of their fathers, who were the princes of the tribes, and were over them that were numbered, offered:
Wolaitta Sentences: Hegaappe guyyiyan, Israa7eela asaa kaalettidaageeti, hegeetenne zareta qoodida so asaa halaqati

English Sentences: And they brought their offering before the LORD, six covered wagons, and twelve oxen; a wagon for two of the princes, and for each one an ox: and they brought them before the tabernacle.
Wolaitta Sentences: GODAAYYO imota shiishshidosona; hegeetikka kamettida usuppun gaareta, tammanne naa77u boorata, halaqan halaqan issi issi booraanne naa77u naa77u halaqati issi issi gaariyaa Xoossaa Dunkkaaniyaa ehiidosona.

English Sentences: And the LORD spake unto Moses, saying,
Wolaitta Sentences: GODAI Muusa hagaadan yaagiis;

English Sentences: Take it of them, that they may be to do the service of the tabernacle of the congregation; and thou shalt give them unto the Levites, to every man according to his service.
Wolaitta Sentences: "Xoossaa Dunkkaaniyaa oosuwaassi go77ana mala, neeni hegeeta etappe ekkada, Leewatuyyo eta oosuwaassi oosuwaassi koshshiyaadan shaakkada imma" yaagiis.

English Sentences: And Moses took the wagons and the oxen, and gave them unto the Levites.
Wolaitta Sentences: Yaagin Muusee gaaretanne boorata ekkidi, Leewatuyyo immiis.

English Sentences: Two wagons and four oxen he gave unto the sons of Gershon, according to their service:
Wolaitta Sentences: Gershshoona yaratuyyo eta oosuwaassi koshshiyoogaadan shaakkidi, naa77u gaaretanne oiddu boorata immiis.

English Sentences: And four wagons and eight oxen he gave unto the sons of Merari, according unto their service, under the hand of Ithamar the son of Aaron the priest.
Wolaitta Sentences: Qassi Maraara yaratuyyo eta oosuwaassi koshshiyoogaadan shaakkidi, oiddu gaaretanne hosppun boorata immiis. Eti ubbaikka qeesiyaa Aaroona na7aa Itaamaara aawatettaa garssaana.

English Sentences: But unto the sons of Kohath he gave none: because the service of the sanctuary belonging unto them was that they should bear upon their shoulders.
Wolaitta Sentences: SHin Muusee Qahaata yaratussi hegaappe aibanne immibeenna; aissi giikko, eta aawatettan de7iya geeshsha miishshati bantta hashiyan tookkanau koshshiyaageeta gidiyo gishshaassa.

English Sentences: And the princes offered for dedicating of the altar in the day that it was anointed, even the princes offered their offering before the altar.
Wolaitta Sentences: Yarshshiyoosaa Muusee tiyidi geeshshido gallassan, halaqati yarshshiyoosaa anjjissanau bantta imuwaa ekkidi, he yarshshuwaa saaxiniyaa sintti ehiidosona.

English Sentences: And the LORD said unto Moses, They shall offer their offering, each prince on his day, for the dedicating of the altar.
Wolaitta Sentences: GODAI Muusa kase, "Issi issi gallassi issi halaqai yarshshiyoosaa anjjanau ba imuwaa GODAAYYO immo" yaagi wottiis.

English Sentences: And he that offered his offering the first day was Nahshon the son of Amminadab, of the tribe of Judah:
Wolaitta Sentences: Koiro gallassi ba imuwaa ehiidaagee Yihudaa zariyaappe Aminadaaba na7aa Na7asoona.

English Sentences: And his offering was one silver charger, the weight thereof was an hundred and thirty shekels, one silver bowl of seventy shekels, after the shekel of the sanctuary; both of them were full of fine flour mingled with oil for a meat offering:
Wolaitta Sentences: Na7asooni ehiido imoi erettida meezaanan wottin, issi kilo giraamenne bagga deexxiya biraappe medhdhido issi keriyaanne hosppun xeetu giraame deexxiya biraappe medhdhido issi kuixaaruwaa, naa77aikka kattaa yarshshuwaa yarshshanau liiqo xiillee zaitiyan munaqqidoogee kumidoogeeta;

English Sentences: One spoon of ten shekels of gold, full of incense:
Wolaitta Sentences: qassi issi xeetanne tammu giraame deexxiya worqqaappe medhdhido, ixaanai kumido shaatiyaa;

English Sentences: One young bullock, one ram, one lamb of the first year, for a burnt offering:
Wolaitta Sentences: xuuggiyo yarshshuwaassi, issi mirgguwaa, issi dorssa orggiyaanne issi laitta kumido attuma dorssaa;

English Sentences: One kid of the goats for a sin offering:
Wolaitta Sentences: nagaraa yarshshuwaassi issi deeshsha orggiyaa;

English Sentences: And for a sacrifice of peace offerings, two oxen, five rams, five he goats, five lambs of the first year: this was the offering of Nahshon the son of Amminadab.
Wolaitta Sentences: issippetettaa yarshshuwaassi naa77u korimata, ichchashu dorssa orggeta, ichchashu gakkida deeshsha orggetanne issi laitta kumido ichchashu attuma dorssata. Aminadaaba na7ai Na7asooni ehiido imoi hagaa.

English Sentences: On the second day Nethaneel the son of Zuar, prince of Issachar, did offer:
Wolaitta Sentences: Naa77antta gallassi Yisaakoora zaretu halaqai, Xu7aara na7ai Nataani7eeli ba imuwaa ehiis.

English Sentences: He offered for his offering one silver charger, the weight whereof was an hundred and thirty shekels, one silver bowl of seventy shekels, after the shekel of the sanctuary; both of them full of fine flour mingled with oil for a meat offering:

English Sentences: On the eighth day offered Gamaliel the son of Pedahzur, prince of the children of Manasseh:
Wolaitta Sentences: Hosppuntta gallassi Minaase zaretu halaqai Padaaxuura na7ai Gamaali7eeli ba imuwaa ehiis.

English Sentences: His offering was one silver charger of the weight of an hundred and thirty shekels, one silver bowl of seventy shekels, after the shekel of the sanctuary; both of them full of fine flour mingled with oil for a meat offering:
Wolaitta Sentences: Gamaali7eeli ehiido imoi erettida meezaanan wottin, issi kilo giraamenne baggaa deexxiya biraappe medhdhido issi keriyaanne hosppun xeetu giraame deexxiya biraappe medhdhido issi kuixaaruwaa, naa77aikka kattaa yarshshuwaassi yarshshanau liiqo xiillee zaitiyaan munaqqidoogee kumidoogeeta

English Sentences: One golden spoon of ten shekels, full of incense:
Wolaitta Sentences: qassi issi xeetanne tammu giraame deexxiya worqqaappe medhdhido ixaanai kumido shaatiyaa;

English Sentences: One young bullock, one ram, one lamb of the first year, for a burnt offering:
Wolaitta Sentences: xuuggiyo yarshshuwaassi issi mirgguwaa, issi dorssa orggiyaanne, issi laitta kumido attuma dorssaa;

English Sentences: One kid of the goats for a sin offering:
Wolaitta Sentences: nagaraa yarshshuwaassi issi deeshsha orggiyaa,

English Sentences: And for a sacrifice of peace offerings, two oxen, five rams, five he goats, five lambs of the first year: this was the offering of Gamaliel the son of Pedahzur.
Wolaitta Sentences: issippetettaa yarshshuwaassi naa77u korimata, ichchashu dorssa orggeta, ichchashu gakkida deeshsha orggetanne issi laitta kumido ichchashu attuma dorssata. Padaaxuura na7ai Gamaali7eeli ehiido imoi hagaa.

Wolaitta Sentences: Uddufuntta gallassi Biniyaama zaretu halaqai Giidi7oona na7ai Abidaani ba imuwaa ehiis.

Wolaitta Sentences: Abidaani ehiido imoi erettida meezaanan wottin, issi kilo giraamenne baggaa deexxiya biraappe medhdhido issi keriyaanne hosppun xeetu giraame deexxiya biraappe medhdhido issi kuixaaruwaa, naa77aikka kattaa yarshshuwaassi yarshshanau liiqo xiillee, zaitiyan munaqqidoogee kumidoogeeta;

Wolaitta Sentences: qassi issi xeetanne tammu giraame deexxiya worqqaappe medhdhido, ixaanai kumido shaatiyaa;

Wolaitta Sentences: xuuggiyo yarshshuwaassi issi mirgguwaa issi dorssa orggiyaanne, issi laitta kumido attuma dorssaa;

English Sentences: On the tenth day Ahiezer the son of Ammishaddai, prince of the children of Dan, offered:
Wolaitta Sentences: Tammantta gallassi Daana zaretu halaqai Amishadaaya na7ai Ahi7eezeri ba imuwaa ehiis.

English Sentences: His offering was one silver charger, the weight whereof was an hundred and thirty shekels, one silver bowl of seventy shekels, after the shekel of the sanctuary; both of them full of fine flour mingled with oil for a meat offering:
Wolaitta Sentences: Ahi7eezeri ehiido imoi erettida meezaanan wottin, issi kilo giraamenne baggaa deexxiya biraappe medhdhido issi keriyaanne hosppun xeetu giraame deexxiya biraappe medhdhido issi kuixaaruwaa, naa77aikka kattaa yarshshuwaassi yarshshanau liiqo xiillee, zaitiyan munaqqidoogee kumidoogeeta;

Wolaitta Sentences: qassi issi xeetanne tammu giraame deexxiya worqqaappe medhdhido, ixaanai kumido shaatiyaa.

Wolaitta Sentences: Xuuggiyo yarshshuwaassi issi mirgguwaa, issi dorssa orggiyaanne, issi laitta kumido attuma dorssaa;

English Sentences: On the eleventh day Pagiel the son of Ocran, prince of the children of Asher, offered:
Wolaitta Sentences: Tammanne isiinintta gallassi Aseera zaretu halaqai Okiraana na7ai Paagi7eeli ba yarshshuwaa ehiis.

English Sentences: His offering was one silver charger, the weight whereof was an hundred and thirty shekels, one silver bowl of seventy shekels, after the shekel of the sanctuary; both of them full of fine flour mingled with oil for a meat offering:
Wolaitta Sentences: Paagi7eeli ehiido imoi erettida meezaanan wottin, issi kilo giraamenne baggaa deexxiya biraappe medhdhido issi keriyaanne hosppun xeetu giraame deexxiya biraappe medhdhido issi kuixaaruwaa, naa77aikka kattaa yarshshuwaassi yarshshanau liiqo xiillee, zaitiyan munaqqidoogee kumidoogeeta;

Wolaitta Sentences: qassi issi xeetanne tammu giraame deexxiya worqqaappe medhdhido shaatiyaa, ixaanai kumidoogaa;

Wolaitta Sentences: xuuggiyo yarshshuwaassi issi mirgguwaa, issi dorssa orggiyaanne issi laitta kumido attuma dorssaa;

Wolaitta Sentences: nagaraa yarshshuwaassi issi deeshsha orggiyaa;

English Sentences: On the twelfth day Ahira the son of Enan, prince of the children of Naphtali, offered:
Wolaitta Sentences: Tammanne naa77antta gallassi Nifttaaleema zaretu halaqai Enaana na7ai Ahiraa7i ba imuwaa ehiis.

English Sentences: His offering was one silver charger, the weight whereof was an hundred and thirty shekels, one silver bowl of seventy shekels, after the shekel of the sanctuary; both of them full of fine flour mingled with oil for a meat offering:
Wolaitta Sentences: Ahiraa7i ehiido imoi erettida meezaanan wottin, issi kilo giraamenne baggaa deexxiya biraappe medhdhido issi keriyaanne hosppun xeetu giraame deexxiya biraappe medhdhido issi kuixaaruwaa, naa77aikka kattaa yarshshuwaassi yarshshanau liiqo xiillee, zaitiyan munaqqidoogee kumidoogeeta,

English Sentences: One golden spoon of ten shekels, full of incense:
Wolaitta Sentences: qassi issi xeetanne tammu giraame deexxiya worqqaappe medhdhido issi shaatiyaa, ixaanai kumidoogaa;

Wolaitta Sentences: xuuggiyo yarshshuwaassi issi mirgguwaa, issi dorssa orggiyaanne issi laitta kumido attuma dorssaa;

English Sentences: This was the dedication of the altar, in the day when it was anointed, by the princes of Israel: twelve chargers of silver, twelve silver bowls, twelve spoons of gold:
Wolaitta Sentences: Yarshshiyoosai tiyettido wode, Israa7eelatu halaqati yarshshiyoosaa anjjanau ehiido imoti muleera hageeta: Biraappe medhdhido tammanne naa77u kereta, biraappe medhdhido tammanne naa77u kuixaarotanne worqqaappe medhdhido tammanne naa77u shaateta;

English Sentences: Each charger of silver weighing an hundred and thirty shekels, each bowl seventy: all the silver vessels weighed two thousand and four hundred shekels, after the shekel of the sanctuary:
Wolaitta Sentences: biraappe medhdhido issi issi keree issi kilo giraamenne baggaa deexxees; biraappe medhdhido issi issi kuixaaroi hosppun xeetu giraame deexxees; biraappe merettida kereenne kuixaaroi erettida meezaanan wottin, muleera laatamanne hosppun kilo giraame keenaa deexxoosona.

English Sentences: The golden spoons were twelve, full of incense, weighing ten shekels apiece, after the shekel of the sanctuary: all the gold of the spoons was an hundred and twenty shekels.
Wolaitta Sentences: Tammanne naa77u worqqa shaateti erettida meezaanan wottin issoi issoi issi xeetanne tammu giraame, muleera issi kilonne heezzu xeetu giraame deexxoosona. Etan ixaanai kumi uttiis.

English Sentences: All the oxen for the burnt offering were twelve bullocks, the rams twelve, the lambs of the first year twelve, with their meat offering: and the kids of the goats for sin offering twelve.
Wolaitta Sentences: Kattaa yarshshuwaara issippe xuuggiyo yarshshuwaassi ehiido mehee muleera tammanne naa77u mirggota, tammanne naa77u dorssa orggetanne issi laitta kumido tammanne naa77u attuma dorssata. Eti nagaraa yarshshuwaassi ehiido deeshsha orggeti muleera tammanne naa77a.

English Sentences: And all the oxen for the sacrifice of the peace offerings were twenty and four bullocks, the rams sixty, the he goats sixty, the lambs of the first year sixty. This was the dedication of the altar, after that it was anointed.
Wolaitta Sentences: Eti issippetettaa yarshshuwaassi ehiido mehee muleera laatamanne oiddu korimata, usuppun tammu dorssa orggeta, usuppun tammu gakkida deeshsha orggetanne issi laitta kumido usuppun tammu attuma dorssata. Yarshshiyoosai tiyettidoogaappe guyyiyan, anjjuwaassi ehiido imoti hageeta.

English Sentences: And when Moses was gone into the tabernacle of the congregation to speak with him, then he heard the voice of one speaking unto him from off the mercy seat that was upon the ark of testimony, from between the two cherubims: and he spake unto him.
Wolaitta Sentences: Muusee GODAARA haasayanau Xoossaa Dunkkaaniyaa geliyo wode, Maachchaa Taabootaa bollan de7iya atto giyo sohuwaa qum77uwaa bollan, naa77u kiruubetuppe gidduwaara GODAI haasayiyo cenggurssaa siyiis; siyidi ikka aara haasayiis.

English Sentences: And the LORD spake unto Moses, saying,
Wolaitta Sentences: GODAI Muusa,

English Sentences: Speak unto Aaron, and say unto him, When thou lightest the lamps, the seven lamps shall give light over against the candlestick.
Wolaitta Sentences: "Neeni Aaroonassi hagaadan yaagada oda; Neeni laappun xomppeta wottiyo wode xomppeti xomppiyaa wottiyo ballatuppe sintta baggaara de7iya heerata poo7issona yaaga" yaagiis.

English Sentences: And Aaron did so; he lighted the lamps thereof over against the candlestick, as the LORD commanded Moses.
Wolaitta Sentences: Yaagin i giidoogaadan Aarooni oottiis. GODAI Muusa azazidoogaadan, Aarooni xomppeta wottiyo ballatuppe sintta baggaara de7iya heerata poo7issanaadan oottidi, ballatun wottiis.

English Sentences: And this work of the candlestick was of beaten gold, unto the shaft thereof, unto the flowers thereof, was beaten work: according unto the pattern which the LORD had shewed Moses, so he made the candlestick.
Wolaitta Sentences: Xomppiyaa wottiyoogee garssa tohuwaappe bolla ciishshaara alleeqettida ballata xeeraa gakkanaassi qoxettida worqqaappe merettiis. Xomppiyaa wottiyo ballai GODAI Muusa bessido leemisuwaadan oosettiis.

English Sentences: And the LORD spake unto Moses, saying,
Wolaitta Sentences: Qassi GODAI Muusa,

English Sentences: Take the Levites from among the children of Israel, and cleanse them.
Wolaitta Sentences: "Hara Israa7eela asaa gidduwaappe Leewata ekkada, eta wogaadan geeshsha.

English Sentences: And thus shalt thou do unto them, to cleanse them: Sprinkle water of purifying upon them, and let them shave all their flesh, and let them wash their clothes, and so make themselves clean.
Wolaitta Sentences: Neeni eta geeshshanau hagaadan ootta: geeshshiya haattaa ekkada eta araca; aracin eti bantta bollaa ubbaa meedettona; bantta maayuwaakka meeccona; yaatidi eti wogaadan geeshsha gidana.

English Sentences: Then let them take a young bullock with his meat offering, even fine flour mingled with oil, and another young bullock shalt thou take for a sin offering.
Wolaitta Sentences: Hegaappe guyyiyan, eti mirgguwaa issuwaanne liiqo xiilliyaa zaitiyan munaqqidoogaa kattaa yarshshuwaassi ekkona; ekkin neeni qassi naa77antto mirgguwaa nagaraa yarshshuwaassi ekka.

English Sentences: And thou shalt bring the Levites before the tabernacle of the congregation: and thou shalt gather the whole assembly of the children of Israel together:
Wolaitta Sentences: Yaatada Leewata Xoossaa Dunkkaaniyaa sintti eha; ehaada Israa7eela asaa maabaraa ubbaa shiishsha.

English Sentences: And thou shalt bring the Levites before the LORD: and the children of Israel shall put their hands upon the Levites:
Wolaitta Sentences: Neeni Leewata GODAA sinttau ehin, Israa7eela asai eta bolli bantta kushiyaa wottona.

English Sentences: And Aaron shall offer the Levites before the LORD for an offering of the children of Israel, that they may execute the service of the LORD.
Wolaitta Sentences: Leewati GODAA oosuwaa oottanau giigana mala, Aarooni Israa7eela asaappe Leewata wuxaawuxiyo yarshsho oottidi, GODAA sintti shiishsho.

English Sentences: And the Levites shall lay their hands upon the heads of the bullocks: and thou shalt offer the one for a sin offering, and the other for a burnt offering, unto the LORD, to make an atonement for the Levites.
Wolaitta Sentences: "Leewati bantta kushiyaa mirggotu huuphiyan wottona; issuwaa nagaraa yarshsho oottada, issuwaa qassi Leewati atto geetettana mala, xuuggiyo yarshsho oottada GODAASSI yarshsha.

English Sentences: And thou shalt set the Levites before Aaron, and before his sons, and offer them for an offering unto the LORD.
Wolaitta Sentences: Leewata Aaroonanne a attuma naatu aawatettaa garssan wotta; yaatada eta wuxaawuxiyo yarshsho oottada, GODAA sintti shiishsha.

English Sentences: Thus shalt thou separate the Levites from among the children of Israel: and the Levites shall be mine.
Wolaitta Sentences: Hegaadan oottada Leewata hara Israa7eela asaappe dummaya; dummayobare Leewati tabaa gidana.

English Sentences: And after that shall the Levites go in to do the service of the tabernacle of the congregation: and thou shalt cleanse them, and offer them for an offering.
Wolaitta Sentences: "Neeni Leewata geeshshidoogaappenne wuxaawuxiyo yarshsho oottada shiishshidoogaappe guyyiyan, Xoossaa Dunkkaaniyan bantta oosuwaa oottanau yoona.

English Sentences: For they are wholly given unto me from among the children of Israel; instead of such as open every womb, even instead of the firstborn of all the children of Israel, have I taken them unto me.
Wolaitta Sentences: Israa7eela asaa gidduwaappe eti taayyo muleera imettidosona; Israa7eela maccaasaappe yelettida baira attumaageetu ubbaa gishshaa taani Leewata taayyo ekkaas.

English Sentences: For all the firstborn of the children of Israel are mine, both man and beast: on the day that I smote every firstborn in the land of Egypt I sanctified them for myself.
Wolaitta Sentences: Israa7eela asaa gidduwan baira yelettidabi asa gidin, mehe gidinkka ubbai tabaa. Taani Gibxxe biittan baira ubbaa worido gallassan, eta taayyo dummayaas.

English Sentences: And I have taken the Levites for all the firstborn of the children of Israel.
Wolaitta Sentences: Israa7eela baira attumaageetu ubbaa gishshaa taani Leewata ekkaas.

English Sentences: And I have given the Levites as a gift to Aaron and to his sons from among the children of Israel, to do the service of the children of Israel in the tabernacle of the congregation, and to make an atonement for the children of Israel: that there be no plague among the children of Israel, when the children of Israel come nigh unto the sanctuary.
Wolaitta Sentences: Israa7eela asaa ubbaa gidduwaappe taani Leewata Aaroonayyoonne Aaroona attuma naatuyyo imo oottada immaas. Israa7eela asai Xoossaa Dunkkaaniyaa shiiqiyo wode, boshai eta bochchenna mala, Leewati Israa7eela asaa gishsha Xoossaa Dunkkaaniyan bantta oosuwaa oottonanne eta gishshaa atto geetettona" yaagiis.

English Sentences: And Moses, and Aaron, and all the congregation of the children of Israel, did to the Levites according unto all that the LORD commanded Moses concerning the Levites, so did the children of Israel unto them.
Wolaitta Sentences: GODAI Muusa Leewata dummayanau azazidoogaadan Muusee, Aarooninne Israa7eela asaa maabarai ubbai oottidosona.

English Sentences: And the Levites were purified, and they washed their clothes; and Aaron offered them as an offering before the LORD; and Aaron made an atonement for them to cleanse them.
Wolaitta Sentences: Leewati nagaraappe banttana geeshshidosona; bantta maayuwaakka meeccidosona. Meeccin Aarooni eta wuxaawuxiyo yarshsho oottidi, GODAA sintti shiishshiis; eta geeshshanau eta nagaraa atto giissiis.
