English Sentences: And after that went the Levites in to do their service in the tabernacle of the congregation before Aaron, and before his sons: as the LORD had commanded Moses concerning the Levites, so did they unto them.
Wolaitta Sentences: Hegaappe guyyiyan, Leewati Aaroonanne Aaroona attuma naatu aawatettaa garssan, Xoossaa Dunkkaaniyaa giddon bantta oosuwaa oottanau yiidosona. GODAI Muusa Leewata dummayanau azazidoogaadan eti oottidosona.

English Sentences: And the LORD spake unto Moses, saying,
Wolaitta Sentences: Qassikka GODAI Muusa hagaadan yaagiis;

English Sentences: This is it that belongeth unto the Levites: from twenty and five years old and upward they shall go in to wait upon the service of the tabernacle of the congregation:
Wolaitta Sentences: "Hagee Leewata xeelliya wogaa: laittai laatamanne ichchashaanne hegaappe bollaara de7iya attumaageeti oosuwaa oottanau Xoossaa Dunkkaaniyaa yoona.

English Sentences: And from the age of fifty years they shall cease waiting upon the service thereof, and shall serve no more:
Wolaitta Sentences: SHin eta laittai ishatamaa gidiyo wode eti bantta oosuwaappe xurataa kiyona; kiyi simmidi naa77antto oottoppona.

English Sentences: But shall minister with their brethren in the tabernacle of the congregation, to keep the charge, and shall do no service. Thus shalt thou do unto the Levites touching their charge.
Wolaitta Sentences: Eti Xoossaa Dunkkaaniyan oottiya bantta ishantta ootti maaddana giikko maaddonappe attin, eti banttarkka ai oosonne oottoppona. Simmi neeni Leewata oosuwaa hagaadan ootissaasa" yaagiis.

English Sentences: And the LORD spake unto Moses in the wilderness of Sinai, in the first month of the second year after they were come out of the land of Egypt, saying,
Wolaitta Sentences: Israa7eela asai Gibxxeppe kiyido naa77antta laittan koiro aginan Siinaa Bazzuwan GODAI Muuseyyo hagaadan yaagidi haasayiis;

English Sentences: Let the children of Israel also keep the passover at his appointed season.
Wolaitta Sentences: "Israa7eela asai Paasikaa Baalaa keerido gallassan bonchcho.

English Sentences: In the fourteenth day of this month, at even, ye shall keep it in his appointed season: according to all the rites of it, and according to all the ceremonies thereof, shall ye keep it.
Wolaitta Sentences: Ha aginan tammanne oiddantta gallassan, a keerido wode, awai wullana haniyo wode, a wogaa ubbaadaaninne a azazo ubbaadan bonchcho" yaagiis.

English Sentences: And Moses spake unto the children of Israel, that they should keep the passover.
Wolaitta Sentences: Yaagin Muusee Israa7eela asai Paasikaa Baalaa bonchchana mala, etayyo yootiis.

English Sentences: And they kept the passover on the fourteenth day of the first month at even in the wilderness of Sinai: according to all that the LORD commanded Moses, so did the children of Israel.
Wolaitta Sentences: Koiro aginaayyo tammanne oiddantta gallassi, awai wullana haniyo wode Siinaa Bazzuwan eti Paasikaa Baalaa bonchchidosona. Israa7eela asai GODAI Muusa azazidoogaadan ubbabaa oottiis.

English Sentences: And there were certain men, who were defiled by the dead body of a man, that they could not keep the passover on that day: and they came before Moses and before Aaron on that day:
Wolaitta Sentences: SHin etappe amaridaageeti haiqqida asa ahaa bochchidi tunido gishshau, he gallassi Paasikaa Baalaa bonchchanau danddayibookkona. Hegaa gishshau, eti Muusekkonne Aaroonakko he gallassi yiidi,

English Sentences: And those men said unto him, We are defiled by the dead body of a man: wherefore are we kept back, that we may not offer an offering of the LORD in his appointed season among the children of Israel?
Wolaitta Sentences: Muusa, "Nuuni haiqqida asa ahaa bochchido gishshau tunida; shin keerido wodiyan hara Israa7eela asaara GODAAYYO yarshshuwaa shiishshiyoogaa nuuni aissi digettiyoonii?" yaagidosona.

English Sentences: And Moses said unto them, Stand still, and I will hear what the LORD will command concerning you.
Wolaitta Sentences: Yaagin Muusee eta, "GODAI inttebaa taassi azaziyoobaa taani siyana gakkanaassi intte takkishshite" yaagiis.

English Sentences: And the LORD spake unto Moses, saying,
Wolaitta Sentences: Hegaappe guyyiyan GODAI Muusa,

English Sentences: Speak unto the children of Israel, saying, If any man of you or of your posterity shall be unclean by reason of a dead body, or be in a journey afar off, yet he shall keep the passover unto the LORD.
Wolaitta Sentences: "Neeni Israa7eela asaa hagaadan yaaga; Intteppe woikko intte zaretuppe ooninne ahaa bochchidi tunikko, woikko manddaridaba gidikko, i GODAAYYO Paasikaa Baalaa bonchcho;

English Sentences: The fourteenth day of the second month at even they shall keep it, and eat it with unleavened bread and bitter herbs.
Wolaitta Sentences: naa77antto aginan tammanne oiddantta gallassi awai wullana haniyo wode Paasikaa Baalaa bonchcho. Bonchchiiddi Paasikaa dorssaa irshshoi gelibeenna oittaaranne camo bonccuwaara mo.

English Sentences: They shall leave none of it unto the morning, nor break any bone of it: according to all the ordinances of the passover they shall keep it.
Wolaitta Sentences: Sa7ai wonttanaashin he dorssaappe aibanne ashshoppo; qassi a meqettaappekka issuwaanne menttoppo. Paasikaa Baalau a woga ubbaa ootto.

English Sentences: But the man that is clean, and is not in a journey, and forbeareth to keep the passover, even the same soul shall be cut off from among his people: because he brought not the offering of the LORD in his appointed season, that man shall bear his sin.
Wolaitta Sentences: SHin manddaribeenna geeshsha asi Paasikaa bonchchennan ixxikko, hegaappe sinttau i ta asaa giddoppe bohetto. Aissi giikko, GODAA yarshshuwaa keerido wodiyan i shiishshibeenna. He asi ba nagarai ehiido metuwaa ekkanau bessees.

English Sentences: And if a stranger shall sojourn among you, and will keep the passover unto the LORD; according to the ordinance of the passover, and according to the manner thereof, so shall he do: ye shall have one ordinance, both for the stranger, and for him that was born in the land.
Wolaitta Sentences: "Intte gidduwan de7iya bete asi Paasikaa Baalaa GODAAYYO bonchchana koyikko, Paasikaa wogaadan bonchcho. Betiyaukka dere asaukka issi mala wogai de7o yaaga" yaagiis.

English Sentences: And on the day that the tabernacle was reared up the cloud covered the tabernacle, namely, the tent of the testimony: and at even there was upon the tabernacle as it were the appearance of fire, until the morning.
Wolaitta Sentences: Xoossaa Dunkkaanee tolettido gallassi shaarai Xoossaa Dunkkaaniyaa maayiis; omarssaappe doommidi, wonttana gakkanaassi Xoossaa Dunkkaaniyaappe bollaara de7iya shaarai tama milatees.

English Sentences: So it was alway: the cloud covered it by day, and the appearance of fire by night.
Wolaitta Sentences: Hegaadan ubba wode gallassi gallassi shaarai maayees; qammi qammi he shaarai tamadan poo7ees.

English Sentences: And when the cloud was taken up from the tabernacle, then after that the children of Israel journeyed: and in the place where the cloud abode, there the children of Israel pitched their tents.
Wolaitta Sentences: He shaarai Xoossaa Dunkkaaniyaa bollaappe denddiyo wode audenne Israa7eelati bantta dunkkaanidosaappe denddoosona; qassi he shaarai wodhdhiyo ai sohuwaaninne Israa7eelati dunkkaanoosona.

English Sentences: At the commandment of the LORD the children of Israel journeyed, and at the commandment of the LORD they pitched: as long as the cloud abode upon the tabernacle they rested in their tents.
Wolaitta Sentences: Israa7eelati GODAA azazuwan denddoosona; hegaadankka, GODAA azazuwan dunkkaanoosona. SHaarai Xoossaa Dunkkaaniyaa bollan gam77iyo wode ubban bantta dunkkaanidosan gam77oosona.

English Sentences: And when the cloud tarried long upon the tabernacle many days, then the children of Israel kept the charge of the LORD, and journeyed not.
Wolaitta Sentences: SHaarai Xoossaa Dunkkaaniyaa bollan daro gallassaa gam77ikko, Israa7eelati GODAA azazuwaa naagoosonappe attin, awanne bookkona.

English Sentences: And so it was, when the cloud was a few days upon the tabernacle; according to the commandment of the LORD they abode in their tents, and according to the commandment of the LORD they journeyed.
Wolaitta Sentences: Issitoo issitoo shaarai Xoossaa Dunkkaaniyaa bollan amarida gallassaa gam77ees. GODAA azazuwan eti dunkkaanoosona; qassi hegaadankka, GODAA azazuwan eti denddoosona.

English Sentences: And so it was, when the cloud abode from even unto the morning, and that the cloud was taken up in the morning, then they journeyed: whether it was by day or by night that the cloud was taken up, they journeyed.
Wolaitta Sentences: Issitoo issitoo shaarai omarssappe wonttana gakkanaashin xalaalaa gam77ees; wonttin shaarai denddiyo wode etikka denddoosona. Gallassa gidin, qamma gidin, shaarai denddiyo wode etikka denddoosona.

English Sentences: Or whether it were two days, or a month, or a year, that the cloud tarried upon the tabernacle, remaining thereon, the children of Israel abode in their tents, and journeyed not: but when it was taken up, they journeyed.
Wolaitta Sentences: SHaarai Xoossaa Dunkkaaniyaa bollan naa77u gallassaa gam77in, woikko issi aginaa, woikko issi laittaa gam77in, Israa7eelati bantta dunkkaanidosan gam77oosonappe attin bookkona. SHin shaarai denddiyo wode etikka denddoosona.

English Sentences: At the commandment of the LORD they rested in the tents, and at the commandment of the LORD they journeyed: they kept the charge of the LORD, at the commandment of the LORD by the hand of Moses.
Wolaitta Sentences: Eti GODAA azazuwan dunkkaanoosonanne qassi GODAA azazuwan denddoosona; GODAI Muuse baggaara azazidoogaadan, eti GODAA azazuwaa naagidosona.

English Sentences: And the LORD spake unto Moses, saying,
Wolaitta Sentences: GODAI Muusa hagaadan yaagiis;

English Sentences: Make thee two trumpets of silver; of a whole piece shalt thou make them: that thou mayest use them for the calling of the assembly, and for the journeying of the camps.
Wolaitta Sentences: "Naa77u xurumbbata biraappe qoxxada ootta; yaatada asaa shiiquwau xeeganaunne qassi dunkkaanidosaappe denddanau denttettanaadan punna.

English Sentences: And when they shall blow with them, all the assembly shall assemble themselves to thee at the door of the tabernacle of the congregation.
Wolaitta Sentences: Ha naa77u xurumbbati punettiyo wode, asai ubbai Xoossaa Dunkkaaniyaa penggee neekko shiiqo.

English Sentences: And if they blow but with one trumpet, then the princes, which are heads of the thousands of Israel, shall gather themselves unto thee.
Wolaitta Sentences: SHin issi xurumbba xalaalai punettikko, Israa7eela zareta halaqati ne sintti shiiqona.

English Sentences: When ye blow an alarm, then the camps that lie on the east parts shall go forward.
Wolaitta Sentences: Neeni xurumbbaa xoqqu oottada punniyo wode Xoossaa Dunkkaaniyaappe arshsho baggaara dunkkaanida zareti denddona.

English Sentences: When ye blow an alarm the second time, then the camps that lie on the south side shall take their journey: they shall blow an alarm for their journeys.
Wolaitta Sentences: Xurumbbaa naa77antto xoqqu oottada punniyo wode, tohossa baggaara dunkkaanida zareti denddona. Xurumbbai xoqqu gi punettiyoogee denddanau malaata gido.

English Sentences: But when the congregation is to be gathered together, ye shall blow, but ye shall not sound an alarm.
Wolaitta Sentences: Yaa7au asaa shiishshanau xurumbbaa punna; shin cenggurssaa xoqqu oottada punnoppa.

English Sentences: And the sons of Aaron, the priests, shall blow with the trumpets; and they shall be to you for an ordinance for ever throughout your generations.
Wolaitta Sentences: Aaroona naati qeeseti xurumbba punnona. Hagee neeyyoonne yiya yeleta ubbau merina woga gido.

English Sentences: And if ye go to war in your land against the enemy that oppresseth you, then ye shall blow an alarm with the trumpets; and ye shall be remembered before the LORD your God, and ye shall be saved from your enemies.
Wolaitta Sentences: "Intte biittan woraajjiya intte morkkiyaara intte olettanau kiyiyo wode, he xurumbbata xoqqu oottidi punnite. Hegan GODAI intte Xoossai inttena he wode hassayidi, intte morkkiyaappe inttena ashshana.

English Sentences: Also in the day of your gladness, and in your solemn days, and in the beginnings of your months, ye shall blow with the trumpets over your burnt offerings, and over the sacrifices of your peace offerings; that they may be to you for a memorial before your God: I am the LORD your God.
Wolaitta Sentences: Hegaadankka, qassi intte ufaittiyo gallassi, baalaa bonchchanau intte keerido gallassinne aginai xeeriyo baalan, intte xuuggiyo yarshshiyo wodenne intte issippetettaa yarshshuwaa yarshshiyo wode he xurumbbata punnite; hegee Xoossaa sinttan inttena hassayissiyaagaa gidana. Taani GODAA, intte Xoossaa" yaagiis.

English Sentences: And it came to pass on the twentieth day of the second month, in the second year, that the cloud was taken up from off the tabernacle of the testimony.
Wolaitta Sentences: Naa77antta laittan naa77antta aginan laatamantta gallassi, shaarai Xoossaa Dunkkaaniyaa bollappe denddiis.

English Sentences: And the children of Israel took their journeys out of the wilderness of Sinai; and the cloud rested in the wilderness of Paran.
Wolaitta Sentences: Hegaappe guyyiyan, Israa7eela asai Siinaa Bazzuwaappe denddiis; shaarai Paaraana giyo bazzuwaa gakkidi wodhdhiis.

English Sentences: And they first took their journey according to the commandment of the LORD by the hand of Moses.
Wolaitta Sentences: Eti ha koiro buussau GODAI Muuse baggaara azazidoogaadan denddidosona.

English Sentences: In the first place went the standard of the camp of the children of Judah according to their armies: and over his host was Nahshon the son of Amminadab.
Wolaitta Sentences: Yihudaa zaretuura dunkkaanida baggai bantta armmaa oiqqidi denddiis. Yihudaa zaretu halaqai Aminadaaba na7aa Na7asoona;

English Sentences: And over the host of the tribe of the children of Issachar was Nethaneel the son of Zuar.
Wolaitta Sentences: Yisaakoora zaretu halaqai Xu7aara na7aa Nataani7eela;

English Sentences: And over the host of the tribe of the children of Zebulun was Eliab the son of Helon.
Wolaitta Sentences: Zaabiloona zaretu halaqai Heloona na7aa Eli7aaba.

English Sentences: And the tabernacle was taken down; and the sons of Gershon and the sons of Merari set forward, bearing the tabernacle.
Wolaitta Sentences: Hegaappe guyyiyan, Xoossaa Dunkkaaniyaa shoddin, Gershshoona yaratinne Maraara yarati tookkidi denddidosona.

English Sentences: And the standard of the camp of Reuben set forward according to their armies: and over his host was Elizur the son of Shedeur.
Wolaitta Sentences: Kaallidi Roobeela zaretuura dunkkaanida baggai bantta armmaa oiqqidi denddiis. Roobeela zaretu halaqai SHade7uura na7aa Eliixuura;

English Sentences: And over the host of the tribe of the children of Simeon was Shelumiel the son of Zurishaddai.
Wolaitta Sentences: Simoona zaretu halaqai Xuriishadaaya na7aa SHalumi7eela;

English Sentences: And over the host of the tribe of the children of Gad was Eliasaph the son of Deuel.
Wolaitta Sentences: Gaada zaretu halaqai Da7u7eela na7aa Eliyasaafa.

English Sentences: And the Kohathites set forward, bearing the sanctuary: and the other did set up the tabernacle against they came.
Wolaitta Sentences: Hegaappe guyyiyan, Qahaata yarati geeshsha miishshata tookkidi denddidosona. Eti gakkanaappe kasetidi, Xoossaa Dunkkaanee toletti uttiis.

English Sentences: And the standard of the camp of the children of Ephraim set forward according to their armies: and over his host was Elishama the son of Ammihud.
Wolaitta Sentences: Kaallidi Efireema zaretuura dunkkaanida baggai ba armmaa oiqqidi denddiis. Efireema zaretu halaqai Amihuuda na7aa Elishamaa7a;

English Sentences: And over the host of the tribe of the children of Manasseh was Gamaliel the son of Pedahzur.
Wolaitta Sentences: Minaase zaretu halaqai Padaaxuura na7aa Gamaali7eela;

English Sentences: And over the host of the tribe of the children of Benjamin was Abidan the son of Gideoni.
Wolaitta Sentences: Biniyaama zaretu halaqai Giidi7oona na7aa Abidaana.

English Sentences: And the standard of the camp of the children of Dan set forward, which was the rereward of all the camps throughout their hosts: and over his host was Ahiezer the son of Ammishaddai.
Wolaitta Sentences: Wurssettan, ha cita ubbaayyo guyye baggan naagiya Daana zaretuura dunkkaanida baggai ba armmaa oiqqidi denddiis. Daana zaretu halaqai Amishadaaya na7aa Ahi7eezera;

English Sentences: And over the host of the tribe of the children of Asher was Pagiel the son of Ocran.
Wolaitta Sentences: Aseera zaretu halaqai Okiraana na7aa Paagi7eela;

English Sentences: And over the host of the tribe of the children of Naphtali was Ahira the son of Enan.
Wolaitta Sentences: Nifttaaleema zaretu halaqai Enaana na7aa Ahiraa7a.

English Sentences: Thus were the journeyings of the children of Israel according to their armies, when they set forward.
Wolaitta Sentences: Israa7eela asai ba baggan baggan denddidi biyo maarai hagaadaana.

English Sentences: And Moses said unto Hobab, the son of Raguel the Midianite, Moses' father in law, We are journeying unto the place of which the LORD said, I will give it you: come thou with us, and we will do thee good: for the LORD hath spoken good concerning Israel.
Wolaitta Sentences: Muusee Midiyaama asa gidiya ba bolluwaa Yatiro na7aa Hobaaba, "Nuuni GODAI, Taani intteyyo immana giido sohuwaa boos; GODAI Israa7eelayyo lo77obaa oottana giido gishshau, neeni nunaara hindda. Nuuni neeyyo lo77obaa oottana" yaagiis.

English Sentences: And he said unto him, I will not go; but I will depart to mine own land, and to my kindred.
Wolaitta Sentences: Yaagin Hobaabi, "CHii, taani biikke; taani ta biitti ta asaakko baana" yaagiis.

English Sentences: And he said, Leave us not, I pray thee; forasmuch as thou knowest how we are to encamp in the wilderness, and thou mayest be to us instead of eyes.
Wolaitta Sentences: Yaagin Muusee a, "Hayyanaa, nuna yeggada boopparkkii! Bazzuwan nuuni dunkkaananau bessiyaasa neeni eraasa; neeni nu biyo ogiyaa nuna kaalettanaukka danddayaasa.

English Sentences: And it shall be, if thou go with us, yea, it shall be, that what goodness the LORD shall do unto us, the same will we do unto thee.
Wolaitta Sentences: Neeni nunaara biikko, GODAI nuuyyo immiyo anjjuwaa ubbaa nuuni nenaara shaakkana" yaagiis.

English Sentences: And they departed from the mount of the LORD three days' journey: and the ark of the covenant of the LORD went before them in the three days' journey, to search out a resting place for them.
Wolaitta Sentences: Yaatin eti GODAA deriyaappe denddidi, heezzu gallassa keena ogiyaa biidosona. GODAA Maachchaa Taabootai eti shemppiyo sohuwaa demmanau he heezzu gallassan etappe sinttau biis.

English Sentences: And the cloud of the LORD was upon them by day, when they went out of the camp.
Wolaitta Sentences: Eti dunkkaanidosaappe denddiyo wode ubban, GODAA shaarai gallassi gallassi etappe bollaara de7ees.

English Sentences: And it came to pass, when the ark set forward, that Moses said, Rise up, LORD, and let thine enemies be scattered; and let them that hate thee flee before thee.
Wolaitta Sentences: Taabootai denddiyo wode ubban Muusee, "Abeet GODAU, dendda! Ne morkketi laalettona; Nena ixxiyaageetakka ne sinttappe baqatona" yaagees.

English Sentences: And when it rested, he said, Return, O LORD, unto the many thousands of Israel.
Wolaitta Sentences: Taabootai shemppiyo wode ubban Muusee, "Abeet GODAU, ha daro sha7an qoodettiya Israa7eela asaakko neeni simma" yaagees.

English Sentences: And when the people complained, it displeased the LORD: and the LORD heard it; and his anger was kindled; and the fire of the LORD burnt among them, and consumed them that were in the uttermost parts of the camp.
Wolaitta Sentences: Asai ba metuwaayyo GODAA bolli zuuzummiis; eti zuuzummishin GODAI siyidi, hanqquwaa eexxi kiyiis. Yaatin GODAA tamai eta gidduwan eexxidi, eti dunkkaanidosaayyo issi issi gaxaa baggaa miis.

English Sentences: And the people cried unto Moses; and when Moses prayed unto the LORD, the fire was quenched.
Wolaitta Sentences: Yaatin asai Muuseyyo waassin, Muusee GODAA woossiis. Woossin tamai to7iis.

English Sentences: And he called the name of the place Taberah: because the fire of the LORD burnt among them.
Wolaitta Sentences: GODAA tamai eta gidduwan eexxido gishshau, he sohoi Tabi7eera geetetti xeesettiis.

English Sentences: And the mixt multitude that was among them fell a lusting: and the children of Israel also wept again, and said, Who shall give us flesh to eat?
Wolaitta Sentences: Israa7eelatuura de7iya dumma dumma dere asai hara qumaa keehi amottiis. Israa7eela asaikka qassi hagaadan yaagidi yeehuwaa doommiis; "Laa nuuni asho auppe demmanee?

English Sentences: We remember the fish, which we did eat in Egypt freely; the cucumbers, and the melons, and the leeks, and the onions, and the garlick:
Wolaitta Sentences: Nuuni Gibxxe biittan miishsha qanxxennan coo miyo moliyaa hassayeettees; qassi qayye miyo paranjja leehiyaa, zolddo leehe milatiya mal77iya haattai kumido meelooniyaa, adussa paranjja sunkkuruutuwaanne tuummuwaa hassayeettees.

English Sentences: But now our soul is dried away: there is nothing at all, beside this manna, before our eyes.
Wolaitta Sentences: SHin ha77i nu qooree gorddettiis; nu aifeekka ha mannaappe attin, harabaa ainne be7enna" yaagidosona.

English Sentences: And the manna was as coriander seed, and the colour thereof as the colour of bdellium.
Wolaitta Sentences: Mannai deebbuwaa aifiyaa milatees; a merai booxxiya adil77e ciishshaa milatees.

English Sentences: And the people went about, and gathered it, and ground it in mills, or beat it in a mortar, and baked it in pans, and made cakes of it: and the taste of it was as the taste of fresh oil.
Wolaitta Sentences: Asai yuuyi yuuyi a qorees; qoridi woxan gaaccees, woikko udulan caddees; eti a otuwan penttissidi, bashiyan komppoosona. I zaitiyan munaqqidi uukkido oittaadan mal77ees.

English Sentences: And when the dew fell upon the camp in the night, the manna fell upon it.
Wolaitta Sentences: Qammi dunkkaanidosan xaazai wodhdhiyo wode, mannai aara wodhdhees.

English Sentences: Then Moses heard the people weep throughout their families, every man in the door of his tent: and the anger of the LORD was kindled greatly; Moses also was displeased.
Wolaitta Sentences: Asai ba dunkkaaniyaa penggen penggen yeekkishin, Muusee siyiis. GODAA hanqqoi eexxi kiyido gishshau, Muusee un77ettiis.

English Sentences: And Moses said unto the LORD, Wherefore hast thou afflicted thy servant? and wherefore have I not found favour in thy sight, that thou layest the burden of all this people upon me?
Wolaitta Sentences: Hegaa gishshau, Muusee GODAA hagaadan yaagidi oichchiis; "Neeni ta bolli ne ashkkaraa bolli aissi ha metuwaa ehaadii? Neeni tanan aissi ufaittabeikkii? Neeni ha asaa ubbaa toohuwaa ta bolli aissi wottadii?

English Sentences: Have I conceived all this people? have I begotten them, that thou shouldest say unto me, Carry them in thy bosom, as a nursing father beareth the sucking child, unto the land which thou swarest unto their fathers?
Wolaitta Sentences: Ha asaa ubbaa taani shahaaridanaayye? Woikko eta taani yelidanaa? Neeni eta maizza aawatuyyo, "Taani intteyyo immana" gaada caaqqido biittaa gattanaassi, naata dichchiyaara xanttiyo na7aa ba qesiyan idimmiyoogaadan, neeni eta ne qesiyan idimma yaagada taayyo aissi yootai?

English Sentences: Whence should I have flesh to give unto all this people? for they weep unto me, saying, Give us flesh, that we may eat.
Wolaitta Sentences: Ha asau ubbau taani asho auppe demmanee? Eti tana, Miyo asho nuuyyo imma yaagidi yeekkoosona.

English Sentences: I am not able to bear all this people alone, because it is too heavy for me.
Wolaitta Sentences: Taani ha asaa ubbaa tarkka tookkana danddayikke; toohoi tau keehi deexxees.

English Sentences: And if thou deal thus with me, kill me, I pray thee, out of hand, if I have found favour in thy sight; and let me not see my wretchedness.
Wolaitta Sentences: Simmi neeni tana hagaadan metootanaadan oottanaagaappe taayyo qarettada tana ha77i wora baya; yaatikko, taani metuwaappe shemppana" yaagiis.

English Sentences: And the LORD said unto Moses, Gather unto me seventy men of the elders of Israel, whom thou knowest to be the elders of the people, and officers over them; and bring them unto the tabernacle of the congregation, that they may stand there with thee.
Wolaitta Sentences: GODAI Muusa, "Israa7eela cimatuppe kaalettiyaageetanne halaqata gidiya, neeni eriyo laappun tammu cimata taayyo shiishsha; eti nenaara yan eqqana mala, Xoossaa Dunkkaaniyaakko, eta neeni eha.

English Sentences: And I will come down and talk with thee there: and I will take of the spirit which is upon thee, and will put it upon them; and they shall bear the burden of the people with thee, that thou bear it not thyself alone.
Wolaitta Sentences: Taani duge wodhdhada nenaara yan haasayana; taani nenan de7iya Ayyaanaappe ekkada, he Ayyaanaa eta bolli wottana. Neeni nerkka tookkenna mala, eti asaa toohuwaa tookkidi, nena maaddana.

English Sentences: And say thou unto the people, Sanctify yourselves against to morrow, and ye shall eat flesh: for ye have wept in the ears of the LORD, saying, Who shall give us flesh to eat? for it was well with us in Egypt: therefore the LORD will give you flesh, and ye shall eat.
Wolaitta Sentences: "Neeni asaassi hagaadan gaada yoota, Wonttoyyo inttena geeshshite; yaatidi intte ashuwaa maana. Intte, "Laa nuuni asho auppe demmanee? Nuuyyo Gibxxe biittan sa7ai lo77o shin!" yaagidi yeekkidoogaa GODAI siyiis. GODAI ashuwaa ha77i intteyyo immana; immin intte maana.

English Sentences: Ye shall not eat one day, nor two days, nor five days, neither ten days, nor twenty days;
Wolaitta Sentences: Intte gidduwan de7iya GODAA intte karido gishshaunne intte, "Nuuni Gibxxe biittaappe aissi kiyidonii?" yaagidi a sinttan yeekkido gishshau,

English Sentences: But even a whole month, until it come out at your nostrils, and it be loathsome unto you: because that ye have despised the LORD which is among you, and have wept before him, saying, Why came we forth out of Egypt?
Wolaitta Sentences: intte issi gallassa, woikko naa77u gallassa, woikko ichchashu gallassa, woikko tammu gallassa, woikko laatamu gallassa xalaalaa asho meekketa; shin intteyyo siiriyaara kiyana gakkanaassi, inttena salettana gakkanaassi, issi agina kumettaa intte asho maana yaaga" yaagiis.

English Sentences: And Moses said, The people, among whom I am, are six hundred thousand footmen; and thou hast said, I will give them flesh, that they may eat a whole month.
Wolaitta Sentences: SHin Muusee GODAA, "Be7a, taani usuppun xeetu sha7u tohuwaasaa gidduwan de7ais; neeni, Issi agina kumettaa eti maanau etayyo taani asho immana gaasa.

English Sentences: Shall the flocks and the herds be slain for them, to suffice them? or shall all the fish of the sea be gathered together for them, to suffice them?
Wolaitta Sentences: Miizzaa wudiyaanne dorssaa wudiyaa etau shukkin kalissanee? Abban de7iya mole ubbaa shiishshiyaaba gidiyaakko, etayyo gidanee?" yaagiis.

English Sentences: And the LORD said unto Moses, Is the LORD's hand waxed short? thou shalt see now whether my word shall come to pass unto thee or not.
Wolaitta Sentences: Yaagin GODAI Muusa, "GODAA kushee qantteeyye? Taani neeyyo giyoobai tumakkonne worddokko neeni ha77i be7ana" yaagiis.

English Sentences: And Moses went out, and told the people the words of the LORD, and gathered the seventy men of the elders of the people, and set them round about the tabernacle.
Wolaitta Sentences: Yaagin Muusee kare kiyidi, GODAI giidobaa asaayyo yootiis. I Israa7eela cimatuppe laappun tammu asaa shiishshidi, Xoossaa Dunkkaaniyaa yuushuwan essiis.

English Sentences: And the LORD came down in a cloud, and spake unto him, and took of the spirit that was upon him, and gave it unto the seventy elders: and it came to pass, that, when the spirit rested upon them, they prophesied, and did not cease.
Wolaitta Sentences: Essin GODAI shaaran duge wodhdhidi, aara haasayiis; yaatidi a bollan de7iya Ayyaanaappe ekkidi, he laappun tammu cimatu bolli wottiis. Ayyaanai eta bollan shemppido wode, eti hananabaa yootidosona. SHin hegaappe guyyiyan, zaarettidi hananabaa yootibookkona.

English Sentences: But there remained two of the men in the camp, the name of the one was Eldad, and the name of the other Medad: and the spirit rested upon them; and they were of them that were written, but went not out unto the tabernacle: and they prophesied in the camp.
Wolaitta Sentences: He laappun tammu cimatuura mazggafan xaafettida asati Elddaadanne Medaada giyo naa77ati dunkkaanidosan attidosona; attidi Xoossaa Dunkkaaniyaakko yibookkona; shin eta bollikka Ayyaanai wodhdhin, dunkkaanidosan hananabaa yootidosona.

English Sentences: And there ran a young man, and told Moses, and said, Eldad and Medad do prophesy in the camp.
Wolaitta Sentences: Issi wodallai woxxi yiidi, Muusa, "Elddaadinne Medaadi dunkkaanidosan hananabaa yootoosona" yaagidi yootiis.

English Sentences: And Joshua the son of Nun, the servant of Moses, one of his young men, answered and said, My lord Moses, forbid them.
Wolaitta Sentences: Yootin ba yelagatettaappe doommidi, Muusa maaddiya Nawe na7ai Yaasu Muusa, "Ta godau Muusee, neeni eta teqqa" yaagiis.

English Sentences: And Moses said unto him, Enviest thou for my sake? would God that all the LORD's people were prophets, and that the LORD would put his spirit upon them!
Wolaitta Sentences: SHin Muusee a, "Ta gishshataa ne mishettai? GODAA asai ubbai hananabaa yootiyaabaanne GODAI ba Ayyaanaa eta bolli wottiyaaba gideerenneeshsha!" yaagiis.

English Sentences: And Moses gat him into the camp, he and the elders of Israel.
Wolaitta Sentences: Hegaappe guyyiyan, Muuseenne Israa7eela cimati dunkkaanidosaa simmidosona.

English Sentences: And there went forth a wind from the LORD, and brought quails from the sea, and let them fall by the camp, as it were a day's journey on this side, and as it were a day's journey on the other side, round about the camp, and as it were two cubits high upon the face of the earth.
Wolaitta Sentences: Hegaappe guyyiyan, GODAI carkkuwaa denttin, abbaa baggappe kuraachchuwaa asai dunkkaanidosaa ubbaa yuushuwaakko carkkoi ehiis; ehin he kafoti sa7aa doonaara biittaappe pude naa77u wara keenan paallidosona. Paalli yiidi eti dunkkaanidosaa ubbaappe gaxaara, issi gallassa oge keenaa sa7an uttidosona.

English Sentences: And the people stood up all that day, and all that night, and all the next day, and they gathered the quails: he that gathered least gathered ten homers: and they spread them all abroad for themselves round about the camp.
Wolaitta Sentences: He gallassa ubban, he qamma ubbaaninne wonttetta gallassa ubban asai kare kiyidi, ha kuraachchota oiqqidi shiishshiis; etappe ooninne issi sha7u kilo giraameppe guuttaa shiishshibeenna. Eti hegaappe guyyiyan, dunkkaanidosaa yuusho ubban melissanau miccidosona.

English Sentences: And while the flesh was yet between their teeth, ere it was chewed, the wrath of the LORD was kindled against the people, and the LORD smote the people with a very great plague.
Wolaitta Sentences: SHin ashoi biron eta achchan de7ishin, eti coommidi mittennan de7ishin, GODAA hanqqoi asaa bolli eexxi kiyiis; yaatin GODAI asaa wolqqaama boshan shociis.

English Sentences: And he called the name of that place Kibrothhattaavah: because there they buried the people that lusted.
Wolaitta Sentences: Yaatin he sohoi Amuwaa Duufuwaa geetetti sunttettiis; aissi giikko, ashuwaa amottida asaa eti he sohuwan moogidosona.

English Sentences: And the people journeyed from Kibrothhattaavah unto Hazeroth; and abode at Hazeroth.
Wolaitta Sentences: Asai hegaappe denddidi Haxeroota giyoosaa biidi, yan dunkkaaniis.

English Sentences: And Miriam and Aaron spake against Moses because of the Ethiopian woman whom he had married: for he had married an Ethiopian woman.
Wolaitta Sentences: Muusee Toophphiyaa biittaa maccaasiyo ekkiis. I ekkido Toophphiyaa maccaasee gishshau, Miiriyaamanne Aarooni Muusa boridosona.

English Sentences: And they said, Hath the LORD indeed spoken only by Moses? hath he not spoken also by us? And the LORD heard it.
Wolaitta Sentences: Eti, "GODAI Muuse bagga xalaalaara haasayideeyye? Qassi i nu baggaara haasayibeenneeyye?" yaagidosona. Yaagin GODAI hegaa siyiis.

English Sentences: (Now the man Moses was very meek, above all the men which were upon the face of the earth.)
Wolaitta Sentences: Muusee biittan sa7an ubban de7iya asaa ubbaappe aadhdhiya ashkke asa.

English Sentences: And the LORD spake suddenly unto Moses, and unto Aaron, and unto Miriam, Come out ye three unto the tabernacle of the congregation. And they three came out.
Wolaitta Sentences: GODAI sohuwaara Muusessi, Aaroonassinne Miiriyaamissi, "Intte heezzaikka Xoossaa Dunkkaaniyaakko kiyite" yaagiis; yaagin eti heezzaikka kiyidosona.

English Sentences: And the LORD came down in the pillar of the cloud, and stood in the door of the tabernacle, and called Aaron and Miriam: and they both came forth.
Wolaitta Sentences: Kiyin GODAI shaaraa tuussan duge wodhdhiis; wodhdhidi Xoossaa Dunkkaaniyaa penggen eqqidi, Aaroonanne Miiriyaamo xeesiis. Eti naa77aikka a sintti shiiqin,

English Sentences: And he said, Hear now my words: If there be a prophet among you, I the LORD will make myself known unto him in a vision, and will speak unto him in a dream.
Wolaitta Sentences: i eta, "Ta yootiyoogaa siyite: Intte gidduwan hananabaa yootiyaagee de7ikko, taani GODAI tana ayyo ajjuutan qonccissais; taani ayyo aimuwan yootais.

English Sentences: My servant Moses is not so, who is faithful in all mine house.
Wolaitta Sentences: SHin ta ashkkaraa Muuseera hegaadan gidenna; i ta keetta ubban ammanettidaagaa.

English Sentences: With him will I speak mouth to mouth, even apparently, and not in dark speeches; and the similitude of the LORD shall he behold: wherefore then were ye not afraid to speak against my servant Moses?
Wolaitta Sentences: Taani Muuseera sintta baazzan haasayaisippe attin, leemisuwan haasayikke. I ta meraa be7ees. Yaatin ta ashkkaraa Muusa boranau intte aissi yayyibeekketii?" yaagiis.

English Sentences: And the anger of the LORD was kindled against them; and he departed.
Wolaitta Sentences: GODAA hanqqoi eta bolli eexxi kiyiis; kiyin GODAI biis.

English Sentences: And the cloud departed from off the tabernacle; and, behold, Miriam became leprous, white as snow: and Aaron looked upon Miriam, and, behold, she was leprous.
Wolaitta Sentences: SHaarai Xoossaa Dunkkaaniyaa bollaappe denddido wode, Miiriyaama hanttaara gogaa harggiyan mulxxi gaada booxxaasu. Aarooni ikko simmidi xeelliyo wode, hanttaara gogaa harggiyan ohettidaaro be7iis.

English Sentences: And Aaron said unto Moses, Alas, my lord, I beseech thee, lay not the sin upon us, wherein we have done foolishly, and wherein we have sinned.
Wolaitta Sentences: Yaatin i Muusa, "Hai ta godau, nuuni eeyyatettan oottido nagaraayyo nuna qaxxayoppa.

English Sentences: Let her not be as one dead, of whom the flesh is half consumed when he cometh out of his mother's womb.
Wolaitta Sentences: Ba aayee uluwaappe kiyiyo wode, a ashuwaappe baggai meetettiichchin, haiqqiichchidi yelettida gacino na7a mala gidopparkkee" yaagiis.

English Sentences: And Moses cried unto the LORD, saying, Heal her now, O God, I beseech thee.
Wolaitta Sentences: Yaagin Muusee, "Hai Xoossau, o pattarkkii!" yaagidi GODAAYYO waassiis.

English Sentences: And the LORD said unto Moses, If her father had but spit in her face, should she not be ashamed seven days? let her be shut out from the camp seven days, and after that let her be received in again.
Wolaitta Sentences: Waassin GODAI Muusa, "I aawai i som77uwan cuuchchaa cuchchidabaa gidiyaakko, laappun gallassaa a yeellaa maayada uttana gidekkeeyye? Hegaa gishshau, neeni o laappun gallassaa dunkkaanidosaappe gaxa baggaara dumma sohuwan utissa; hegaappe guyyiyan, simmada yu" yaagiis.

English Sentences: And Miriam was shut out from the camp seven days: and the people journeyed not till Miriam was brought in again.
Wolaitta Sentences: Yaatin Miiriyaama asai dunkkaanidosaappe gaxi kiyada laappun gallassaa uttaasu. A simmana gakkanaassi asai baanau denddibeenna.

English Sentences: And afterward the people removed from Hazeroth, and pitched in the wilderness of Paran.
Wolaitta Sentences: Hegaappe guyyiyan, asai Haxeroota giyoosaappe denddidi, Paaraana Bazzuwan dunkkaaniis.

English Sentences: And the LORD spake unto Moses, saying,
Wolaitta Sentences: GODAI, Muusa,

English Sentences: Send thou men, that they may search the land of Canaan, which I give unto the children of Israel: of every tribe of their fathers shall ye send a man, every one a ruler among them.
Wolaitta Sentences: "Taani Israa7eelatuyyo immiyo Kanaane biittaa wochchana mala, amarida asa kiitta; eta zare ubbaappe issi issi halaqaa kiitta" yaagiis.

English Sentences: And Moses by the commandment of the LORD sent them from the wilderness of Paran: all those men were heads of the children of Israel.
Wolaitta Sentences: Yaagin Muusee GODAA azazuwan Paaraana Bazzuwaappe eta kiittiis. Eti ubbaikka Israa7eela asa halaqata.

English Sentences: And these were their names: of the tribe of Reuben, Shammua the son of Zaccur.
Wolaitta Sentences: Eta sunttai hagaappe kaallidi xaafettidaagaa: Zariyaa Halaqaa Roobeela Zakkuura na7aa SHaamu7a

English Sentences: Of the tribe of Simeon, Shaphat the son of Hori.
Wolaitta Sentences: Simoona Hoora na7aa SHafaaxa

English Sentences: Of the tribe of Judah, Caleb the son of Jephunneh.
Wolaitta Sentences: Yihudaa Yifune na7aa Kaaleeba

English Sentences: Of the tribe of Issachar, Igal the son of Joseph.
Wolaitta Sentences: Yisaakoora Yooseefa na7aa Yigi7aala

English Sentences: Of the tribe of Ephraim, Oshea the son of Nun.
Wolaitta Sentences: Efireema Nawe na7aa Hoshee7a

English Sentences: Of the tribe of Benjamin, Palti the son of Raphu.
Wolaitta Sentences: Biniyaama Raafu na7aa Palxxa

English Sentences: Of the tribe of Zebulun, Gaddiel the son of Sodi.
Wolaitta Sentences: Zaabiloona Sooda na7aa Gaddi7eela

English Sentences: Of the tribe of Joseph, namely, of the tribe of Manasseh, Gaddi the son of Susi.
Wolaitta Sentences: Yooseefa na7aa Minaasa Suusa na7aa Gadda

English Sentences: Of the tribe of Dan, Ammiel the son of Gemalli.
Wolaitta Sentences: Daana Gamaalla na7aa Ami7eela

English Sentences: Of the tribe of Asher, Sethur the son of Michael.
Wolaitta Sentences: Aseera Mikaa7eela na7aa Satuura

English Sentences: Of the tribe of Naphtali, Nahbi the son of Vophsi.
Wolaitta Sentences: Nifttaaleema Waafisa na7aa Naahiba

English Sentences: Of the tribe of Gad, Geuel the son of Machi.
Wolaitta Sentences: Gaada Maaka na7aa Ge7u7eela.

English Sentences: These are the names of the men which Moses sent to spy out the land. And Moses called Oshea the son of Nun Jehoshua.
Wolaitta Sentences: He biittaa wochchana mala, Muusee kiittido asatu sunttai hagaappe qommoora de7iyaagaa. Muusee Nawe na7aa Hoshee7a sunttaa Yaasa yaagidi sunttiis.

English Sentences: And Moses sent them to spy out the land of Canaan, and said unto them, Get you up this way southward, and go up into the mountain:
Wolaitta Sentences: Eti Kanaane biittaa wochchana mala, Muusee eta kiittiyo wode hagaadan yaagiis; "Hagaappe Neegeeba Bazzuwaa pude kiyidi, yaappe huuphessa baggan de7iya gezze biittaa biite.

English Sentences: And see the land, what it is; and the people that dwelleth therein, whether they be strong or weak, few or many;
Wolaitta Sentences: Biidi biittai ai mala biittakkonne be7ite; he biittan de7iya asai minokkonne laafakko, guuttakkonne darokko,

English Sentences: And what the land is that they dwell in, whether it be good or bad; and what cities they be that they dwell in, whether in tents, or in strong holds;
Wolaitta Sentences: eti de7iyo biittai lo77okko iitakko, eti de7iyo katamainne ai mala katamakko, gimbbiyan diretti uttidaakko direttibeennaakko,

English Sentences: And what the land is, whether it be fat or lean, whether there be wood therein, or not. And be ye of good courage, and bring of the fruit of the land. Now the time was the time of the firstripe grapes.
Wolaitta Sentences: biittai ai mala araddakko ladakko, he biittan mitti de7iyaakko bainnaakko be7ite. Minnite! He biittan mokkidabaa aifiyaappe ekkennan yooppite" yaagiis. He wodee woine turai koiro aifiyaa aifiyo wode.

English Sentences: So they went up, and searched the land from the wilderness of Zin unto Rehob, as men come to Hamath.
Wolaitta Sentences: Yaagin eti pude kiyidi, Xiina giyo bazzuwaappe doommidi, biidi Hamaata Pinuwaa matan de7iya Rahooba gakkanaassi he biittaa wochchidosona.

English Sentences: And they ascended by the south, and came unto Hebron; where Ahiman, Sheshai, and Talmai, the children of Anak, were. (Now Hebron was built seven years before Zoan in Egypt.)
Wolaitta Sentences: Neegeeba Bazzuwaa pude kiyidi, Kebroona gakkidosona; hegan Ahimaana, SHeshaayanne Talmmaaya geetettiya Anaaqe zareti de7oosona. Kebrooni Gibxxen de7iya Xo7aane katamaappe laappun laittaa kaseti keexettiis.

English Sentences: And they came unto the brook of Eshcol, and cut down from thence a branch with one cluster of grapes, and they bare it between two upon a staff; and they brought of the pomegranates, and of the figs.
Wolaitta Sentences: Hegaara kanttidi, eti Eshkkoola giyo zanggaaraa biidi gakkido wode, woine tura issuwaappe issi wurccuwaara de7iya issi tashiyaa qanxxidosona; qanxxidi etappe naa77ai kasuwaa gidduwan gelissi tookkidosona. Hegaara roomaaniyaanne balasiyaa giyo mittatu aifiyaa ehiidosona.

English Sentences: The place was called the brook Eshcol, because of the cluster of grapes which the children of Israel cut down from thence.
Wolaitta Sentences: Israa7eela asati hegaappe qanxxido woine turaa wurccuwaa gishshau, he sohuwaa Eshkkoola Zanggaaraa giidi xeesidosona.

English Sentences: And they returned from searching of the land after forty days.
Wolaitta Sentences: Eti he biittaa wochchiiddi, oitamu gallassaappe guyyiyan simmidosona;

English Sentences: And they went and came to Moses, and to Aaron, and to all the congregation of the children of Israel, unto the wilderness of Paran, to Kadesh; and brought back word unto them, and unto all the congregation, and shewed them the fruit of the land.
Wolaitta Sentences: simmidi Paaraana Bazzuwan Qaadeesa giyoosan de7iya Muusekko, Aaroonakkonne Israa7eela asaa maabaraa ubbaakko yiidosona. Yiidi bantta be7idobaa etaunne asa ubbau yootidosona; he biittan aifiya aifiyaakka eta bessidosona.

English Sentences: And they told him, and said, We came unto the land whither thou sentest us, and surely it floweth with milk and honey; and this is the fruit of it.
Wolaitta Sentences: Eti Muuseyyo hagaadan yaagidi yootidosona; "Neeni nuna kiittido biittaa nuuni biida; he biittan maattainne eessai goggees. An aifiya aifiyaakka hagaa be7a.

English Sentences: Nevertheless the people be strong that dwell in the land, and the cities are walled, and very great: and moreover we saw the children of Anak there.
Wolaitta Sentences: SHin he biittan de7iya asai wolqqaama; eta katamaikka gimbbe dirssan diretti uttidaagaanne gita. Nuuni qassi Anaaqe zareta yan be7ida.

English Sentences: The Amalekites dwell in the land of the south: and the Hittites, and the Jebusites, and the Amorites, dwell in the mountains: and the Canaanites dwell by the sea, and by the coast of Jordan.
Wolaitta Sentences: Neegeeba Bazzuwan Amaaleeqa asati de7oosona; gezziyan Hiiteti, Yaabuusatinne Amooreti de7oosona; qassi Kanaaneti Meediteraane Abbaa doonaaninne Yorddaanoosa SHaafaa xanxxan de7oosona" yaagidosona.

English Sentences: And Caleb stilled the people before Moses, and said, Let us go up at once, and possess it; for we are well able to overcome it.
Wolaitta Sentences: Yaagin Kaaleebi asaa Muuse sinttan co77u giissidi, "Nuuni tumu xoonanau danddayiyo gishshau, pude ha77i kiyidi, he biittaa olidi ane oiqqoos" yaagiis.

English Sentences: But the men that went up with him said, We be not able to go up against the people; for they are stronger than we.
Wolaitta Sentences: SHin Kaaleebaara pude biida asati, "He biittaa asai nuuppe minniyo gishshau, nuuni eta xoonanau danddayokko" yaagidosona.

English Sentences: And they brought up an evil report of the land which they had searched unto the children of Israel, saying, The land, through which we have gone to search it, is a land that eateth up the inhabitants thereof; and all the people that we saw in it are men of a great stature.
Wolaitta Sentences: Eti yuuyi wochchido biittaabaa Israa7eela asaayyo hagaadan giidi, iita oduwaa odidosona, "Nuuni wochchido biittai banan de7iya asaakka miyaagaa; asai ubbaikka keehi adussa.

English Sentences: And there we saw the giants, the sons of Anak, which come of the giants: and we were in our own sight as grasshoppers, and so we were in their sight.
Wolaitta Sentences: Nuuni wogga adussa asatu yara gidiya Anaaqe zareta yan be7ida; nuuni nu aifiyan nuna xeelliyo wode gumbburo milatida; qassi nuuni eta aifiyan hegaakka mala" yaagidosona.

English Sentences: And all the congregation lifted up their voice, and cried; and the people wept that night.
Wolaitta Sentences: He gallassa qammi maabarai ubbai bantta qaalaa xoqqissidi yeekkidosona.

English Sentences: And all the children of Israel murmured against Moses and against Aaron: and the whole congregation said unto them, Would God that we had died in the land of Egypt! or would God we had died in this wilderness!
Wolaitta Sentences: Israa7eela asai ubbai Muuse bollinne Aaroona bolli zuuzummidosona. Maabarai kumettai eta, "Nuuni Gibxxe biittan de7iiddi haiqqidabaa gidorkkonii! Woikko nuuni ha bazzuwan haiqqidabaa gidorkkonii!

English Sentences: And wherefore hath the LORD brought us unto this land, to fall by the sword, that our wives and our children should be a prey? were it not better for us to return into Egypt?
Wolaitta Sentences: Bisuwan nuna wori wurssanau GODAI ha biitti nuna aissi ehii? Nu maccaasatinne nu naati omoodettana. Hegaappe guyye Gibxxe biitti simmiyoogee nuuyyo kehenneeyye?" yaagidosona.

English Sentences: And they said one to another, Let us make a captain, and let us return into Egypt.
Wolaitta Sentences: Qassi eti issoi issuwaa, "Nuuni kaalettiyaabaa dooridi, guyye Gibxxe simmoos" yaagidosona.

English Sentences: Then Moses and Aaron fell on their faces before all the assembly of the congregation of the children of Israel.
Wolaitta Sentences: Yaagin Muuseenne Aarooni hegan shiiqida Israa7eela asaa maabaraa ubbaa sinttan som77uwaa sa7an gattidi gufannidosona.

English Sentences: And Joshua the son of Nun, and Caleb the son of Jephunneh, which were of them that searched the land, rent their clothes:
Wolaitta Sentences: He biittaa wochchida asatu giddoppe Nawe na7ai Yaasunne Yifune na7ai Kaaleebi bantta maayuwaa pooshshidosona.

English Sentences: And they spake unto all the company of the children of Israel, saying, The land, which we passed through to search it, is an exceeding good land.
Wolaitta Sentences: Pooshshidi Israa7eela asaa maabaraa ubbaayyo, "Nuuni kantti kiyidi wochchido biittai keehi daro lo77o.

English Sentences: If the LORD delight in us, then he will bring us into this land, and give it us; a land which floweth with milk and honey.
Wolaitta Sentences: GODAI nunan ufaittiyaabaa gidikko, maattainne eessai goggiyo he biittau nuna i gelissana; he biittaa nuuyyo i immana.

English Sentences: Only rebel not ye against the LORD, neither fear ye the people of the land; for they are bread for us: their defence is departed from them, and the LORD is with us: fear them not.
Wolaitta Sentences: Hegaa gishshau, GODAA bolli makkala makkaloppite. He biittaa asau yayyoppite; eti nuuyyo haatta ushshakka gakkokkona. Etau ambboomiyaabi baawa; shin GODAI nunaara de7ees. Intte etayyo yayyoppite!" yaagidosona.

English Sentences: But all the congregation bade stone them with stones. And the glory of the LORD appeared in the tabernacle of the congregation before all the children of Israel.
Wolaitta Sentences: Yaagin maabarai ubbai eta shuchchan caddanau denddiis. He wode GODAA bonchchoi Xoossaa Dunkkaaniyan Israa7eela asa ubbau qoncciis.

English Sentences: And the LORD said unto Moses, How long will this people provoke me? and how long will it be ere they believe me, for all the signs which I have shewed among them?
Wolaitta Sentences: GODAI Muusa, "Ha asai aude gakkanaassi tana karanee? Taani eta gidduwan oottido malaata ubbaa be7iiddi, aude gakkanaassi eti tanan ammanennan ixxanee?

English Sentences: I will smite them with the pestilence, and disinherit them, and will make of thee a greater nation and mightier than they.
Wolaitta Sentences: Taani eta boshan shocada xaissana; yaatada taani nena etappe dariyaanne minniya kawotettaayyo aawa oottana" yaagiis.

English Sentences: And Moses said unto the LORD, Then the Egyptians shall hear it, (for thou broughtest up this people in thy might from among them;)
Wolaitta Sentences: Yaagin Muusee GODAA hagaadan yaagidi woossiis; "Neeni ne wolqqan ha asaa Gibxxeppe pude kessidoogaa eriya Gibxxeti hagaa siyikko, eti woiganee?

English Sentences: And they will tell it to the inhabitants of this land: for they have heard that thou LORD art among this people, that thou LORD art seen face to face, and that thy cloud standeth over them, and that thou goest before them, by day time in a pillar of a cloud, and in a pillar of fire by night.
Wolaitta Sentences: Eti ha biittan de7iyaageetuyyookka hegaa odana. Abeet GODAU, neeni ha asaa gidduwan de7iyoogaa eti siyidosona. Abeet GODAU, nuuni nena be7idoogaa eti eridosona; ne shaarai etappe bollaara takkiyoogaanne gallassi shaaraa tuussan, qammi tamaa tuussan neeni eta sinttan biyoogaa be7idosona.

English Sentences: Now if thou shalt kill all this people as one man, then the nations which have heard the fame of thee will speak, saying,
Wolaitta Sentences: Ha77i neeni ha asaa ubbaa issi kuttan woriyaaba gidikko, ne kase oottidoogaa siyida kawotettati,

English Sentences: Because the LORD was not able to bring this people into the land which he sware unto them, therefore he hath slain them in the wilderness.
Wolaitta Sentences: GODAI ha asaa, "Intteyyo immana" giidi caaqqido biittaa eta efaanau danddayibeenna gishshau, bazzuwan eta woriis yaagidi haasayana.

English Sentences: And now, I beseech thee, let the power of my LORD be great, according as thou hast spoken, saying,
Wolaitta Sentences: "Hegaa gishshau, Godau, neeni ne wolqqaa nuna bessa; neeni gaidda,

English Sentences: The LORD is longsuffering, and of great mercy, forgiving iniquity and transgression, and by no means clearing the guilty, visiting the iniquity of the fathers upon the children unto the third and fourth generation.
Wolaitta Sentences: GODAI danddayanchchanne aggenna siiquwan kumidaagaa; nagaraanne makkalaa atto giyaagaa; gidikkonne, mooranchchaa qaxxayennan aggennaagaa; aawatu nagaraa gishshau naata heezzanttanne oiddantta yeletaa gakkanaassi qaxxayiyaagaa gaada yoota wottidoogaa pola.

English Sentences: Pardon, I beseech thee, the iniquity of this people according unto the greatness of thy mercy, and as thou hast forgiven this people, from Egypt even until now.
Wolaitta Sentences: Ha asai Gibxxeppe kiyoosappe doommada hachchi gakkanaassi neeni atto giidoogaadan, ne aggenna siiquwaa daruwan ha asaa nagaraa atto garkkii!" yaagiis.

English Sentences: And the LORD said, I have pardoned according to thy word:
Wolaitta Sentences: Yaagin GODAI Muusa, "Neeni oichchidoogaadan taani etayyo atto gaas.

English Sentences: But as truly as I live, all the earth shall be filled with the glory of the LORD.
Wolaitta Sentences: SHin ta de7uwan caaqqais; ta bonchchoi sa7a ubbaa kumiyoogaadan,

English Sentences: Because all those men which have seen my glory, and my miracles, which I did in Egypt and in the wilderness, and have tempted me now these ten times, and have not hearkened to my voice;
Wolaitta Sentences: ha asaappe issoinne he biittaa be7enna. Ta bonchchuwaanne Gibxxe biittaaninne bazzuwan taani oottido malaataa ha asati be7idosona;

English Sentences: Surely they shall not see the land which I sware unto their fathers, neither shall any of them that provoked me see it:
Wolaitta Sentences: shin eti zaaretti zaarettidi tana paaccidosonanne ta qaalaa siyennan ixxidosona. Hegaa gishshau, taani eta maizza aawatuyyo immana gaada caaqqido biittaa tana karidaageetuppe issoinne mulekka be7enna.

English Sentences: But my servant Caleb, because he had another spirit with him, and hath followed me fully, him will I bring into the land whereinto he went; and his seed shall possess it.
Wolaitta Sentences: SHin ta ashkkarai Kaaleebi etappe dummatiyo gishshaunne i tana polo wozanaappe kaallido gishshau, taani i kase biido biittaa a gattana; a zerettai he biittaa laattana.

English Sentences: (Now the Amalekites and the Canaanites dwelt in the valley.) Tomorrow turn you, and get you into the wilderness by the way of the Red sea.
Wolaitta Sentences: SHin ha77i Amaaleeqatinne Kanaaneti wombban de7iyo gishshau, wontto guyye simmidi, Zo7o Abbaakko efiya ogiyaa oiqqidi bazzo biite" yaagiis.

English Sentences: And the LORD spake unto Moses and unto Aaron, saying,
Wolaitta Sentences: Qassi GODAI Muusanne Aaroona hagaadan yaagiis;

English Sentences: How long shall I bear with this evil congregation, which murmur against me? I have heard the murmurings of the children of Israel, which they murmur against me.
Wolaitta Sentences: "Ha iita asai ta bolli aude gakkanaassi zuuzummanee? Taani Israa7eela asaa zuuzunttaa ubbaa siyaas.

English Sentences: Say unto them, As truly as I live, saith the LORD, as ye have spoken in mine ears, so will I do to you:
Wolaitta Sentences: Hegaa gishshau, neeni etau hagaadan yaagada oda; Ta de7uwan caaqqais; taani intte haasayishin ta haittan siyidoogaa intteyyo oottana. Taani GODAI hegaa odais.

English Sentences: Your carcases shall fall in this wilderness; and all that were numbered of you, according to your whole number, from twenty years old and upward, which have murmured against me,
Wolaitta Sentences: Intte ahai ha bazzuwan kunddana; aissi giikko, asaa qoodiyo wode qoodettida laatamu laittanne hegaappe bollaara de7iya asai ubbai ta bolli zuuzummideta.

English Sentences: Doubtless ye shall not come into the land, concerning which I sware to make you dwell therein, save Caleb the son of Jephunneh, and Joshua the son of Nun.
Wolaitta Sentences: Yifune na7aa Kaaleebappenne Nawe na7aa Yaasuppe attin, intteppe ooninne taani inttena wottanau caaqqido he biittaa gelenna.

English Sentences: But your little ones, which ye said should be a prey, them will I bring in, and they shall know the land which ye have despised.
Wolaitta Sentences: Intte, "Nu naati omoodettana" giido intte guutta naata he intte karido biittaa gelissana; biittaikka etassa gidana.

English Sentences: But as for you, your carcases, they shall fall in this wilderness.
Wolaitta Sentences: SHin inttena gidikko, intte ahai ha bazzuwan kunddana.

English Sentences: And your children shall wander in the wilderness forty years, and bear your whoredoms, until your carcases be wasted in the wilderness.
Wolaitta Sentences: Intte ammanettibeenna gishshau, intte wurssetta ahai ha bazzuwan wullana gakkanaassi, intte naati waayettiiddi, ha bazzuwan oitamu laittaa henttanchcha gididi yuuyana.

English Sentences: After the number of the days in which ye searched the land, even forty days, each day for a year, shall ye bear your iniquities, even forty years, and ye shall know my breach of promise.
Wolaitta Sentences: Intte he biittaa wochchido he oitamu gallassaa qoodan, issi gallassaayyo issi laittaa, hegeenne, oitamu laittau intte nagaraa gishshau intte waayettana; taani intte bolli denddiyoogaa intte erana yaaga yoota.

English Sentences: I the LORD have said, I will surely do it unto all this evil congregation, that are gathered together against me: in this wilderness they shall be consumed, and there they shall die.
Wolaitta Sentences: Taani GODAI hagaa odais. Ta bolli shiiqi uttida ha iita maabaraa bolli hagaadan tumu oottana: eti ha bazzuwan wurana; hagan eti haiqqana" yaagiis.

English Sentences: And the men, which Moses sent to search the land, who returned, and made all the congregation to murmur against him, by bringing up a slander upon the land,
Wolaitta Sentences: He biittaa wochchana mala, Muusee eta kiittin biidi simmida asati, he biittaabaa iita oduwaa odidi, Muuse bolli asai ubbai zuuzummana mala oottidaageeti,

English Sentences: Even those men that did bring up the evil report upon the land, died by the plague before the LORD.
Wolaitta Sentences: he iita oduwaa odida asati, GODAA sinttan boshan haiqqidosona.

English Sentences: But Joshua the son of Nun, and Caleb the son of Jephunneh, which were of the men that went to search the land, lived still.
Wolaitta Sentences: He biittaa wochchanau biida asatuppe Yifune na7ai Kaaleebinne Nawe na7ai Yaasu xalaalai paxa attidosona.

English Sentences: And Moses told these sayings unto all the children of Israel: and the people mourned greatly.
Wolaitta Sentences: Muusee hagaa Israa7eela asau ubbau yootido wode, asai keehi yeekkiis.

English Sentences: And they rose up early in the morning, and gat them up into the top of the mountain, saying, Lo, we be here, and will go up unto the place which the LORD hath promised: for we have sinned.
Wolaitta Sentences: Wonttetta gallassi maallado guuran eti denddidi, pude gezze biittaa kiyidi, "Nuuni nagaraa oottida; shin ha77i GODAI nuuyyo immana giido sohuwaa pude kiyana" yaagidosona.

English Sentences: And Moses said, Wherefore now do ye transgress the commandment of the LORD? but it shall not prosper.
Wolaitta Sentences: SHin Muusee eta, "GODAA azazuwaa intte aibissi mentteetii? Intteyyo hanenna.

English Sentences: Go not up, for the LORD is not among you; that ye be not smitten before your enemies.
Wolaitta Sentences: GODAI inttenaara de7enna gishshau, pude kiyoppite; intte morkketi inttena xoonana.

English Sentences: For the Amalekites and the Canaanites are there before you, and ye shall fall by the sword: because ye are turned away from the LORD, therefore the LORD will not be with you.
Wolaitta Sentences: Amaaleeqa asatuuranne Kanaane asatuura intte olettana; olettidi intte bisuwan haiqqana. GODAAPPE intte wora simmido gishshau, GODAI inttenaara de7enna" yaagiis.

English Sentences: But they presumed to go up unto the hill top: nevertheless the ark of the covenant of the LORD, and Moses, departed not out of the camp.
Wolaitta Sentences: SHin eti GODAA Maachchaa Taabootainne Muuseenne dunkkaanidosaappe denddana xayikkokka, gezze biittaa kiyanau xalidi denddidosona.

English Sentences: Then the Amalekites came down, and the Canaanites which dwelt in that hill, and smote them, and discomfited them, even unto Hormah.
Wolaitta Sentences: Denddin gezze biittan de7iya Amaaleeqa asatinne Kanaane asati wodhdhidi eta oli xoonidi, Horima gakkanaassi eta yedettidosona.

English Sentences: And the LORD spake unto Moses, saying,
Wolaitta Sentences: GODAI Muusa hagaadan yaagiis;

English Sentences: Speak unto the children of Israel, and say unto them, When ye be come into the land of your habitations, which I give unto you,
Wolaitta Sentences: "Israa7eela asaayyo hagaadan yaaga; Intte de7ana mala, taani intteyyo immiyo biitti geliyo wode,

English Sentences: And will make an offering by fire unto the LORD, a burnt offering, or a sacrifice in performing a vow, or in a freewill offering, or in your solemn feasts, to make a sweet savour unto the LORD, of the herd, or of the flock:
Wolaitta Sentences: mehiyaappe woikko dorssaappe, xuuggiyo yarshsho gidin, woikko shiiqo gattanau yarshshiyo yarshsho gidin, woikko taani keerido baala gallassatun intte dosan coo immiyo yarshsho gidin, GODAAYYO taman xuuggiyo, sawuwaa tonggu giya yarshshota yarshshite.

English Sentences: Then shall he that offereth his offering unto the LORD bring a meat offering of a tenth deal of flour mingled with the fourth part of an hin of oil.
Wolaitta Sentences: Yarshshuwaa shiishshiya urai kattaa yarshshuwaassi issi kilo giraame xiilliyaa issi litiro wogaraa zaitiyan munaqqidoogaakka eho.

English Sentences: And the fourth part of an hin of wine for a drink offering shalt thou prepare with the burnt offering or sacrifice, for one lamb.
Wolaitta Sentences: Qassi xuuggiyo yarshshuwaassi, woikko hara yarshshuwaassi ehiyo issi issi dorssaara issi litiro woiniyaa eessaa ushshaa yarshsho oottidi giigissite.

English Sentences: Or for a ram, thou shalt prepare for a meat offering two tenth deals of flour mingled with the third part of an hin of oil.
Wolaitta Sentences: "Dorssa orggiyaa yarshshanau shiishshiyo wode, kattaa yarshshuwaassi naa77u kilo giraame xiilliyaa issi litironne bagga wogaraa zaitiyan munaqqidoogaanne

English Sentences: And for a drink offering thou shalt offer the third part of an hin of wine, for a sweet savour unto the LORD.
Wolaitta Sentences: issi litironne bagga woine eessaa ushshaa yarshshuwaassi ehiite. Ehiidi GODAAYYO sawuwaa tonggu giya yarshshuwaa yarshshite.

English Sentences: And when thou preparest a bullock for a burnt offering, or for a sacrifice in performing a vow, or peace offerings unto the LORD:
Wolaitta Sentences: "Issi mirgguwaa xuuggiyo yarshsho, woikko shiiquwaa gattiyo yarshsho, woikko issippetettaa yarshsho oottidi yarshshanau GODAAYYO ehiyo wode,

English Sentences: Then shall he bring with a bullock a meat offering of three tenth deals of flour mingled with half an hin of oil.
Wolaitta Sentences: mirgguwaara issippe kattaa yarshshuwaassi heezzu kilo giraame xiilliyaa naa77u litiro wogaraa zaitiyan munaqqidoogaanne

English Sentences: And thou shalt bring for a drink offering half an hin of wine, for an offering made by fire, of a sweet savour unto the LORD.
Wolaitta Sentences: ushshaa yarshshuwaassi naa77u litiro woiniyaa eessaakka ehiite. Ehiidi GODAAYYO sawuwaa tonggu giya yarshshuwaa taman yarshshite.

English Sentences: Thus shall it be done for one bullock, or for one ram, or for a lamb, or a kid.
Wolaitta Sentences: "Issi issi korima booraa, woikko issi issi dorssa orggiyaa, woikko yelaga deeshsha orggiyaa, woikko attuma dorssa maraa yarshshanau shiishshiyo wode, kattaa yarshshoinne ushshaa yarshshoi hagaadan issippe shiiqees.

English Sentences: According to the number that ye shall prepare, so shall ye do to every one according to their number.
Wolaitta Sentences: Issi meheppe daroi shiiqiyo wode, kattaa yarshshoinne ushshaa yarshshoi hegaadan daridi shiiqees.

English Sentences: All that are born of the country shall do these things after this manner, in offering an offering made by fire, of a sweet savour unto the LORD.
Wolaitta Sentences: Israa7eela asa gidiya ooninne taman xuuggiyo, sawuwaa tonggu giya yarshshuwaa GODAAYYO shiishshiyo wode ubban, hagaadan oottanau koshshees.

English Sentences: And if a stranger sojourn with you, or whosoever be among you in your generations, and will offer an offering made by fire, of a sweet savour unto the LORD; as ye do, so he shall do.
Wolaitta Sentences: Sinttappe yaana yeletan intte giddon de7iya betee woikko hara asi ooninne xuuggiyo, sawuwaa tonggu giya yarshshuwaa GODAAYYO shiishshanau koyikko, ikka intte oottiyoogaadan oottanau koshshees.

English Sentences: One ordinance shall be both for you of the congregation, and also for the stranger that sojourneth with you, an ordinance for ever in your generations: as ye are, so shall the stranger be before the LORD.
Wolaitta Sentences: Inttessikka intte giddon de7iya betetussikka ha wogai issuwaa; hagee sinttappe yaana yeletaassikka eqqidi de7iya woga. Inttekka betetikka GODAA sinttan issuwaa.

English Sentences: One law and one manner shall be for you, and for the stranger that sojourneth with you.
Wolaitta Sentences: Inttessikka intte giddon de7iya bete asatussikka higgeenne wogai issuwaa gidana yaaga" yaagiis.

English Sentences: And the LORD spake unto Moses, saying,
Wolaitta Sentences: Hegaappe guyyiyan, GODAI Muusa hagaadan yaagiis;

English Sentences: Speak unto the children of Israel, and say unto them, When ye come into the land whither I bring you,
Wolaitta Sentences: "Israa7eela asaayyo hagaadan yaagada oda; Taani inttena efiyo biitti intte gelidi,

English Sentences: Then it shall be, that, when ye eat of the bread of the land, ye shall offer up an heave offering unto the LORD.
Wolaitta Sentences: he biittan mokkiya kattaa miyo wode, he kattaappe xeeraa kessidi, intte GODAAYYO yarshsho oottidi shiishshite.

English Sentences: Ye shall offer up a cake of the first of your dough for an heave offering: as ye do the heave offering of the threshingfloor, so shall ye heave it.
Wolaitta Sentences: Hegeekka, baira ka77ida kattaappe uukkido koiro komppuwaa, kattaa qoxxiyo audiyaappe immiyo yarshsho oottidi shiishshite.

English Sentences: Of the first of your dough ye shall give unto the LORD an heave offering in your generations.
Wolaitta Sentences: Yaana yeleta ubban intte intte biittan mokkida kattaappe xeeraa kessido komppuwaa, GODAAYYO yarshsho oottidi shiishshite.

English Sentences: And if ye have erred, and not observed all these commandments, which the LORD hath spoken unto Moses,
Wolaitta Sentences: "GODAI Muusessi odido ha azazota ubbaa intte erana xayidi, naagennan aggikko,

English Sentences: Even all that the LORD hath commanded you by the hand of Moses, from the day that the LORD commanded Moses, and henceforward among your generations;
Wolaitta Sentences: GODAI a baggaara inttena azazido azazota ubbaa, GODAI immido gallassaappe doommidi, yaana yeletaa gakkanaashin, paccennan naagennan aggikko,

English Sentences: Then it shall be, if ought be committed by ignorance without the knowledge of the congregation, that all the congregation shall offer one young bullock for a burnt offering, for a sweet savour unto the LORD, with his meat offering, and his drink offering, according to the manner, and one kid of the goats for a sin offering.
Wolaitta Sentences: qassi hegaa maabarai erennan oottidoba gidikko, maabarai ubbai GODAAYYO issi mirgguwaa xuuggiyo, sawuwaa tonggu giya yarshsho oottidi, ayyo wogai azaziyoogaadan, kattaa yarshshuwaaranne ushshaa yarshshuwaara shiishsho; qassi nagaraa yarshsho oottidi, issi deeshsha orggiyaa shiishsho.

English Sentences: And the priest shall make an atonement for all the congregation of the children of Israel, and it shall be forgiven them; for it is ignorance: and they shall bring their offering, a sacrifice made by fire unto the LORD, and their sin offering before the LORD, for their ignorance:
Wolaitta Sentences: Yaatobare qeesee kumetta Israa7eela maabaraa nagaraa atto giissiyo wogaa polo; polin eta nagarai atto geetettana. Aissi giikko, eti eriiddi oottibookkona; qassi eti bantta mooruwaa gishshau, GODAAYYO taman xuuggiyo yarshshuwaanne bantta nagaraa yarshshuwaa shiishshidosona.

English Sentences: And it shall be forgiven all the congregation of the children of Israel, and the stranger that sojourneth among them; seeing all the people were in ignorance.
Wolaitta Sentences: Asai ubbai erennan he mooruwan hambbalaashettido gishshau, kumetta Israa7eela maabaraukka eta giddon de7iya bete asaukka atto geetettana.

English Sentences: And if any soul sin through ignorance, then he shall bring a she goat of the first year for a sin offering.
Wolaitta Sentences: "Issi asi barkka erana xayidi nagaraa oottikko, yelettoosappe issi laitta gidiyo issi deeshshiyo nagaraa yarshsho oottidi shiishsho;

English Sentences: And the priest shall make an atonement for the soul that sinneth ignorantly, when he sinneth by ignorance before the LORD, to make an atonement for him; and it shall be forgiven him.
Wolaitta Sentences: shiishshin erennan de7iiddi nagaraa oottida uraayyo qeesee GODAA sinttan nagaraa atto giissiyo wogaa polo; polin a nagarai atto geetettana.

English Sentences: Ye shall have one law for him that sinneth through ignorance, both for him that is born among the children of Israel, and for the stranger that sojourneth among them.
Wolaitta Sentences: Erennan de7iiddi nagaraa oottiya asa ubbau, yeletan Israa7eela asa gidinkka bete asa gidinkka ha higgee issuwaa.

English Sentences: But the soul that doeth ought presumptuously, whether he be born in the land, or a stranger, the same reproacheth the LORD; and that soul shall be cut off from among his people.
Wolaitta Sentences: "SHin yeletan Israa7eela asa gidinkka bete asa gidinkka eriiddi otoruwan nagara oottiya uri GODAA cayees. He aawu haiqqidi, ba asaa giddoppe xayo.

English Sentences: Because he hath despised the word of the LORD, and hath broken his commandment, that soul shall utterly be cut off; his iniquity shall be upon him.
Wolaitta Sentences: He aawu GODAA qaalaa karido gishshaunne a azazuwaa kanttido gishshau, i tumuppe haiqqanau bessees; a mooroi aana yaaga" yaagiis.

English Sentences: And while the children of Israel were in the wilderness, they found a man that gathered sticks upon the sabbath day.
Wolaitta Sentences: Issi gallassi Israa7eela asai bazzon de7ishin, issi bitanee Sambbatan mittaa mixiiddi beettiis.

English Sentences: And they that found him gathering sticks brought him unto Moses and Aaron, and unto all the congregation.
Wolaitta Sentences: Mittaa i mixishin demmida asati Muusekko, Aaroonakkonne kumetta yaa7aakko a ehiidosona.

English Sentences: And they put him in ward, because it was not declared what should be done to him.
Wolaitta Sentences: Ehin eti a oottanabaa eribeenna gishshau, qashuwan takissidosona.

English Sentences: And the LORD said unto Moses, The man shall be surely put to death: all the congregation shall stone him with stones without the camp.
Wolaitta Sentences: Hegaappe guyyiyan GODAI Muusa, "Ha bitanee haiqqanau bessees; kumetta yaa7ai bantta dunkkaanidosaappe gaxi kessidi, shuchchan caddidi a woro" yaagiis.

English Sentences: And all the congregation brought him without the camp, and stoned him with stones, and he died; as the LORD commanded Moses.
Wolaitta Sentences: Yaagin kumetta yaa7ai GODAI Muusa azazidoogaadan, dunkkaanidosaappe gaxi kessidi, shuchchan caddidi a woriis.

English Sentences: And the LORD spake unto Moses, saying,
Wolaitta Sentences: GODAI Muusa hagaadan yaagiis;

English Sentences: Speak unto the children of Israel, and bid them that they make them fringes in the borders of their garments throughout their generations, and that they put upon the fringe of the borders a ribband of blue:
Wolaitta Sentences: "Israa7eela asaayyo hagaadan yaagada oda; Inttekka sinttappe yaana yeletaikka intte maayuwaa gaxa xeeran xeeran macaraa kessite; kessidi he macaraa bolli salo milatiya qacinaa sikkite.

English Sentences: And it shall be unto you for a fringe, that ye may look upon it, and remember all the commandments of the LORD, and do them; and that ye seek not after your own heart and your own eyes, after which ye use to go a whoring:
Wolaitta Sentences: He macaraa intte be7iyo wode ubban ta azazota hassayidi polite; yaatikko, intte intte aifiyaanne intte wozanaa amuwaa kaallidi, taappe wora simmekketa.

English Sentences: That ye may remember, and do all my commandments, and be holy unto your God.
Wolaitta Sentences: He macaraa be7iyoogan intte ta azazota ubbaa hassayidi polananne intte intte Xoossaayyo geeshsha gidana.

English Sentences: I am the LORD your God, which brought you out of the land of Egypt, to be your God: I am the LORD your God.
Wolaitta Sentences: Taani GODAA, intte Xoossaattennee; taani intte Xoossaa gidanau, inttena Gibxxeppe kessaas. Taani GODAA, intte Xoossaa yaaga" yaagiis.

English Sentences: Now Korah, the son of Izhar, the son of Kohath, the son of Levi, and Dathan and Abiram, the sons of Eliab, and On, the son of Peleth, sons of Reuben, took men:
Wolaitta Sentences: Leewa zariyaappe Qahaata yara gidiya Yixihaara na7ai Qoraahi, Roobeela zariyaappe Eli7aaba naati Daataaninne Abiiraaminne qassi Peleeta na7ai Ooni

English Sentences: And they rose up before Moses, with certain of the children of Israel, two hundred and fifty princes of the assembly, famous in the congregation, men of renown:
Wolaitta Sentences: Muuse bolli denddidosona. Etaara naa77u xeetanne ishatamu Israa7eela asati de7oosona; eti erettida asanne maabaran doorettida kaalettiyaageeta.

English Sentences: And they gathered themselves together against Moses and against Aaron, and said unto them, Ye take too much upon you, seeing all the congregation are holy, every one of them, and the LORD is among them: wherefore then lift ye up yourselves above the congregation of the LORD?
Wolaitta Sentences: Eti Muusenne Aaroona sintti shiiqidi, hagaadan yaagidosona; "Intte darissideta! Maabarai ubbai huuphiyan huuphiyan geeshsha; GODAIKKA eta gidduwan de7ees; yaatin GODAA maabaraa bolli inttena aissi xoqqu xoqqu ootteetii?" yaagidosona.

English Sentences: And when Moses heard it, he fell upon his face:
Wolaitta Sentences: Muusee hagaa siyido wode GODAA sinttan sa7an gufanniis;

English Sentences: And he spake unto Korah and unto all his company, saying, Even to morrow the LORD will shew who are his, and who is holy; and will cause him to come near unto him: even him whom he hath chosen will he cause to come near unto him.
Wolaitta Sentences: gufannidi Qoraahanne a citaa ubbaa, "Wontto maallado GODAI ooni aagaakkonne ooni geeshshakkonne bessana; i he dooriyo asa baakko shiishshana.

English Sentences: This do; Take you censers, Korah, and all his company;
Wolaitta Sentences: Qoraahaa, neeninne ne citai ubbai hagaa oottite: wontto ixaanaa cuwayiyoogeeta ekkidi,

English Sentences: And put fire therein, and put incense in them before the LORD to morrow: and it shall be that the man whom the LORD doth choose, he shall be holy: ye take too much upon you, ye sons of Levi.
Wolaitta Sentences: bonqquwaa an wottidi, GODAA sinttan ixaanaa cuwayite. GODAI dooriyo asi, i geeshsha gidana. Leewa zaretoo, intte darissideta" yaagiis.

English Sentences: And Moses said unto Korah, Hear, I pray you, ye sons of Levi:
Wolaitta Sentences: Muusee qassikka Qoraaha, "Inttenoo Leewa zaretoo, siyite!

English Sentences: Seemeth it but a small thing unto you, that the God of Israel hath separated you from the congregation of Israel, to bring you near to himself to do the service of the tabernacle of the LORD, and to stand before the congregation to minister unto them?
Wolaitta Sentences: Israa7eela Xoossai inttena Israa7eela maabaraappe dummayidi, Xoossaa Dunkkaaniyaa oosuwaa oottana malanne asaa sinttan he oosuwaa oottanau intte eqqana mala, baakko shiishshidoogee intteyyo guuxxidee?

English Sentences: And he hath brought thee near to him, and all thy brethren the sons of Levi with thee: and seek ye the priesthood also?
Wolaitta Sentences: I inttenanne intte ishantta Leewata ubbaa baakko shiishshiis; qassi ha77i intte qeesetettaakka kajjeeleeta.

English Sentences: For which cause both thou and all thy company are gathered together against the LORD: and what is Aaron, that ye murmur against him?
Wolaitta Sentences: Neeninne ne citai ubbai Aaroona bolli zuuzummiyoogaa GODAA bolli makkaleeta" yaagiis.

English Sentences: And Moses sent to call Dathan and Abiram, the sons of Eliab: which said, We will not come up:
Wolaitta Sentences: Hegaappe guyyiyan, Muusee kiittidi Eli7aaba naata, Daataananne Abiiraama xeesissiis; shin eti a, "Nuuni bookko!

English Sentences: Is it a small thing that thou hast brought us up out of a land that floweth with milk and honey, to kill us in the wilderness, except thou make thyself altogether a prince over us?
Wolaitta Sentences: Neeni bazzuwan nuna woranau maattainne eessai goggiyo biittaappe kessidoogee guuxxidee? Qassi ha77i neeni nu bolli halaqa gidanau koyai?

English Sentences: Moreover thou hast not brought us into a land that floweth with milk and honey, or given us inheritance of fields and vineyards: wilt thou put out the eyes of these men? we will not come up.
Wolaitta Sentences: Hegaa bollikka qassi maattainne eessai goggiyo biittaa neeni nuna gelissabaakka, woikko neeni nuuyyo laata oottada gadiyaanne woine turaa immabaakka; neeni ha asaa cimmaasa. Nuuni bookko!" yaagidosona.

English Sentences: And Moses was very wroth, and said unto the LORD, Respect not thou their offering: I have not taken one ass from them, neither have I hurt one of them.
Wolaitta Sentences: Yaagin Muusee keehi hanqqettidi GODAA, "Neeni eti yarshshiyo yarshshuwaa ekkoppa; taani etappe hare issuwaanne ekkabeikke, woikko taani etappe issi asanne naaqqabeikke" yaagiis.

English Sentences: And Moses said unto Korah, Be thou and all thy company before the LORD, thou, and they, and Aaron, to morrow:
Wolaitta Sentences: Qassi Muusee Qoraaha, "Wontto neeni, ne citai ubbainne Aarooni GODAA sintti shiiqite.

English Sentences: And take every man his censer, and put incense in them, and bring ye before the LORD every man his censer, two hundred and fifty censers; thou also, and Aaron, each of you his censer.
Wolaitta Sentences: Issi issi asai ba ixaanaa cuwayiyoogaa muleera naa77u xeetanne ishatamaa ekkidi, ixaanaa an wottidi, GODAA sintti shiishsho. Qassi neeninne Aarooni intte ixaanaa cuwayiyoogeeta ehiite" yaagiis.

English Sentences: And they took every man his censer, and put fire in them, and laid incense thereon, and stood in the door of the tabernacle of the congregation with Moses and Aaron.
Wolaitta Sentences: Yaagin asai ubbaikka ba ixaanaa cuwayiyoogaa ekkidi, bonqquwaanne ixaanaa an wottiis; wottidi Xoossaa Dunkkaaniyaa penggen Muuseeranne Aaroonaara eqqidosona.

English Sentences: And Korah gathered all the congregation against them unto the door of the tabernacle of the congregation: and the glory of the LORD appeared unto all the congregation.
Wolaitta Sentences: Eqqidaashin Qoraahi kumetta maabaraa Xoossaa Dunkkaaniyaa penggen shiishshiis. He wode GODAA bonchchoi kumetta maabarau qoncciis.

English Sentences: And the LORD spake unto Moses and unto Aaron, saying,
Wolaitta Sentences: GODAI Muusanne Aaroona,

English Sentences: Separate yourselves from among this congregation, that I may consume them in a moment.
Wolaitta Sentences: "Taani issi kuttan ha maabaraa xaissana haniyo gishshau, etappe shaahettite" yaagiis.

English Sentences: And they fell upon their faces, and said, O God, the God of the spirits of all flesh, shall one man sin, and wilt thou be wroth with all the congregation?
Wolaitta Sentences: SHin Muuseenne Aarooni sa7an gufannidi, "Abeet Xoossau, asho maayida asaa ubbaa medhdhida Xoossau, issi uri nagara oottikko, neeni kumetta maabaraa hanqqettai?" yaagidosona.

English Sentences: And the LORD spake unto Moses, saying,
Wolaitta Sentences: Yaatin GODAI Muusa,

English Sentences: Speak unto the congregation, saying, Get you up from about the tabernacle of Korah, Dathan, and Abiram.
Wolaitta Sentences: "Neeni maabaraa, Qoraaha, Daataananne Abiiraama dunkkaanetuppe kichchite yaagada yoota" yaagiis.

English Sentences: And Moses rose up and went unto Dathan and Abiram; and the elders of Israel followed him.
Wolaitta Sentences: Muusee denddidi, Daataanakkonne Abiiraamakko bin, Israa7eela cimati a kaallidosona.

English Sentences: And he spake unto the congregation, saying, Depart, I pray you, from the tents of these wicked men, and touch nothing of theirs, lest ye be consumed in all their sins.
