Wolaitta Sentences: Maabaraa i, "Ha iita asatu dunkkaanetuppe kichchite; etabaa gididabaa aibaanne bochchoppite. Hinkkoode eta nagaraa ubbaa gaasuwan inttekka pitetti xayana" yaagidi minttidi yootiis.

English Sentences: So they gat up from the tabernacle of Korah, Dathan, and Abiram, on every side: and Dathan and Abiram came out, and stood in the door of their tents, and their wives, and their sons, and their little children.
Wolaitta Sentences: Yootin eti Qoraaha, Daataananne Abiiraama dunkkaanetuppe kichchidosona. Daataaninne Abiiraami kare kiyidi, bantta maccaasatuura, bantta naatuuranne bantta guutta naatuura bantta dunkkaanetu penggen eqqidosona.

English Sentences: And Moses said, Hereby ye shall know that the LORD hath sent me to do all these works; for I have not done them of mine own mind.
Wolaitta Sentences: Muusee asaa, "Taani ha ooso ubbaa oottana mala, GODAI tana kiittidoogaanne taani ta sheniyan oottennaagaa intte hagan erana.

English Sentences: If these men die the common death of all men, or if they be visited after the visitation of all men; then the LORD hath not sent me.
Wolaitta Sentences: Ha asati asi haiqqiyoogaadan haiqqikko, woikko asa bolli gakkiyaaba xalaalai eta bolli gakkikko, yaatikko GODAI tana kiittibeenna.

English Sentences: But if the LORD make a new thing, and the earth open her mouth, and swallow them up, with all that appertain unto them, and they go down quick into the pit; then ye shall understand that these men have provoked the LORD.
Wolaitta Sentences: SHin GODAI muleera oorattabaa oottin, biittai dooyettidi etanne etau de7iyaabaa ubbaa mitti aggikko, eti paxa de7iiddi Si7ooliyaa duge wodhdhikko, he wode ha asati GODAA karidoogaa intte erana" yaagiis.

English Sentences: And it came to pass, as he had made an end of speaking all these words, that the ground clave asunder that was under them:
Wolaitta Sentences: I yaagidi wurssido sohuwaarakka, eti eqqido biittai phalqqetti wodhdhiis.

English Sentences: And the earth opened her mouth, and swallowed them up, and their houses, and all the men that appertained unto Korah, and all their goods.
Wolaitta Sentences: Biittai dooyettidi, etanne eta so asaa, Qoraaha citaa ubbaa etassi de7iyaaba ubbaara mitti bayiis.

English Sentences: They, and all that appertained to them, went down alive into the pit, and the earth closed upon them: and they perished from among the congregation.
Wolaitta Sentences: Yaatin eti banttau de7iyaabaa ubbaara paxa de7iiddi, Si7ooliyaa duge wodhdhidosona. Biittaikka eta bolli gorddetti bayiis; eti maabaraa giddoppe tippe giidi xayi bayidosona.

English Sentences: And all Israel that were round about them fled at the cry of them: for they said, Lest the earth swallow us up also.
Wolaitta Sentences: Eta waasuwan eta matan de7iya Israa7eelati ubbai, "Biittai nunakka qassi mittana hanees!" yaagiiddi baqatidosona.

English Sentences: And there came out a fire from the LORD, and consumed the two hundred and fifty men that offered incense.
Wolaitta Sentences: Qassi tamaikka GODAA matappe yiidi, ixaanaa cuwayiya naa77u xeetanne ishatamu asaa mi bayiis.

English Sentences: And the LORD spake unto Moses, saying,
Wolaitta Sentences: Hegaappe guyyiyan GODAI Muusa,

English Sentences: Speak unto Eleazar the son of Aaron the priest, that he take up the censers out of the burning, and scatter thou the fire yonder; for they are hallowed.
Wolaitta Sentences: "Neeni qeesiyaa Aaroona na7aa El77aazarassi yaagada yoota, Ixaanaa cuwayiyoobata taman xuugettida asaa giddoppe ekka; bonqquwaa cuwayiyoobatuppe haassada laala. He ixaanaa cuwayiyoobati geeshsha.

English Sentences: The censers of these sinners against their own souls, let them make them broad plates for a covering of the altar: for they offered them before the LORD, therefore they are hallowed: and they shall be a sign unto the children of Israel.
Wolaitta Sentences: Bantta nagaraa gishshau haiqqida ha asatu ixaanaa cuwayiyoobata lee7issada qoxxada, yarshshuwaa saaxiniyaa kamma. Eti hegeeta GODAA sinttan shiishshido gishshau, hegeeti geeshsha; hegeeti Israa7eelata hassayissiya malaata gidana yaaga" yaagiis.

English Sentences: And Eleazar the priest took the brasen censers, wherewith they that were burnt had offered; and they were made broad plates for a covering of the altar:
Wolaitta Sentences: Yaagin qeesee El77aazari xuugettida asati shiishshido nahaase birataappe oosettida ixaanaa cuwayiyoobata ekkidi, yarshshuwaa saaxiniyaa kammanau lee7issidi qoxxiis.

English Sentences: To be a memorial unto the children of Israel, that no stranger, which is not of the seed of Aaron, come near to offer incense before the LORD; that he be not as Korah, and as his company: as the LORD said to him by the hand of Moses.
Wolaitta Sentences: Aaroona zare gidenna ooninne GODAA sinttan ixaanaa cuwayanau shiiqenna mala, Qoraahanne a citaa gakkidaagee a gakkenna mala, Israa7eelata hassayissanau hageeta oottiis. GODAI Muuse baggaara El77aazara azazidoogaadan hagee haniis.

English Sentences: But on the morrow all the congregation of the children of Israel murmured against Moses and against Aaron, saying, Ye have killed the people of the LORD.
Wolaitta Sentences: Wonttetta gallassi Israa7eela maabarai ubbai, "GODAA asaa intte worideta" yaagidi, Muuse bollinne Aaroona bolli zuuzummidosona.

English Sentences: And it came to pass, when the congregation was gathered against Moses and against Aaron, that they looked toward the tabernacle of the congregation: and, behold, the cloud covered it, and the glory of the LORD appeared.
Wolaitta Sentences: Maabarai Muusenne Aaroona bolli denddanau shiiqidi, Xoossaa Dunkkaaniyaakko simmi xeelliyo wode, shaarai Xoossaa Dunkkaaniyaa kammin, GODAA bonchchoi qoncciis.

English Sentences: And Moses and Aaron came before the tabernacle of the congregation.
Wolaitta Sentences: Hegaappe guyyiyan, Muuseenne Aarooni Xoossaa Dunkkaaniyaa sinttau yiidosona.

English Sentences: And the LORD spake unto Moses, saying,
Wolaitta Sentences: Yin GODAI Muusa,

English Sentences: Get you up from among this congregation, that I may consume them as in a moment. And they fell upon their faces.
Wolaitta Sentences: "Ha asaa gidduwaappe kichchite; taani eta issi kuttan xaissa bayana" yaagiis. Yaagin eti sa7an gufannidosona.

English Sentences: And Moses said unto Aaron, Take a censer, and put fire therein from off the altar, and put on incense, and go quickly unto the congregation, and make an atonement for them: for there is wrath gone out from the LORD; the plague is begun.
Wolaitta Sentences: Muusee Aaroona, "Ne ixaanaa cuwayiyoogaa ekkada, bonqquwaa yarshshiyoosaappe ekkada, ixaanaa an wotta; wottada etayyo atto giissanau eesuwan maabaraakko efa. Aissi giikko, GODAA hanqqoi a matappe kiyiichchiis; boshaikka doommiichchiis" yaagiis.

English Sentences: And Aaron took as Moses commanded, and ran into the midst of the congregation; and, behold, the plague was begun among the people: and he put on incense, and made an atonement for the people.
Wolaitta Sentences: Yaagin Muusee giidoogaadan Aarooni ba ixaanaa cuwayiyoogaa ekkidi, maabaraa giddo woxxiis. Boshai asaa gidduwan doommidaashin, Aarooni ixaanaa cuwayidi, asaayyo atto giissiis.

English Sentences: And he stood between the dead and the living; and the plague was stayed.
Wolaitta Sentences: Yaatidi i haiqqidaageetuppenne paxa de7iyaageetuppe gidduwan eqqin, boshai aggi bayiis.

English Sentences: Now they that died in the plague were fourteen thousand and seven hundred, beside them that died about the matter of Korah.
Wolaitta Sentences: Qoraaha gaasuwan haiqqida asai qoodettennan, ha boshan haiqqidaageeti 14,700.

English Sentences: And Aaron returned unto Moses unto the door of the tabernacle of the congregation: and the plague was stayed.
Wolaitta Sentences: Boshai eqqidoogaappe guyyiyan, Aarooni Xoossaa Dunkkaaniyaa penggen de7iya Muusekko simmiis.

English Sentences: And the LORD spake unto Moses, saying,
Wolaitta Sentences: GODAI Muusa hagaadan yaagiis;

English Sentences: Speak unto the children of Israel, and take of every one of them a rod according to the house of their fathers, of all their princes according to the house of their fathers twelve rods: write thou every man's name upon his rod.
Wolaitta Sentences: "Neeni, Intte zariyan zariyan intte halaqatuppe huuphiyan huuphiyan issi issi xam77aa muleera tammanne naa77u xam77aa tau immite yaagada Israa7eelatuppe ekka. Issi issi asaa sunttaa xam77aa bollan xaafa.

English Sentences: And thou shalt write Aaron's name upon the rod of Levi: for one rod shall be for the head of the house of their fathers.
Wolaitta Sentences: Issi issi zariyaa halaqaassi issi xam77a gidiyo gishshau, Leewa xam77an Aaroona sunttaa xaafa.

English Sentences: And thou shalt lay them up in the tabernacle of the congregation before the testimony, where I will meet with you.
Wolaitta Sentences: Xaafada Xoossaa Dunkkaaniyaa giddon taani nenaara gaittiyo Taabootaa sinttan wotta.

English Sentences: And it shall come to pass, that the man's rod, whom I shall choose, shall blossom: and I will make to cease from me the murmurings of the children of Israel, whereby they murmur against you.
Wolaitta Sentences: Taani dooriyo asa xam77ai aacana; hagaadan oottada intte bollan Israa7eelati zuuzummiyo zuuzunttaa taani mule xaissana" yaagiis.

English Sentences: And Moses spake unto the children of Israel, and every one of their princes gave him a rod apiece, for each prince one, according to their fathers' houses, even twelve rods: and the rod of Aaron was among their rods.
Wolaitta Sentences: Yaagin Muusee Israa7eela asau yootin, eta halaqati tammanne naa77u xam77ata, issi issi zariyaa halaqati issi issi xam77aa ayyo immidosona. He xam77atu gidduwan Aaroona xam77aikka de7ees.

English Sentences: And Moses laid up the rods before the LORD in the tabernacle of witness.
Wolaitta Sentences: Muusee he xam77aa ubbaa Xoossaa Dunkkaaniyaa giddon GODAA sinttan wottiis.

English Sentences: And it came to pass, that on the morrow Moses went into the tabernacle of witness; and, behold, the rod of Aaron for the house of Levi was budded, and brought forth buds, and bloomed blossoms, and yielded almonds.
Wolaitta Sentences: Wonttetta gallassi Xoossaa Dunkkaaniyaa giddo Muusee gelido wode, Leewa zare gidiya Aaroona xam77ai aacidaagaa, gumbbidaagaa, ciiyyidaagaanne ciiyidi lauziyaa giyo mitta aifiyaa aifidaagaa be7iis.

English Sentences: And Moses brought out all the rods from before the LORD unto all the children of Israel: and they looked, and took every man his rod.
Wolaitta Sentences: Hegaappe guyyiyan, Muusee xam77a ubbaa GODAA sinttappe Israa7eela asaa ubbaakko ehiis. Ehin asai eta be7idoogaappe guyyiyan, halaqati bantta xam77aa xam77aa ekkidosona.

English Sentences: And the LORD said unto Moses, Bring Aaron's rod again before the testimony, to be kept for a token against the rebels; and thou shalt quite take away their murmurings from me, that they die not.
Wolaitta Sentences: GODAI Muusa, "Aaroona xam77aa Taabootaa sinttan zaara wotta. Hegaa makkalidaageeti ta bolli naa77antto zuuzummidi haiqqennaadan, etau malaata oottada naaga" yaagiis.

English Sentences: And Moses did so: as the LORD commanded him, so did he.
Wolaitta Sentences: Yaagin GODAI azazidoogaadan Muusee oottiis.

English Sentences: And the children of Israel spake unto Moses, saying, Behold, we die, we perish, we all perish.
Wolaitta Sentences: Israa7eela asai Muusa, "Nuuni haiqqana; xayana; nuuni ubbaikka xayana!

English Sentences: Whosoever cometh any thing near unto the tabernacle of the LORD shall die: shall we be consumed with dying?
Wolaitta Sentences: Xoossaa Dunkkaaniyaakko, harai atto mataa shiiqiya uri ooninne haiqqana. Simmi nuuni ubbaikka haiqqiyoo?" yaagidosona.

English Sentences: And the LORD said unto Aaron, Thou and thy sons and thy father's house with thee shall bear the iniquity of the sanctuary: and thou and thy sons with thee shall bear the iniquity of your priesthood.
Wolaitta Sentences: GODAI Aaroona, "Neeni, ne attuma naatinne Leewati geeshsha sohuwaa oosuwan polettiya nagaraa tookkana; neeninne ne attuma naatu xalaalai intte qeesetettaa oosuwan polettiya nagaraa tookkana.

English Sentences: And thy brethren also of the tribe of Levi, the tribe of thy father, bring thou with thee, that they may be joined unto thee, and minister unto thee: but thou and thy sons with thee shall minister before the tabernacle of witness.
Wolaitta Sentences: Neeninne ne attuma naati Xoossaa Dunkkaaniyaa sinttan oottiyo wode, nenaara oottidi maaddana mala, Leewa zare gidiya ne dabbota eha.

English Sentences: And they shall keep thy charge, and the charge of all the tabernacle: only they shall not come nigh the vessels of the sanctuary and the altar, that neither they, nor ye also, die.
Wolaitta Sentences: Eti intteppe garssaara Xoossaa Dunkkaaniyaa ooso ubbaa oottona; shin etikka inttekka issippe haiqqennaadan, eti geeshsha sohuwaa miishshaakkonne yarshshiyoosaakko shiiqoppona.

English Sentences: And they shall be joined unto thee, and keep the charge of the tabernacle of the congregation, for all the service of the tabernacle: and a stranger shall not come nigh unto you.
Wolaitta Sentences: Eti inttenaara issippe gidona; Xoossaa Dunkkaaniyan de7iya ooso ubbaa oottona. Leewatuppe attin, hara uri ooninne inttekko shiiqoppo.

English Sentences: And ye shall keep the charge of the sanctuary, and the charge of the altar: that there be no wrath any more upon the children of Israel.
Wolaitta Sentences: Naa77anttuwaa Israa7eelatu bolli hanqqoi wodhdhenna mala, geeshsha sohuwaanne yarshshiyoosaa oosuwaa oottite.

English Sentences: And I, behold, I have taken your brethren the Levites from among the children of Israel: to you they are given as a gift for the LORD, to do the service of the tabernacle of the congregation.
Wolaitta Sentences: Leewata intte dabbota Israa7eelatu giddoppe taani ta huuphen dooraas. Eti Xoossaa Dunkkaaniyaa oosuwaa oottanau intteyyo imodan immada, GODAU dummayaas.

English Sentences: Therefore thou and thy sons with thee shall keep your priest's office for everything of the altar, and within the vail; and ye shall serve: I have given your priest's office unto you as a service of gift: and the stranger that cometh nigh shall be put to death.
Wolaitta Sentences: SHin neeninne ne attuma naatu xalaalai yarshshiyoosaa oosuwaa ubbaanne magalashuwaa giddon de7iya qeesetetta ooso ubbaa oottite. Qeesetettaa oosuwaa taani intteyyo imodan oottada immais; hara uri ooninne geeshsha sohuwaakko shiiqiyaabi haiqqo" yaagiis.

English Sentences: And the LORD spake unto Aaron, Behold, I also have given thee the charge of mine heave offerings of all the hallowed things of the children of Israel; unto thee have I given them by reason of the anointing, and to thy sons, by an ordinance for ever.
Wolaitta Sentences: Hegaappe guyyiyan GODAI Aaroona, "Israa7eelati taayyo immiyo geeshsha imota ubbaa taani neeyyo immaas. Taani neeyyo ne gishshaanne ne attuma naatuyyo eta gishshaa merinau gishsha oottada immaas.

English Sentences: This shall be thine of the most holy things, reserved from the fire: every oblation of theirs, every meat offering of theirs, and every sin offering of theirs, and every trespass offering of theirs which they shall render unto me, shall be most holy for thee and for thy sons.
Wolaitta Sentences: Taayyo immiyo aadhdhida geeshsha imuwaappe taman xuugettenna baggai inttessa gidana: eti taassi immiyo geeshsha imuwaa ubbaappe kattaa yarshshoi, woikko nagaraa gishshau yarshshiyo yarshshoi, woikko naaquwaa gishshau yarshshiyo yarshshoi neessanne ne attuma naatussa gidana.

English Sentences: In the most holy place shalt thou eat it; every male shall eat it: it shall be holy unto thee.
Wolaitta Sentences: Intte hegaa geeshsha sohuwan miite; attumaagee ubbai hegaa mo; hegee inttessi geeshsha gidana.

English Sentences: And this is thine; the heave offering of their gift, with all the wave offerings of the children of Israel: I have given them unto thee, and to thy sons and to thy daughters with thee, by a statute for ever: every one that is clean in thy house shall eat of it.
Wolaitta Sentences: "Hagee qassi neessa. Israa7eelatu wuxaawuxo yarshsho ubbaa neeyyo, ne attuma naatuyyoonne ne macca naatuyyo merinau gishsha oottada immais; intte keettaa asaa giddon wogaadan geeshsha gidiya ubbai hegaa mo.

English Sentences: All the best of the oil, and all the best of the wine, and of the wheat, the firstfruits of them which they shall offer unto the LORD, them have I given thee.
Wolaitta Sentences: "Eti taayyo immiyo koiro aifiyaappe lo77o wogaraa zaitiyaa ubbaa, yelaga woine eessaa ubbaanne muruta kattaa ubbaa neeyyo immais.

English Sentences: And whatsoever is first ripe in the land, which they shall bring unto the LORD, shall be thine; every one that is clean in thine house shall eat of it.
Wolaitta Sentences: Eti GODAAYYO ehiyo eta biittan de7iya koiro gakkida aifee inttessa; intte keettaa asaa giddon wogaadan geeshsha gidiya ubbai hegaa mo.

English Sentences: Every thing devoted in Israel shall be thine.
Wolaitta Sentences: "Israa7eelan GODAAYYO dummatidabai ubbai inttessa.

English Sentences: Every thing that openeth the matrix in all flesh, which they bring unto the LORD, whether it be of men or beasts, shall be thine: nevertheless the firstborn of man shalt thou surely redeem, and the firstling of unclean beasts shalt thou redeem.
Wolaitta Sentences: Baira yelettida asi woikko mehee, Israa7eelati GODAAYYO immidobi inttessa. SHin baira yelettida asanne baira yelettida geeshsha gidenna mehe intte wozanau bessees.

English Sentences: And those that are to be redeemed from a month old shalt thou redeem, according to thine estimation, for the money of five shekels, after the shekel of the sanctuary, which is twenty gerahs.
Wolaitta Sentences: Issi agina naata wozanau Xoossaa Dunkkaaniyan eriyo meezaanaa likkiyan ichchashu xaqara biraa wozo waagaa qanxxite.

English Sentences: But the firstling of a cow, or the firstling of a sheep, or the firstling of a goat, thou shalt not redeem; they are holy: thou shalt sprinkle their blood upon the altar, and shalt burn their fat for an offering made by fire, for a sweet savour unto the LORD.
Wolaitta Sentences: SHin miizzaa bairaa, woikko dorssaa bairaa, woikko deeshshaa bairaa intte wozanau koshshenna; eti geeshsha. Neeni eta suuttaa yarshshiyoosaa bollan caccafa; GODAA tonggu giidi sawana mala, eta modhdhuwaa taman xuugga.

English Sentences: And the flesh of them shall be thine, as the wave breast and as the right shoulder are thine.
Wolaitta Sentences: Etappe beettiya ashoi wuxaawuxido anggaasuwaadaaninne ushachcha gedaadan inttessa.

English Sentences: All the heave offerings of the holy things, which the children of Israel offer unto the LORD, have I given thee, and thy sons and thy daughters with thee, by a statute for ever: it is a covenant of salt for ever before the LORD unto thee and to thy seed with thee.
Wolaitta Sentences: Israa7eelati GODAAYYO immiyo geeshsha yarshsho ubbaa neessi, ne attuma naatussinne ne macca naatussi merinau gishsha oottada immais. Hageekka taani nenaaranne ne zerettatuura maacettiyo merinaa maachcha" yaagiis.

English Sentences: And the LORD spake unto Aaron, Thou shalt have no inheritance in their land, neither shalt thou have any part among them: I am thy part and thine inheritance among the children of Israel.
Wolaitta Sentences: Qassikka GODAI Aaroona, "Eta biittan neeni ainne laattakka; eta giddon nena gakkiya shaahoi aibikka baawa; Israa7eelatu giddon ne laatainne nena gakkiya shaahoi tana" yaagiis.

English Sentences: And, behold, I have given the children of Levi all the tenth in Israel for an inheritance, for their service which they serve, even the service of the tabernacle of the congregation.
Wolaitta Sentences: GODAI, "Leewati Xoossaa Dunkkaaniyan oottiyo oosuwaa gishshau, Israa7eelatu asirata ubbaa etayyo immaas.

English Sentences: Neither must the children of Israel henceforth come nigh the tabernacle of the congregation, lest they bear sin, and die.
Wolaitta Sentences: Hachchippe doommidi, Israa7eela asati bantta nagaran haiqqenna mala, Xoossaa Dunkkaaniyaakko shiiqoppona.

English Sentences: But the Levites shall do the service of the tabernacle of the congregation, and they shall bear their iniquity: it shall be a statute for ever throughout your generations, that among the children of Israel they have no inheritance.
Wolaitta Sentences: Xoossaa Dunkkaaniyaa oosuwaa oottiyaageetinne hegan polettiya nagaraa tookkiyaageeti Leewata. Hagee yeleta ubbau merinaa wogaa. Leewati Israa7eela asaa gidduwan ainne laattokkona.

English Sentences: But the tithes of the children of Israel, which they offer as an heave offering unto the LORD, I have given to the Levites to inherit: therefore I have said unto them, Among the children of Israel they shall have no inheritance.
Wolaitta Sentences: Hegaa gishshaa, Israa7eelati GODAAYYO imodan immiyo asirataa, taani Leewatuyyo eta laatadan immaas. Taani etabaa, Eti Israa7eela asaa gidduwan ainne laattokkona yaagidoogee hegaassa" yaagiis.

English Sentences: And the LORD spake unto Moses, saying,
Wolaitta Sentences: Qassi GODAI Muusa,

English Sentences: Thus speak unto the Levites, and say unto them, When ye take of the children of Israel the tithes which I have given you from them for your inheritance, then ye shall offer up an heave offering of it for the LORD, even a tenth part of the tithe.
Wolaitta Sentences: "Neeni Leewata hagaadan yaaga; Taani intteyyo laatadan immido asirataa intte Israa7eela asaappe ekkiyo wode, intte he asirataappe asirataa GODAAYYO immite.

English Sentences: And this your heave offering shall be reckoned unto you, as though it were the corn of the threshingfloor, and as the fulness of the winepress.
Wolaitta Sentences: Intte imoi intteyyo kattaa qoxxiyo audiyaa kattaadaaninne gum77iyo woine aifiyaadan qoodettees.

English Sentences: Thus ye also shall offer an heave offering unto the LORD of all your tithes, which ye receive of the children of Israel; and ye shall give thereof the LORD's heave offering to Aaron the priest.
Wolaitta Sentences: Qassi hagaadan Israa7eela asaappe intte ekkiyo asirata ubbaappe imuwaa GODAAYYO immite; ha asirataappe GODAA gishshaa qeesiyaa Aaroonayyo intte immanau bessees.

English Sentences: Out of all your gifts ye shall offer every heave offering of the LORD, of all the best thereof, even the hallowed part thereof out of it.
Wolaitta Sentences: Intte ekkiyo imota ubbaappe, lo77iyaagaanne geeshshaa GODAASSI gishsha oottidi, intte immanau bessees yaaga.

English Sentences: Therefore thou shalt say unto them, When ye have heaved the best thereof from it, then it shall be counted unto the Levites as the increase of the threshingfloor, and as the increase of the winepress.
Wolaitta Sentences: neeni Leewata, Ubbaappe lo77o imuwaa intte immidoogaappe guyyiyan, attidaagee intteyyo kattaa qoxxiyo audiyaa kattaadaaninne gum77iyo woiniyaa aifiyaadan qoodettana.

English Sentences: And ye shall eat it in every place, ye and your households: for it is your reward for your service in the tabernacle of the congregation.
Wolaitta Sentences: Inttenne intte keettaa asai hegaappe attidaagaa awaaninne miite; aissi giikko, hegee Xoossaa Dunkkaaniyan intte oottiyo oosuwaayyo intte damoozaa.

English Sentences: And ye shall bear no sin by reason of it, when ye have heaved from it the best of it: neither shall ye pollute the holy things of the children of Israel, lest ye die.
Wolaitta Sentences: Lo77o baggaa GODAASSI immirggidoogaappe guyyiyan intte miyo wode, mooranchcha gidekketa. SHin lo77o baggaa he imotaappe kessennan de7iiddi, he imotaappe miidi, intte Israa7eela asaa imotaa tunissennaadan naagettite. Hegaadan oottana xayikko, intte haiqqana yaaga" yaagiis.

English Sentences: And the LORD spake unto Moses and unto Aaron, saying,
Wolaitta Sentences: GODAI Muusanne Aaroona hagaadan yaagiis;

English Sentences: This is the ordinance of the law which the LORD hath commanded, saying, Speak unto the children of Israel, that they bring thee a red heifer without spot, wherein is no blemish, and upon which never came yoke:
Wolaitta Sentences: "GODAI higgiyan azazido wogai hagaa: Tilla bollaara de7iya woikko borssoi bainna, i morggiyan qambbari wodhdhibeenna zo7o ussiyo neeyyo ehaana mala, Israa7eela asaayyo yootite.

English Sentences: And ye shall give her unto Eleazar the priest, that he may bring her forth without the camp, and one shall slay her before his face:
Wolaitta Sentences: Qeesiyaa El77aazarayyo o immite; i o dunkkaanidosaappe gaxi efin, issi asi o a sinttan shukko.

English Sentences: And Eleazar the priest shall take of her blood with his finger, and sprinkle of her blood directly before the tabernacle of the congregation seven times:
Wolaitta Sentences: Qeesiyaa El77aazari i suuttaappe amaridaagaa ba biradhdhiyan ekkidi, Xoossaa Dunkkaaniyaayyo sintta baggaara laapputtoo caccafo.

English Sentences: And one shall burn the heifer in his sight; her skin, and her flesh, and her blood, with her dung, shall he burn:
Wolaitta Sentences: I xeellishin ussiyaa xuugettu; i galbbai, ashoi, suuttainne tocee xuugetto.

English Sentences: And the priest shall take cedar wood, and hyssop, and scarlet, and cast it into the midst of the burning of the heifer.
Wolaitta Sentences: Qeesee zigaa, hiisoophphiyaa tashiyaanne zo7o qunccuutiyaa ekkidi, ussiyo xuuggiyo taman olo.

English Sentences: Then the priest shall wash his clothes, and he shall bathe his flesh in water, and afterward he shall come into the camp, and the priest shall be unclean until the even.
Wolaitta Sentences: Hegaappe guyyiyan, qeesee ba maayuwaa meecco; ba bollaakka haattan meecetto; meecettidi dunkkaanidosaa gelo; shin omarssa gakkanaassi i wogaadan tuna gidana.

English Sentences: And he that burneth her shall wash his clothes in water, and bathe his flesh in water, and shall be unclean until the even.
Wolaitta Sentences: He ussiyo xuuggidaagee qassi ba maayuwaa meecco; ba bollaakka haattan meecetto; ikka qassi omarssa gakkanaassi wogaadan tuna gidana.

English Sentences: And a man that is clean shall gather up the ashes of the heifer, and lay them up without the camp in a clean place, and it shall be kept for the congregation of the children of Israel for a water of separation: it is a purification for sin.
Wolaitta Sentences: "Hegaappe guyyiyan, geeshsha asi ussiyaa xuugettido bidinttaa shiishshidi, dunkkaanidosaappe gaxaara geeshsha sohuwan wotto. Israa7eela asai tunatettaappe geeyiyo haattan go7ettanau hegaa naagi wottana; hegee nagaraappe geeshshanaassa.

English Sentences: And he that gathereth the ashes of the heifer shall wash his clothes, and be unclean until the even: and it shall be unto the children of Israel, and unto the stranger that sojourneth among them, for a statute for ever.
Wolaitta Sentences: Qassi ussee bidinttaa shiishshida asi ba maayuwaa meecco; omarssi gakkanaassi i wogaadan tuna gidana. Ha wogai Israa7eela asaunne eta gidduwan de7iya hara dere asau naa77aukka merinaa woga gidana.

English Sentences: He that toucheth the dead body of any man shall be unclean seven days.
Wolaitta Sentences: "Haiqqida asa ahaa bochchiya ooninne laappun gallassaa wogaadan tunana.

English Sentences: He shall purify himself with it on the third day, and on the seventh day he shall be clean: but if he purify not himself the third day, then the seventh day he shall not be clean.
Wolaitta Sentences: He tunatettaappe geeyiyo haattan heezzantta gallassinne laappuntta gallassi, i bana geeshsho; hegaappe guyyiyan, i wogaadan geeshsha gidana; shin heezzantta gallassaaninne laappuntta gallassan bana geeshshana xayikko, i geeshsha gidenna.

English Sentences: Whosoever toucheth the dead body of any man that is dead, and purifieth not himself, defileth the tabernacle of the LORD; and that soul shall be cut off from Israel: because the water of separation was not sprinkled upon him, he shall be unclean; his uncleanness is yet upon him.
Wolaitta Sentences: Haiqqida uraa ahaa bochchiya ooninne bana geeshshennan aggikko, GODAA Dunkkaaniyaa i tunissees; he urai Israa7eela asaa giddoppe bohetto. Tunatettaappe geeyiyo haattai a bollan caccafettibeenna gishshau, i tuna; a tunatettai a bollan gam77ees.

English Sentences: This is the law, when a man dieth in a tent: all that come into the tent, and all that is in the tent, shall be unclean seven days.
Wolaitta Sentences: "Issi uri dunkkaaniyaa giddon haiqqikko de7iya wogai hagaa: dunkkaaniyaa giddo geliya ooninne, qassi dunkkaaniyaa giddon de7iya ubbaikka laappun gallassaa tuna gidana.

English Sentences: And every open vessel, which hath no covering bound upon it, is unclean.
Wolaitta Sentences: Hegaadankka, qum77ettennan dooya de7iya miishsha ubbai tuna gidana.

English Sentences: And whosoever toucheth one that is slain with a sword in the open fields, or a dead body, or a bone of a man, or a grave, shall be unclean seven days.
Wolaitta Sentences: Qassi dembban bisuwan haiqqida asa, woikko coo haiqqida ahaa, woikko asa meqetta, woikko duufuwaa bochchiya ooninne laappun gallassaa tuna gidana.

English Sentences: And for an unclean person they shall take of the ashes of the burnt heifer of purification for sin, and running water shall be put thereto in a vessel:
Wolaitta Sentences: "Tunatettaappe geeshshanau xuuggido ussee bidinttaappe amaridaagaa ekkada, otuwan wottada, pultto haattaa an tiga;

English Sentences: And a clean person shall take hyssop, and dip it in the water, and sprinkle it upon the tent, and upon all the vessels, and upon the persons that were there, and upon him that touched a bone, or one slain, or one dead, or a grave:
Wolaitta Sentences: tigin geeshsha asi hiisoophphiyaa bonccuwaa ekkidi, haattan naaqqi kessidi, dunkkaaniyaa, dunkkaaniyan de7iya miishshaa ubbaaninne hegan de7iya asaa ubbaa bollan caccafo. Qassi asa meqettaa, woikko duufuwaa, woikko worido uraa, woikko haiqqida uraa bochchida asa o bollinne i caccafo.

English Sentences: And the clean person shall sprinkle upon the unclean on the third day, and on the seventh day: and on the seventh day he shall purify himself, and wash his clothes, and bathe himself in water, and shall be clean at even.
Wolaitta Sentences: Geeshsha asi heezzanttanne laappuntta gallassan tunida uraa bollan caccafo. I laappuntta gallassan he uraa tunatettaappe geeshsho; he geeyida bitanee ba maayuwaa meecco; ba bollaakka haattan meecetto; he gallassa omarssi i geeshsha gidana.

English Sentences: But the man that shall be unclean, and shall not purify himself, that soul shall be cut off from among the congregation, because he hath defiled the sanctuary of the LORD: the water of separation hath not been sprinkled upon him; he is unclean.
Wolaitta Sentences: "SHin tuna uri bana geeshshennabaa gidikko, he uri GODAA geeshsha sohuwaa tunissido gishshau, Israa7eela asaa giddoppe bohetto; tunatettaappe geeyiyo haattai a bollan caccafettibeenna gishshau, i tuna.

English Sentences: And it shall be a perpetual statute unto them, that he that sprinkleth the water of separation shall wash his clothes; and he that toucheth the water of separation shall be unclean until even.
Wolaitta Sentences: Hagee intteyyo merinaa woga gidana. Qassi tunatettaappe geeyiyo haattaa caccafiya asi ba maayuwaa meecco; tunatettaappe geeyiyo haattaa bochchiya ooninnekka omarssi gakkanaassi tuna gidana.

English Sentences: And whatsoever the unclean person toucheth shall be unclean; and the soul that toucheth it shall be unclean until even.
Wolaitta Sentences: Tuna uri bochchiyo aibinne tunees. Qassi hegaa bochchiya ooninne omarssa gakkanaassi tuna gidees" yaagiis.

English Sentences: Then came the children of Israel, even the whole congregation, into the desert of Zin in the first month: and the people abode in Kadesh; and Miriam died there, and was buried there.
Wolaitta Sentences: Koiro aginan Israa7eelati ubbai Xiina giyo bazzuwaa gakkidi, Qaadeesa giyoosan dunkkaanidosona. Hegan Miiriyaama haiqqada moogettaasu.

English Sentences: And there was no water for the congregation: and they gathered themselves together against Moses and against Aaron.
Wolaitta Sentences: Hegan asaayyo haatti xayin, asai shiiqidi, Muuse bollinne Aaroona bolli denddiis.

English Sentences: And the people chode with Moses, and spake, saying, Would God that we had died when our brethren died before the LORD!
Wolaitta Sentences: Eti, "Nu ishantti GODAA sinttan haiqqido wode, nuunikka haiqqidabaa gidorkkoniishsha!

English Sentences: And why have ye brought up the congregation of the LORD into this wilderness, that we and our cattle should die there?
Wolaitta Sentences: Nuuninne nu mehee ha bazzuwan haiqqanaadan, GODAA asaa hagau intte aissi ehiidetii?

English Sentences: And wherefore have ye made us to come up out of Egypt, to bring us in unto this evil place? it is no place of seed, or of figs, or of vines, or of pomegranates; neither is there any water to drink.
Wolaitta Sentences: Ha hanttaara sohuwaa nuna Gibxxeppe pude aissi ehiidetii? Hagan katta aifee, woikko balasee, woikko woine aifee, woikko roomaanee baawa; qassi uyiyo haattikka hagan baawa" yaagidi Muuseera ooyettidosona.

English Sentences: And Moses and Aaron went from the presence of the assembly unto the door of the tabernacle of the congregation, and they fell upon their faces: and the glory of the LORD appeared unto them.
Wolaitta Sentences: Yaatin Muuseenne Aarooni asaa matappe Xoossaa Dunkkaaniyaa pengge biidi gufannidosona; gufannin GODAA bonchchoi etayyo qoncciis.

English Sentences: And the LORD spake unto Moses, saying,
Wolaitta Sentences: GODAI Muusa,

English Sentences: Take the rod, and gather thou the assembly together, thou, and Aaron thy brother, and speak ye unto the rock before their eyes; and it shall give forth his water, and thou shalt bring forth to them water out of the rock: so thou shalt give the congregation and their beasts drink.
Wolaitta Sentences: "Ne gatimaa ekka; neeninne ne ishaa Aarooni yaa7aa shiishshite; shiiqin eta sinttan zaallai haattaa goggana mala yoota. Zaallaappe haattaa intte kessidi, yaa7aanne eta mehiyaa ushshana" yaagiis.

English Sentences: And Moses took the rod from before the LORD, as he commanded him.
Wolaitta Sentences: GODAI azazidoogaadan, Muusee GODAA sinttappe gatimaa ekkiis.

English Sentences: And Moses and Aaron gathered the congregation together before the rock, and he said unto them, Hear now, ye rebels; must we fetch you water out of this rock?
Wolaitta Sentences: Inne Aarooni yaa7aa zaallaa sinttan shiishshidosona; shiishshin Muusee eta, "Inttenoo makkalanchchatoo, siyite; ha zaallaappe haattaa intteyyo nuuni tumu kessanee?" yaagiis.

English Sentences: And Moses lifted up his hand, and with his rod he smote the rock twice: and the water came out abundantly, and the congregation drank, and their beasts also.
Wolaitta Sentences: Yaagidi Muusee ba kushiyaa xoqqu oottidi, ba gatiman naa77utoo zaallaa shocin, haattai xuuqqidi kiyiis; kiyin yaa7ainne eta mehee uyiis.

English Sentences: And the LORD spake unto Moses and Aaron, Because ye believed me not, to sanctify me in the eyes of the children of Israel, therefore ye shall not bring this congregation into the land which I have given them.
Wolaitta Sentences: SHin GODAI Muusanne Aaroona, "Israa7eela asaa sinttan intte ta geeshshatettaa bessanau ammanettibeenna gishshau, taani etayyo immiyo biittaa ha asaa intte gelissekketa" yaagiis.

English Sentences: This is the water of Meribah; because the children of Israel strove with the LORD, and he was sanctified in them.
Wolaitta Sentences: Israa7eela asai GODAARA ooyettidonne i ba geeshshatettaa eta giddon qonccissidosai ha Mariiba haattaana.

English Sentences: And Moses sent messengers from Kadesh unto the king of Edom, Thus saith thy brother Israel, Thou knowest all the travail that hath befallen us:
Wolaitta Sentences: Muusee Qaadeesappe Eedooma biittaa kawuwaakko, ba kiitettiyaageeta hagaadan yaagidi kiittiis; "Ne dabbo gidiya Israa7eela asai hagaadan yaagees; Nuna gakkida meto ubbaa neeni eraasa.

English Sentences: How our fathers went down into Egypt, and we have dwelt in Egypt a long time; and the Egyptians vexed us, and our fathers:
Wolaitta Sentences: Nu maizza aawati duge Gibxxe wodhdhidosona; yan nuuni daro laittaa de7ida. Gibxxeti nunanne nu aawata huqqunnidosona.

English Sentences: And when we cried unto the LORD, he heard our voice, and sent an angel, and hath brought us forth out of Egypt: and, behold, we are in Kadesh, a city in the uttermost of thy border:
Wolaitta Sentences: Huqqunnin nuuni GODAASSI waassin, nu waasuwaa siyidi, kiitanchchaa kiittidi, nuna Gibxxeppe kessiis. Ha77i nuuni ne biittaa gaxan de7iya Qaadeesa kataman de7oos.

English Sentences: Let us pass, I pray thee, through thy country: we will not pass through the fields, or through the vineyards, neither will we drink of the water of the wells: we will go by the king's high way, we will not turn to the right hand nor to the left, until we have passed thy borders.
Wolaitta Sentences: Hayyanaa, nuna ne biittaara kanttissarkkii! Nuuni ai gade giddoorakka woikko woine turaa giddoorakka kanttokko! Qassi nuuni ai haatta ollappenne haattaa uyokko. Nuuni Kawo Ogiyaa oiqqidi baana; nuuni ne biittaara kanttana gakkanaassi, haddirssi woikko ushachchi gookko yaagees" yaagiis.

English Sentences: And Edom said unto him, Thou shalt not pass by me, lest I come out against thee with the sword.
Wolaitta Sentences: SHin Eedooma kawoi, "Nu biittaara kanttissikke; intte hagaara kanttana kajjeelikko, nuuni denddidi inttena bisuwan olana" yaagidosona.

English Sentences: And the children of Israel said unto him, We will go by the high way: and if I and my cattle drink of thy water, then I will pay for it: I will only, without doing anything else, go through on my feet.
Wolaitta Sentences: Yaagin Israa7eelati a, "Nuuni Kawo Ogiyaara baana; nuuni woikko nu mehee intte haattaa uyikko, nuuni hegaayyo waagaa qanxxana. Nuuni tohuwan aaretta xalaalaa koyoos; harabaa aibanne koyokko" yaagidosona.

English Sentences: And he said, Thou shalt not go through. And Edom came out against him with much people, and with a strong hand.
Wolaitta Sentences: Eedooma kawoi zaarettidi, "Inttena kanttissikke" yaagiis. Hegaappe guyyiyan, daronne wolqqaama olanchchata ekkidi, Israa7eela asaara olaa gaittanau kiyiis.

English Sentences: Thus Edom refused to give Israel passage through his border: wherefore Israel turned away from him.
Wolaitta Sentences: Eedoomati bantta biittaara Israa7eela asai kanttanau diggido gishshau, Israa7eela asai simmidi hara ogiyaa biis.

English Sentences: And the children of Israel, even the whole congregation, journeyed from Kadesh, and came unto mount Hor.
Wolaitta Sentences: Israa7eela asai ubbai Qaadeesappe denddidi, Hoora giyo deriyaa biidosona.

English Sentences: And the LORD spake unto Moses and Aaron in mount Hor, by the coast of the land of Edom, saying,
Wolaitta Sentences: Eedooma zawaa matan de7iya Hoora Deriyan, GODAI Muusanne Aaroona,

English Sentences: Aaron shall be gathered unto his people: for he shall not enter into the land which I have given unto the children of Israel, because ye rebelled against my word at the water of Meribah.
Wolaitta Sentences: "Aarooni haiqqidi ba maizzan gaittiyo wodee gakkiis. Mariiba haattaa matan intte naa77aikka ta azazuwaa bolli makkalido gishshau, Israa7eela asaayyo taani immiyo biittaa i gelenna.

English Sentences: Take Aaron and Eleazar his son, and bring them up unto mount Hor:
Wolaitta Sentences: Aaroonanne a na7aa El77aazara ekkada, Hoora Deriyaa eha.

English Sentences: And strip Aaron of his garments, and put them upon Eleazar his son: and Aaron shall be gathered unto his people, and shall die there.
Wolaitta Sentences: Aaroona maayuwaa qaarada, a na7aa El77aazara maizza. Aarooni ba maizzan gaittana; i yan haiqqana" yaagiis.

English Sentences: And Moses did as the LORD commanded: and they went up into mount Hor in the sight of all the congregation.
Wolaitta Sentences: GODAI azazidoogaadan Muusee oottiis; asai ubbai xeellishin, eti Hoora Deriyaa kiyidosona.

English Sentences: And Moses stripped Aaron of his garments, and put them upon Eleazar his son; and Aaron died there in the top of the mount: and Moses and Eleazar came down from the mount.
Wolaitta Sentences: Kiyin Muusee Aaroona maayuwaa qaaridi, a na7aa El77aazara maizziis. Aarooni he deriyaa huuphiyan haiqqiis. Hegaappe guyyiyan, Muuseenne El77aazari deriyaappe wodhdhidosona.

English Sentences: And when all the congregation saw that Aaron was dead, they mourned for Aaron thirty days, even all the house of Israel.
Wolaitta Sentences: Aarooni haiqqidoogaa asai ubbai erido wode, Israa7eela asai ubbai Aaroonayyo hasttamu gallassaa yeekkiis.

English Sentences: And when king Arad the Canaanite, which dwelt in the south, heard tell that Israel came by the way of the spies; then he fought against Israel, and took some of them prisoners.
Wolaitta Sentences: Neegeeba Bazzuwan, Kanaane biittan de7iya Araada kawoi Israa7eela asai Ataarima efiya ogiyaa baggaara yiyoogaa siyido wode, i Israa7eelatuura olaa gaittidi, etappe amaridaageeta omooddiis.

English Sentences: And Israel vowed a vow unto the LORD, and said, If thou wilt indeed deliver this people into my hand, then I will utterly destroy their cities.
Wolaitta Sentences: He wode Israa7eela asai, "Neeni ha asaa nu kushiyan aattada immikko, nuuni eta katamata muleera xaissana" yaagidi GODAA shiiqqidosona.

English Sentences: And the LORD hearkened to the voice of Israel, and delivered up the Canaanites; and they utterly destroyed them and their cities: and he called the name of the place Hormah.
Wolaitta Sentences: GODAI Israa7eela qaalaa siyidi, he Kanaaneta etayyo aatti immiis; immin eti he Kanaanetanne eta katamata muleera xaissidosona. Hegaa gishshau, he sohoi Horima geetetti sunttettiis.

English Sentences: And they journeyed from mount Hor by the way of the Red sea, to compass the land of Edom: and the soul of the people was much discouraged because of the way.
Wolaitta Sentences: Israa7eela asai Hoora Deriyaappe denddidi, Eedooma biittaa yuushuwaa baanau Zo7o Abbaa efiya ogiyaara biidosona; shin ogiyaa bollan asau danddayai wuriis.

English Sentences: And the people spake against God, and against Moses, Wherefore have ye brought us up out of Egypt to die in the wilderness? for there is no bread, neither is there any water; and our soul loatheth this light bread.
Wolaitta Sentences: Asai, "Nuuni bazzuwan haiqqanau Gibxxeppe pude nuna aissi ehiidetii? Qumi baawa; haatti baawa; ha iita qumai nuna sheneyiis" yaagidi Xoossaa bollinne Muuse bolli zuuzummiis.

English Sentences: And the LORD sent fiery serpents among the people, and they bit the people; and much people of Israel died.
Wolaitta Sentences: Zuuzummin GODAI asaa gidduwan marzziyaara de7iya shooshshata yeddiis; eti dukkin, daro Israa7eelati haiqqidosona.

English Sentences: Therefore the people came to Moses, and said, We have sinned, for we have spoken against the LORD, and against thee; pray unto the LORD, that he take away the serpents from us. And Moses prayed for the people.
Wolaitta Sentences: Eti Muusekko yiidi a, "Nuuni GODAA bollinne ne bolli zuuzummidi, nagaraa oottida. Nuuppe ha shooshshaa haassana mala, neeni GODAA woossa" yaagidosona. Yaagin Muusee asaa gishshau woossiis.

English Sentences: And the LORD said unto Moses, Make thee a fiery serpent, and set it upon a pole: and it shall come to pass, that every one that is bitten, when he looketh upon it, shall live.
Wolaitta Sentences: Hegaappe guyyiyan GODAI Muusa, "Neeni nahaase shooshshaa medhdhada, eta sinttan mittaa bollan kaqqa; dukettida ooninne a xeellikko paxana" yaagiis.

English Sentences: And Moses made a serpent of brass, and put it upon a pole, and it came to pass, that if a serpent had bitten any man, when he beheld the serpent of brass, he lived.
Wolaitta Sentences: Yaagin Muusee nahaase birataappe shooshshaa medhdhidi, mittaa bollan kaqqiis. Hegaappe guyyiyan, shooshshai dukkido asai ubbai nahaase shooshshaa xeellidi paxiis.

English Sentences: And the children of Israel set forward, and pitched in Oboth.
Wolaitta Sentences: Israa7eela asai denddidi, Oboota giyoosan dunkkaanidosona.

English Sentences: And they journeyed from Oboth, and pitched at Ijeabarim, in the wilderness which is before Moab, toward the sunrising.
Wolaitta Sentences: Obootappe denddidi, Moo7aabappe sintta baazzan de7iya bazzuwan, arshsho baggaara, laalettida Abaarima kataman dunkkaanidosona.

English Sentences: From thence they removed, and pitched in the valley of Zared.
Wolaitta Sentences: Hegaappe denddidi, Zareeda Zanggaaran dunkkaanidosona.

English Sentences: From thence they removed, and pitched on the other side of Arnon, which is in the wilderness that cometh out of the coasts of the Amorites: for Arnon is the border of Moab, between Moab and the Amorites.
Wolaitta Sentences: Hegaappe denddidi, Amooretu biittaa gaxaa gakkanau biya bazzuwaa giddon Arnnoona SHaafaappe hefinttan dunkkaanidosona. Arnnoona SHaafai Moo7aaba biittaappenne Amooretu biittaappe gidduwan de7iya zawaa.

English Sentences: Wherefore it is said in the book of the wars of the LORD, What he did in the Red sea, and in the brooks of Arnon,
Wolaitta Sentences: Hegaa gishshau, GODAA Olaa Maxaafan, "Suufa heeran de7iya Waaheeba katamaanne Arnnoona SHaafaa zanggaaraa,

English Sentences: And at the stream of the brooks that goeth down to the dwelling of Ar, and lieth upon the border of Moab.
Wolaitta Sentences: Eera katamaa gakkanaassinne Moo7aaba zawaa gakkanaassi de7iya zanggaara dugettaa" yaagetti xaafettiis.

English Sentences: And from thence they went to Beer: that is the well whereof the LORD spake unto Moses, Gather the people together, and I will give them water.
Wolaitta Sentences: Eti hegaappe denddidi, Beera giyoosaa biidosona; hegee GODAI Muusa, "Asaa shiishsha; taani etau haattaa immana" yaagidi yootido haatta ollaa.

English Sentences: Then Israel sang this song, Spring up, O well; sing ye unto it:
Wolaitta Sentences: Hegan Israa7eela asai ha mazamuriyaa yexxiis.

English Sentences: The princes digged the well, the nobles of the people digged it, by the direction of the lawgiver, with their staves. And from the wilderness they went to Mattanah:
Wolaitta Sentences: "Haattaa ollau, pultta! Halaqati bookkido haattaa ollaayyo, asaa kaalettiyaageetu ollaayyo, kawotaa xam77aaninne eta kazaran bookkido haatta ollaayyo ane yexxoos" yaagiis. Eti he bazzuwaappe Mataana giyoosaa biidosona;

English Sentences: And from Mattanah to Nahaliel: and from Nahaliel to Bamoth:
Wolaitta Sentences: Mataanappe Naahili7eela, Naahili7eelappe Baamoota giyoosaa,

English Sentences: And from Bamoth in the valley, that is in the country of Moab, to the top of Pisgah, which looketh toward Jeshimon.
Wolaitta Sentences: Baamootappe denddidi, Moo7aaban de7iya zanggaaraa biidosona; ha zanggaarai Pisgga Deriyaappe garssan bazzuwaa giigan de7ees.

English Sentences: And Israel sent messengers unto Sihon king of the Amorites, saying,
Wolaitta Sentences: Hegaappe guyyiyan, Israa7eela asai Amoore biittaa Kawuwaa Sihoonakko kiitettiyaageeta hagaadan yaagidi kiittiis;

English Sentences: Let me pass through thy land: we will not turn into the fields, or into the vineyards; we will not drink of the waters of the well: but we will go along by the king's high way, until we be past thy borders.
Wolaitta Sentences: "Nuna ne biittaara kanttissarkkii! Nuuni ne gadiyaa giddo woikko woine turaa giddo gelokko; qassi haatta ollaa augaappenne uyokko. Nuuni ne biittaara kanttana gakkanaassi, Kawo Ogiyaara baana" yaagiis.

English Sentences: And Sihon would not suffer Israel to pass through his border: but Sihon gathered all his people together, and went out against Israel into the wilderness: and he came to Jahaz, and fought against Israel.
Wolaitta Sentences: SHin Sihooni ba biittaara Israa7eela asaa kanttissennan diggiis; i ba olanchchata ubbaa shiishshidi, Israa7eela asaa olanau bazzo biis; Yahaaxa giyoosaa bi gakkidi, Israa7eela asaara olettiis.

English Sentences: And Israel smote him with the edge of the sword, and possessed his land from Arnon unto Jabbok, even unto the children of Ammon: for the border of the children of Ammon was strong.
Wolaitta Sentences: SHin Israa7eela asai olan Amooretuppe daruwaa woridi, eta biittaa Arnnoona SHaafaappe doommidi, Amoonatu zawan de7iya Yaabooqa SHaafaa gakkanaassi oiqqiis. Amoona asatu biittaa zawai gimbbetti uttido gishshau, eti yaa gelibookkona.

English Sentences: And Israel took all these cities: and Israel dwelt in all the cities of the Amorites, in Heshbon, and in all the villages thereof.
Wolaitta Sentences: Yaatin Israa7eelati Amooretu katamata ubbaa xoonidi ekkidosona. Qassi Haseboonanne a yuushuwan de7iya qeeri katamatakka ubbaa oiqqidi, yan uttidosona.

English Sentences: For Heshbon was the city of Sihon the king of the Amorites, who had fought against the former king of Moab, and taken all his land out of his hand, even unto Arnon.
Wolaitta Sentences: Haseboona katamai Amooretu Kawuwaa Sihoona katamaa. Sihooni Moo7aaba biittaa kawuwaa kaseegaa olidi, Arnnoona SHaafaa gakkanaassi a biittaa ubbaa appe ekkidaagaa.

English Sentences: Wherefore they that speak in proverbs say, Come into Heshbon, let the city of Sihon be built and prepared:
Wolaitta Sentences: Hegaa gishshau, leemisuwan hagaadan yaagidosona; "Hasebooni haayite; he katamai zaaretti keexetto; Sihoona gita katamai wodhdhi eqqidi keexetto!

English Sentences: For there is a fire gone out of Heshbon, a flame from the city of Sihon: it hath consumed Ar of Moab, and the lords of the high places of Arnon.
Wolaitta Sentences: Aissi giikko, tamai Haseboonappe, lacoi Sihoona katamaappe kiyiis; kiyidi Moo7aaban de7iya Eeranne Arnnoona SHaafaa heeran gezziyan de7iya halaqata miis.

English Sentences: Woe to thee, Moab! thou art undone, O people of Chemosh: he hath given his sons that escaped, and his daughters, into captivity unto Sihon king of the Amorites.
Wolaitta Sentences: Moo7aabaa, neeyyo aayye7ana! Kamooshau goinniyaageetoo, intte xayideta. Intte xoossai, Kamooshi, intte attuma naata baqatau, intte macca naata omooduwau, Amooretu Kawuwaa Sihoonayyo immiis.

English Sentences: We have shot at them; Heshbon is perished even unto Dibon, and we have laid them waste even unto Nophah, which reacheth unto Medeba.
Wolaitta Sentences: Intte zerettati Haseboonappe doommidi, Diboona gakkanaassi muleera xayidosona. Medaaba matan de7iya Nofaaha gakkanaassi wurssidi bashshidosona" yaagidosona.

English Sentences: Thus Israel dwelt in the land of the Amorites.
Wolaitta Sentences: Hegaadan hanidi, Israa7eelati Amooretu biittan uttidosona.

English Sentences: And Moses sent to spy out Jaazer, and they took the villages thereof, and drove out the Amorites that were there.
Wolaitta Sentences: Qassi Muusee wochchiyaageeta Yaa7izeera giyo katamaa yeddin, Israa7eelati he katamaanne a heeran de7iya qeeri katamata oiqqidi, hegan de7iya Amooreta kessidi yedettidosona.

English Sentences: And they turned and went up by the way of Bashan: and Og the king of Bashan went out against them, he, and all his people, to the battle at Edrei.
Wolaitta Sentences: Hegaappe guyyiyan, Israa7eelati simmidi, Baasaane efiya ogiyaara kiyidosona. Kiyin Baasaane Kawoi Oogi ba olanchchatu ubbaara Ediraa7a giyo katamaa etaara olettanau kiyiis.

English Sentences: And the LORD said unto Moses, Fear him not: for I have delivered him into thy hand, and all his people, and his land; and thou shalt do to him as thou didst unto Sihon king of the Amorites, which dwelt at Heshbon.
Wolaitta Sentences: SHin GODAI Muusa, "Ayyo yayyoppa! Aissi giikko, taani Kawuwaa Ooga a asaa ubbaaranne a biittaara ne kushiyan aattada immaas. Haseboonan uttidi haarida Amooretu Kawuwaa Sihoona bolli oottidoogaadan, neeni a bollikka oottana" yaagiis.

English Sentences: So they smote him, and his sons, and all his people, until there was none left him alive: and they possessed his land.
Wolaitta Sentences: Yaagin Israa7eelati Ooga, a attuma naatanne a asaa ubbaa issuwaanne paxa ashshennan woridosona. Woridi eti a biittaa laattidosona.

English Sentences: And the children of Israel set forward, and pitched in the plains of Moab on this side Jordan by Jericho.
Wolaitta Sentences: Hegaappe guyyiyan Israa7eela asai denddidi, Yarkko ginan Yorddaanoosa hefinttan de7iya Moo7aaba dembban dunkkaaniis.

English Sentences: And Balak the son of Zippor saw all that Israel had done to the Amorites.
Wolaitta Sentences: Israa7eela asai Amooretu bolli oottidoogaa ubbaa Xippoora na7ai Baalaaqi siyiis.

English Sentences: And Moab was sore afraid of the people, because they were many: and Moab was distressed because of the children of Israel.
Wolaitta Sentences: Siyin Israa7eela asai keehi daro gidido gishshau, Moo7aabati keehi dagammidi yayyidosona.

English Sentences: And Moab said unto the elders of Midian, Now shall this company lick up all that are round about us, as the ox licketh up the grass of the field. And Balak the son of Zippor was king of the Moabites at that time.
Wolaitta Sentences: Moo7aabati Midiyaama cimata, "Boorai maataa mi xaissiyoogaadan ha wude asai nu yuushuwan de7iya ubbaa mi xaissana" yaagidosona. Yaagin he wode Moo7aaba Kawoi, Xippoora na7ai Baalaaqi

English Sentences: He sent messengers therefore unto Balaam the son of Beor to Pethor, which is by the river of the land of the children of his people, to call him, saying, Behold, there is a people come out from Egypt: behold, they cover the face of the earth, and they abide over against me:
Wolaitta Sentences: Amaawa biittan Efiraaxiisa SHaafaa matan Patoora kataman de7iya Bi7oora na7aa Balaamakko asa kiittiis. Kiittiiddi Baalaaqi, "Be7a, Gibxxeppe daro asai kiyiis; eti biitta ubbaa maayidi, taappe ya baggan de7oosona.

English Sentences: Come now therefore, I pray thee, curse me this people; for they are too mighty for me: peradventure I shall prevail, that we may smite them, and that I may drive them out of the land: for I wot that he whom thou blessest is blessed, and he whom thou cursest is cursed.
Wolaitta Sentences: Eti taayyo keehi wolqqaamiyo gishshau, hayyanaa ha77i yaada, eta taayyo qanggarkkii! Ooni erii, taani eta xoonanaunne biittaappe kessanau danddayanaakkonne. Aissi giikko, neeni anjjidoogee anjjettidaagaanne neeni qanggidoogee qanggettidaagaa gidiyoogaa taani erais" yaagiis.

English Sentences: And the elders of Moab and the elders of Midian departed with the rewards of divination in their hand; and they came unto Balaam, and spake unto him the words of Balak.
Wolaitta Sentences: Yaagin Moo7aaba cimatinne Midiyaama cimati qanggissiyo waagaa ekkidi, Balaamakko biidosona. Biidi Baalaaqi giidoogaa ayyo yootidosona.

English Sentences: And he said unto them, Lodge here this night, and I will bring you word again, as the LORD shall speak unto me: and the princes of Moab abode with Balaam.
Wolaitta Sentences: Yootin Balaami eta, "Hachchi qammi hagan aqite; GODAI taayyo yootiyoogaa taani intteyyo yootana" yaagiis. Yaagin Moo7aaba halaqati Balaamaagan takkidosona.

English Sentences: And God came unto Balaam, and said, What men are these with thee?
Wolaitta Sentences: Xoossai Balaamakko yiidi, "Hageeti nenaara de7iya asati oonee?" yaagidi oichchiis.

English Sentences: And Balaam said unto God, Balak the son of Zippor, king of Moab, hath sent unto me, saying,
Wolaitta Sentences: Oichchin Balaami Xoossaa, "Moo7aaba Kawoi, Xippoora na7ai Baalaaqi,

English Sentences: Behold, there is a people come out of Egypt, which covereth the face of the earth: come now, curse me them; peradventure I shall be able to overcome them, and drive them out.
Wolaitta Sentences: Gibxxeppe daro asai kiyiis; eti biitta ubbaa maayidosona. Ha77i neeni yaada, eta taayyo qanggarkkii! Ooni erii, taani eta xoonanaunne biittaappe kessanau danddayanaakkonne yaagidi eta taakko kiittiis" yaagiis.

English Sentences: And God said unto Balaam, Thou shalt not go with them; thou shalt not curse the people: for they are blessed.
Wolaitta Sentences: Yaagin Xoossai Balaama, "Neeni etaara booppa. Israa7eelati anjjettidaageeta gidiyo gishshau, neeni he asaa qanggoppa" yaagiis.

English Sentences: And Balaam rose up in the morning, and said unto the princes of Balak, Get you into your land: for the LORD refuseth to give me leave to go with you.
Wolaitta Sentences: Wonttetta gallassi maallado Balaami denddidi, Baalaaqa halaqata, "Taani inttenaara beennaadan GODAI diggido gishshau, intte biitti simmite" yaagiis.

English Sentences: And the princes of Moab rose up, and they went unto Balak, and said, Balaam refuseth to come with us.
Wolaitta Sentences: Yaagin Moo7aaba halaqati yaappe denddidi, Baalaaqakko simmidi a, "Balaami nunaara yeennan ixxiis" yaagidosona.

English Sentences: And Balak sent yet again princes, more, and more honourable than they.
Wolaitta Sentences: Zaaridikka Baalaaqi kaseegeetuppe aadhdhi bonchchettidanne qoodankka corattida hara halaqata akko kiittiis.

English Sentences: And they came to Balaam, and said to him, Thus saith Balak the son of Zippor, Let nothing, I pray thee, hinder thee from coming unto me:
Wolaitta Sentences: Eti Balaamakko yiidi, "Xippoora na7ai Baalaaqi nena, Neeni taakko yaanaagaa nena aibinne teqqoppo.

English Sentences: For I will promote thee unto very great honour, and I will do whatsoever thou sayest unto me: come therefore, I pray thee, curse me this people.
Wolaitta Sentences: Aissi giikko, taani neeyyo daro woituwaa immana; neeni giyoobaa ubbaa aibanne taani oottana. Yaada ha asaa taayyo qanggarkkii! yaagiis" yaagidi yootidosona.

English Sentences: And Balaam answered and said unto the servants of Balak, If Balak would give me his house full of silver and gold, I cannot go beyond the word of the LORD my God, to do less or more.
Wolaitta Sentences: SHin Balaami etayyo, "Baalaaqi harai atto birainne worqqai kumido ba kawo keettaa tau immidaba gidiyaakkonne, GODAA ta Xoossaa azazuwaappe kanttada, taani aibanne pacissanau woikko gujjanau danddayikke.

English Sentences: Now therefore, I pray you, tarry ye also here this night, that I may know what the LORD will say unto me more.
Wolaitta Sentences: GODAI taayyo yootiyo harabi de7ikko taani eranaadan, inttekka hachchi qamma hagan aqite" yaagiis.

English Sentences: And God came unto Balaam at night, and said unto him, If the men come to call thee, rise up, and go with them; but yet the word which I shall say unto thee, that shalt thou do.
Wolaitta Sentences: He gallassa qammi Xoossai Balaamakko yiidi, "Ha asai nena xeesanau yiido gishshau, neeni etaara ba. SHin taani neeyyo yootiyoobaa xalaalaa ootta" yaagiis.

English Sentences: And Balaam rose up in the morning, and saddled his ass, and went with the princes of Moab.
Wolaitta Sentences: Yaagin wonttetta gallassi Balaami ba hariyo kooridi, Moo7aaba halaqatuura biis.

English Sentences: And God's anger was kindled because he went: and the angel of the LORD stood in the way for an adversary against him. Now he was riding upon his ass, and his two servants were with him.
Wolaitta Sentences: SHin i biyo wode Xoossaa hanqqoi eexxi kiyiis; yaatin GODAA kiitanchchai a teqqanau ogiyan eqqiis. He wode Balaami ba hariyo toggidaashin, a naa77u ashkkarati aara de7oosona.

English Sentences: And the ass saw the angel of the LORD standing in the way, and his sword drawn in his hand: and the ass turned aside out of the way, and went into the field: and Balaam smote the ass, to turn her into the way.
Wolaitta Sentences: GODAA kiitanchchai bisuwaa zaaretti oiqqidi, ogiyan eqqidaagaa hariyaa be7annee, ogiyaa aggada, goshshaa giddo gelaasu. Gelin Balaami ogiyaa zaaranau hariyo bukkiis.

English Sentences: But the angel of the LORD stood in a path of the vineyards, a wall being on this side, and a wall on that side.
Wolaitta Sentences: Yaatin GODAA kiitanchchai naa77u woine turaa sohotuppe gidduwan, ya baggaaranne ha baggaara gimbbiyan diretti uttida un77o ogiyan eqqiis.

English Sentences: And when the ass saw the angel of the LORD, she thrust herself unto the wall, and crushed Balaam's foot against the wall: and he smote her again.
Wolaitta Sentences: Hariyaa GODAA kiitanchchaa be7ido wode, gimbbe dirssaakko shiiqada, Balaama tohuwaa gimbbe dirssaara daraxaasu; daraxin i hariyo naa77anttokka bukkiis.

English Sentences: And the angel of the LORD went further, and stood in a narrow place, where was no way to turn either to the right hand or to the left.
Wolaitta Sentences: Hegaappe guyyiyan, GODAA kiitanchchai sinttaukko aadhdhidi, haddirssa baggaarakka ushachcha baggaara kanttiyoosi bainna un77o sohuwan eqqiis.

English Sentences: And when the ass saw the angel of the LORD, she fell down under Balaam: and Balaam's anger was kindled, and he smote the ass with a staff.
Wolaitta Sentences: Hariyaa GODAA kiitanchchaa be7ada, Balaami toggidaashin zin77aasu. Balaami keehi hanqqettidi, ba xam77an hariyo bukkiis.

English Sentences: And the LORD opened the mouth of the ass, and she said unto Balaam, What have I done unto thee, that thou hast smitten me these three times?
Wolaitta Sentences: Hegaappe guyyiyan, GODAI haree doonaa dooyin, hariyaa Balaama, "Taani neeyyo ai oottiinee neeni tana ha heezzutoo bukkidoogee?" yaagaasu.

English Sentences: And Balaam said unto the ass, Because thou hast mocked me: I would there were a sword in mine hand, for now would I kill thee.
Wolaitta Sentences: Yaagin Balaami hariyo, "Neeni tana eeyettido gishshataassa. Ta kushiyan bisoi de7idabaa gidiyaakko, taani nena ha77i worana shin!" yaagiis.

English Sentences: And the ass said unto Balaam, Am not I thine ass, upon which thou hast ridden ever since I was thine unto this day? was I ever wont to do so unto thee? And he said, Nay.
Wolaitta Sentences: Yaagin hariyaa Balaama, "Taani ne de7o ubban hachchi gakkanaassi toggiyo ne hariyo gidikkinaa? Taani neeyyo hagaadan hana eriyaanaa?" yaagaasu. Yaagin Balaami, "Hana erakka" yaagiis.

English Sentences: Then the LORD opened the eyes of Balaam, and he saw the angel of the LORD standing in the way, and his sword drawn in his hand: and he bowed down his head, and fell flat on his face.
Wolaitta Sentences: Hegaappe guyyiyan, GODAI Balaama aifiyaa dooyin, GODAA kiitanchchai shoohuwaappe shoddido bisuwaa oiqqidi, ogiyan eqqidaagaa be7iis. Be7idi i lichchi giidi, som77uwaa sa7aa gattidi gufanniis.

English Sentences: And the angel of the LORD said unto him, Wherefore hast thou smitten thine ass these three times? behold, I went out to withstand thee, because thy way is perverse before me:
Wolaitta Sentences: GODAA kiitanchchai a, "Ne hariyo ha heezzutoo aissi bukkadii? Ne ogee ta sinttan geella gidiyo gishshau, taani nena teqqanau hagaa yaas.

English Sentences: And the ass saw me, and turned from me these three times: unless she had turned from me, surely now also I had slain thee, and saved her alive.
Wolaitta Sentences: Hariyaa tana be7ada, ta sinttappe heezzutoo wora simmaasu. Hariyaa wora simmabeennaba gidiyaakko, taani nena hannoode tumu worarggada, hariyo ashshana shin" yaagiis.

English Sentences: And Balaam said unto the angel of the LORD, I have sinned; for I knew not that thou stoodest in the way against me: now therefore, if it displease thee, I will get me back again.
Wolaitta Sentences: Yaagin Balaami GODAA kiitanchchaa zaaridi, "Taani nagaraa oottaas. Neeni tana teqqanau ogiyaa bollan eqqidoogaa taani erabeikke. Neeni dosabeennabaa gidikko, taani ha77i guyye simmana" yaagiis.

English Sentences: And the angel of the LORD said unto Balaam, Go with the men: but only the word that I shall speak unto thee, that thou shalt speak. So Balaam went with the princes of Balak.
Wolaitta Sentences: Yaagin GODAA kiitanchchai Balaama, "Neeni ha asatuura ba; shin taani neeyyo yootiyoogaa xalaalaa haasaya" yaagiis. Yaagin Balaami Baalaaqa biittaa halaqatuura biis.

English Sentences: And when Balak heard that Balaam was come, he went out to meet him unto a city of Moab, which is in the border of Arnon, which is in the utmost coast.
Wolaitta Sentences: Balaami yiyoogaa Baalaaqi siyido wode, Arnnoona SHaafaa zawan ba biittaa gaxan de7iya Moo7aabatu kataman aara gaittanau biis.

English Sentences: And Balak said unto Balaam, Did I not earnestly send unto thee to call thee? wherefore camest thou not unto me? am I not able indeed to promote thee to honour?
Wolaitta Sentences: Baalaaqi Balaama, "Neeni eesuwan yaanaadan taani kiittabeikkinaa? Neeni aibissi taakko sohuwaara yabeikkii? Taani neeyyo woitanau tumu danddayikkinaa?" yaagiis.

English Sentences: And Balaam said unto Balak, Lo, I am come unto thee: have I now any power at all to say any thing? the word that God putteth in my mouth, that shall I speak.
Wolaitta Sentences: Yaagin Balaami Baalaaqa, "Be7a, ha77i taani neekko yaas; shin taani aibanne gaanau tumu danddayikke. Xoossai tana haasayissiyoogaa xalaalaa taani haasayana" yaagiis.

English Sentences: And Balaam went with Balak, and they came unto Kirjathhuzoth.
Wolaitta Sentences: Hegaappe guyyiyan, Balaami Baalaaqaara Qiriyaati-Huxoota giyo katamaa biis.

English Sentences: And Balak offered oxen and sheep, and sent to Balaam, and to the princes that were with him.
Wolaitta Sentences: Bin Baalaaqi miizzaanne dorssaa yarshshidi, ashuwaappe amaridaagaa Balaamayyoonne aara de7iya halaqatuyyo immiis.

English Sentences: And it came to pass on the morrow, that Balak took Balaam, and brought him up into the high places of Baal, that thence he might see the utmost part of the people.
Wolaitta Sentences: Wonttetta gallassi maallado Baalaaqi Balaama ekkidi, Baamooti-Ba7aali giyoosaa pude kessiis; kessin hegan eqqidi, Balaami Israa7eela asaappe baggaa be7iis.

English Sentences: And Balaam said unto Balak, Build me here seven altars, and prepare me here seven oxen and seven rams.
Wolaitta Sentences: Balaami Baalaaqa, "Hagan neeni tau laappun yarshshiyo sohota gimbba; qassi laappun korima booraanne laappun dorssa orggeta neeni taayyo giigissa" yaagiis.

English Sentences: And Balak did as Balaam had spoken; and Balak and Balaam offered on every altar a bullock and a ram.
Wolaitta Sentences: Balaami giidoogaadan Baalaaqi oottiis; eti naa77aikka issi issi yarshshiyo sohuwan issi korima booraanne issi dorssa orggiyaa yarshshidosona.

English Sentences: And Balaam said unto Balak, Stand by thy burnt offering, and I will go: peradventure the LORD will come to meet me: and whatsoever he sheweth me I will tell thee. And he went to an high place.
Wolaitta Sentences: Hegaappe guyyiyan, Balaami Baalaaqa, "Neeni ne xuuggiyo yarshshuwaa matan hagan eqqashsha; taani gedekko bais. GODAI tanaara gaittanau geelladan yeennan aggenna. I taayyo qonccissiyoobaa aibanne taani neeyyo yootana" yaagiis. Yaagidi xoqqa booddila sohuwaa kiyiis.

English Sentences: And God met Balaam: and he said unto him, I have prepared seven altars, and I have offered upon every altar a bullock and a ram.
Wolaitta Sentences: Hegan Xoossai Balaamaara gaittin Balaami, "Taani laappun yarshshiyo sohota giigissaas; issi issi yarshshiyo sohuwan issi korima booraanne issi dorssa orggiyaa yarshshaas" yaagiis.

English Sentences: And the LORD put a word in Balaam's mouth, and said, Return unto Balak, and thus thou shalt speak.
Wolaitta Sentences: Yaagin Balaami gaanabaa GODAI ayyo yootidi, "Neeni Baalaaqakko simmada, ayyo ha hiraagaa yoota" yaagiis.

English Sentences: And he returned unto him, and, lo, he stood by his burnt sacrifice, he, and all the princes of Moab.
Wolaitta Sentences: Yaagin i Baalaaqakko simmiyo wode, Baalaaqi Moo7aaba halaqatu ubbaara ba xuuggiyo yarshshuwaa matan eqqiis.

English Sentences: And he took up his parable, and said, Balak the king of Moab hath brought me from Aram, out of the mountains of the east, saying, Come, curse me Jacob, and come, defy Israel.
Wolaitta Sentences: Hegaappe guyyiyan, Balaami ba hiraagaa hagaadan yaagidi yootiis; "Moo7aaba kawoi arshsho bagga deretuppe, Sooriyaa biittaappe tana hagaadan yaagidi ehiis; Haa ya; Yaaqooba taayyo qangga! Israa7eela asaa, "Wurite!" yaaga yaagiis.

English Sentences: How shall I curse, whom God hath not cursed? or how shall I defy, whom the LORD hath not defied?
Wolaitta Sentences: Xoossai qanggibeennaageeta taani waata qanggoo? GODAI, Wurite! yaagibeennaageeta taani waatada, Wurite! yaagoo?

English Sentences: For from the top of the rocks I see him, and from the hills I behold him: lo, the people shall dwell alone, and shall not be reckoned among the nations.
Wolaitta Sentences: Taani xoqqa zaallaa huuphiyan eqqada eta xeellais; keran eqqada taani eta be7ais. Eti banttarkka de7iya asa; eti banttana kawotettatuppe issuwaadan qoodokkona.

English Sentences: Who can count the dust of Jacob, and the number of the fourth part of Israel? Let me die the death of the righteous, and let my last end be like his!
Wolaitta Sentences: Baanaadan corattida Yaaqooba zerettaa ooni qoodanau danddayii? Harai atto Israa7eela asau oiddantta kushiyaa ooni qoodanau danddayii? Ta haiqoi xillotu haiquwaa mala gido; ta de7uwaa wurssettaikka etaagaadan hano!" yaagiis.

English Sentences: And Balak said unto Balaam, What hast thou done unto me? I took thee to curse mine enemies, and, behold, thou hast blessed them altogether.
Wolaitta Sentences: Yaagin Baalaaqi Balaama, "Neeni ta bolli oottiyoobi aibee? Taani nena ta morkketa qangganaadan ehaas; shin neeni eta anjjadasappe attin, haraba ainne oottabaakka!" yaagiis.

English Sentences: And he answered and said, Must I not take heed to speak that which the LORD hath put in my mouth?
Wolaitta Sentences: Yaagin Balaami zaaridi, "Taani GODAI tana haasayissiyoogaappe haraa haasayooyye?" yaagiis.

English Sentences: And Balak said unto him, Come, I pray thee, with me unto another place, from whence thou mayest see them: thou shalt see but the utmost part of them, and shalt not see them all: and curse me them from thence.
Wolaitta Sentences: Hegaappe guyyiyan, Baalaaqi a, "Eta neeni be7anau danddayiyo harasaa tanaara hindda. Neeni etappe amaridaagaa be7anaappe attin, eta ubbaa be7akka. Neeni hegan taayyo eta qanggarkkii" yaagiis.

English Sentences: And he brought him into the field of Zophim, to the top of Pisgah, and built seven altars, and offered a bullock and a ram on every altar.
Wolaitta Sentences: Yaagidi Pisgga giyo deriyaa huuphiyan de7iya Xofiima dembbaa ekkidi efiis. Hegan laappun yarshshiyo sohota gimbbiis; gimbbidi issi issi yarshshiyo sohuwan issi korima booraanne issi dorssa orggiyaa yarshshiis.

English Sentences: And he said unto Balak, Stand here by thy burnt offering, while I meet the LORD yonder.
Wolaitta Sentences: Balaami Baalaaqa, "Taani hinin GODAARA gaittiyo wode, neeni hagan ne xuuggiyo yarshshuwaa matan eqqashsha" yaagiis.

English Sentences: And the LORD met Balaam, and put a word in his mouth, and said, Go again unto Balak, and say thus.
Wolaitta Sentences: GODAI Balaamaara gaittidi kiittiiddi, "Neeni Baalaaqakko simmada, ayyo ha hiraagaa yoota" yaagiis.

English Sentences: And when he came to him, behold, he stood by his burnt offering, and the princes of Moab with him. And Balak said unto him, What hath the LORD spoken?
Wolaitta Sentences: Yaagin i akko simmidi, ba xuuggiyo yarshshuwaa matan Moo7aaba biittaa halaqatuura eqqidaagaa demmiis. Baalaaqi a, "GODAI yootidobai aibee?" yaagiis.

English Sentences: And he took up his parable, and said, Rise up, Balak, and hear; hearken unto me, thou son of Zippor:
Wolaitta Sentences: Yaagin Balaami ba hiraagaa hagaadan yaagidi yootiis; "Xippoora na7aa Baalaaqaa denddada ezgga; taani yootiyoogaa siya!

English Sentences: God is not a man, that he should lie; neither the son of man, that he should repent: hath he said, and shall he not do it? or hath he spoken, and shall he not make it good?
Wolaitta Sentences: Xoossai worddotanau asa gidenna; ba qofaa laammanau i asa na7a gidenna. I yootidi, ba yootidoogaa oottennee? Woikko i ba giidobaa polennee?

English Sentences: Behold, I have received commandment to bless: and he hath blessed; and I cannot reverse it.
Wolaitta Sentences: Taani anjjanau azazuwaa ekkaas. I anjjiichchiis; taani hegaa laammanau danddayikke.

English Sentences: He hath not beheld iniquity in Jacob, neither hath he seen perverseness in Israel: the LORD his God is with him, and the shout of a king is among them.
Wolaitta Sentences: Yaaqooba zariyau iitabi yaanabi, Israa7eela asau metoi gakkanabi taayyo beettibeenna. GODAI eta Xoossai etaara de7ees; i etau kawo gidiyoogaa awaajjoosona.

English Sentences: God brought them out of Egypt; he hath as it were the strength of an unicorn.
Wolaitta Sentences: Xoossai eta Gibxxeppe kessiis; i mino menttaadan etau de7ees.

English Sentences: Surely there is no enchantment against Jacob, neither is there any divination against Israel: according to this time it shall be said of Jacob and of Israel, What hath God wrought!
Wolaitta Sentences: Yaaqooba zariyaa gakkana biti baawa; Israa7eela asaa qohana murunnoikka baawa. Asai ha77i, Yaaqoobassinne Israa7eelassi Xoossai oottidobaa be7ite yaagana.

English Sentences: Behold, the people shall rise up as a great lion, and lift up himself as a young lion: he shall not lie down until he eat of the prey, and drink the blood of the slain.
Wolaitta Sentences: Ha asai macca gaammeedan denddiis. Ba oiqqidobaa maana gakkanaashiininne ba woridoogaa suuttaa uyana gakkanaashin, shemppenna gaammuwaadan eti eqqi denddoosona" yaagiis.

English Sentences: And Balak said unto Balaam, Neither curse them at all, nor bless them at all.
Wolaitta Sentences: Hegaappe guyyiyan, Baalaaqi Balaama, "Neeni eta mulekka qanggoppanne mulekka anjjoppa" yaagiis.

English Sentences: But Balaam answered and said unto Balak, Told not I thee, saying, All that the LORD speaketh, that I must do?
Wolaitta Sentences: Yaagin Balaami zaaridi, "GODAI giyoobaa ubbaa oottana gaada taani neeyyo yootabeikkinaa?" yaagiis.

English Sentences: And Balak said unto Balaam, Come, I pray thee, I will bring thee unto another place; peradventure it will please God that thou mayest curse me them from thence.
Wolaitta Sentences: Hegaappe guyyiyan, Baalaaqi Balaama, "Haa ya; taani nena harasaa efaana. Ooni erii, nena yaa efin Xoossai ufaittidi, nena eta taayyo qanggissanaakko" yaagiis.

English Sentences: And Balak brought Balaam unto the top of Peor, that looketh toward Jeshimon.
Wolaitta Sentences: Baalaaqi Balaama bazzuwaa bollaara duge xeelliyo Pa7oora Deriyaa huuphiyaa efiis.

English Sentences: And Balaam said unto Balak, Build me here seven altars, and prepare me here seven bullocks and seven rams.
Wolaitta Sentences: Efin Balaami, "Neeni hagan tau laappun yarshshiyo sohota gimbba; qassi laappun korima booratanne laappun dorssa orggeta taayyo giigissa" yaagiis.

English Sentences: And Balak did as Balaam had said, and offered a bullock and a ram on every altar.
Wolaitta Sentences: Balaami giidoogaadan Baalaaqi oottiis; issi issi yarshshiyo sohuwan issi korima booraanne issi dorssaa orggiyaa yarshshiis.

English Sentences: And when Balaam saw that it pleased the LORD to bless Israel, he went not, as at other times, to seek for enchantments, but he set his face toward the wilderness.
Wolaitta Sentences: Israa7eela anjjiyoogee GODAA ufaissidoogaa Balaami be7ido wode, kase i oottidoogaadan murunnanau koyibeenna; shin ba som77uwaa bazzuwaakko zaariis.

English Sentences: And Balaam lifted up his eyes, and he saw Israel abiding in his tents according to their tribes; and the spirit of God came upon him.
Wolaitta Sentences: Zaaridi xoqqu giidi xeellidi, Israa7eela asai ba zariyan zariyan dunkkaani uttidaagaa be7iis; be7in Xoossaa Ayyaanai a bolli wodhdhiis.

English Sentences: And he took up his parable, and said, Balaam the son of Beor hath said, and the man whose eyes are open hath said:
Wolaitta Sentences: Wodhdhin i ba hiraagaa hagaadan yaagidi yootiis; "Bi7oora na7aa Balaama hiraagai, a aifee tishshi ootti xeelliyoogaa hiraagai,

English Sentences: He hath said, which heard the words of God, which saw the vision of the Almighty, falling into a trance, but having his eyes open:
Wolaitta Sentences: Xoossai giyoobaa siyiyaagaa hiraagai, lichchi giidi gufannin, a aifee dooyettidoogaanne Ubbaa Danddayiya Xoossaa ajjuutaa be7iyaagaa hiraagai hagaa.

English Sentences: How goodly are thy tents, O Jacob, and thy tabernacles, O Israel!
Wolaitta Sentences: Yaaqooba zaretoo, intte dunkkaaneti, Israa7eela asau, intte de7iyoosatikka aiba lo77oo!

English Sentences: As the valleys are they spread forth, as gardens by the river's side, as the trees of lign aloes which the LORD hath planted, and as cedar trees beside the waters.
Wolaitta Sentences: Eti micettida wombbaadan, shaafaa doonan de7iya ataakilttiyaa sohuwaadan, GODAI tokkido godare uuttaadaaninne haattaa doonan de7iya zigaadan hanoosona.

English Sentences: He shall pour the water out of his buckets, and his seed shall be in many waters, and his king shall be higher than Agag, and his kingdom shall be exalted.
Wolaitta Sentences: Etau daro haattai pulttana; eta zerettau gidiya haattai de7ana. Eta kawoi Kawuwaa Agaagappe gitatana; eta kawotettaikka bonchchettana.

English Sentences: God brought him forth out of Egypt; he hath as it were the strength of an unicorn: he shall eat up the nations his enemies, and shall break their bones, and pierce them through with his arrows.
Wolaitta Sentences: Xoossai eta Gibxxeppe kessiis; i mino menttaadan etau de7ees. Eti morkke kawotettaa mittana; eta meqettaakka liiqissana; eti bantta wonddafiyaa zubbiyan eta caddana.

English Sentences: He couched, he lay down as a lion, and as a great lion: who shall stir him up? Blessed is he that blesseth thee, and cursed is he that curseth thee.
Wolaitta Sentences: Israa7eela asai gaammuwaadan zin77ees. Macca gaammeedan eta denttanau ooni xalanee? Inttena anjjiya ubbai anjjettidaagaa gidana; inttena qanggiya ubbai qanggettidaagaa gidana" yaagiis.

English Sentences: And Balak's anger was kindled against Balaam, and he smote his hands together: and Balak said unto Balaam, I called thee to curse mine enemies, and, behold, thou hast altogether blessed them these three times.
Wolaitta Sentences: Hegaappe guyyiyan, Baalaaqi Balaama bolli hanqquwaa eexxi kiyiis. Baalaaqi ba kushiyaa dukkidi Balaama, "Ta morkketa qangganaadan taani nena xeesaas; shin neeni ha heezzutookka eta anjjadasa.

English Sentences: Therefore now flee thou to thy place: I thought to promote thee unto great honour; but, lo, the LORD hath kept thee back from honour.
Wolaitta Sentences: Simmi ha77i neeni ne soo baqata; Taani neeyyo darobaa woitana gaas; shin neeni woituwaa ekkennaadan GODAI nena diggiis" yaagiis.

English Sentences: And Balaam said unto Balak, Spake I not also to thy messengers which thou sentest unto me, saying,
Wolaitta Sentences: Yaagin Balaami Baalaaqa zaaridi, "Neeni taakko kiittidoogeetun,

English Sentences: If Balak would give me his house full of silver and gold, I cannot go beyond the commandment of the LORD, to do either good or bad of mine own mind; but what the LORD saith, that will I speak?
Wolaitta Sentences: Baalaaqi harai atto ba birainne worqqai kumido ba kawo keettaa tau immidaba gidiyaakkonne, GODAI yootidoogaa kanttada, lo77uwaa woikko iitaa ta sheniyan oottanau danddayikke. Taani GODAI giyoobaa xalaalaa gaana yaagada neeyyo yootabeikkinaayye?" yaagiis.

English Sentences: And now, behold, I go unto my people: come therefore, and I will advertise thee what this people shall do to thy people in the latter days.
Wolaitta Sentences: Yaagidi, "Taani ha77i ta asaakko bais; shin neeni haa ya; ha asai wurssetta wodiyan ne asaa oottanabaa taani neeyyo yootana" yaagiis.

English Sentences: And he took up his parable, and said, Balaam the son of Beor hath said, and the man whose eyes are open hath said:
