Wolaitta Sentences: Yaagidi i ba hiraagaa hagaadan yaagidi yootiis; "Bi7oora na7aa Balaama hiraagai, a aifee tishshi oottidi xeelliyoogaa hiraagai,

English Sentences: He hath said, which heard the words of God, and knew the knowledge of the most High, which saw the vision of the Almighty, falling into a trance, but having his eyes open:
Wolaitta Sentences: Xoossai giyoobaa siyiyaagaanne Ubbaappe Xoqqiya Xoossaappe gidida eratettai de7iyoogaa hiraagai, lichchi giidi gufannin, a aifee dooyettidoogaanne Ubbaa Danddayiya Xoossaa ajjuutaa be7iyaagaa hiraagai hagaa.

English Sentences: I shall see him, but not now: I shall behold him, but not nigh: there shall come a Star out of Jacob, and a Sceptre shall rise out of Israel, and shall smite the corners of Moab, and destroy all the children of Sheth.
Wolaitta Sentences: Taani a be7ais; shin wodee ha77a gidenna; taani a xeellais; shin matan gidenna. Yaaqooba zariyaappe xoolinttee kiyana. Israa7eelappe kawotaa xam77ai kiyana. Moo7aaba asaa som77uwaa i gaacci qolana. Seeta asaa ubbaa huuphiyaa i kinchchana.

English Sentences: And Edom shall be a possession, Seir also shall be a possession for his enemies; and Israel shall do valiantly.
Wolaitta Sentences: Eedoomi xoonettana; a morkkee Se7iirikka xoonettana; shin Israa7eeli minni minnidi baana.

English Sentences: Out of Jacob shall come he that shall have dominion, and shall destroy him that remaineth of the city.
Wolaitta Sentences: Yaaqoobappe haariyaagee kiyana; kiyidi eta kataman paxa attidaageeta xaissana" yaagiis.

English Sentences: And when he looked on Amalek, he took up his parable, and said, Amalek was the first of the nations; but his latter end shall be that he perish for ever.
Wolaitta Sentences: Hegaappe guyyiyan, Balaami Amaaleeqa asata be7idi, ba hiraagaa hagaadan yaagidi yootiis; "Kawotettatu giddon Amaaleeqi koiro; shin eta wurssettai xayo" yaagiis.

English Sentences: And he looked on the Kenites, and took up his parable, and said, Strong is thy dwellingplace, and thou puttest thy nest in a rock.
Wolaitta Sentences: Qassi Balaami Qeena asata be7idi, ba hiraagaa hagaadan yaagidi yootiis; "Intte de7iyo sohoi saro soho gidees; intte keettai zaallaa bollan keexettiis.

English Sentences: Nevertheless the Kenite shall be wasted, until Asshur shall carry thee away captive.
Wolaitta Sentences: SHin Asooreti inttena omooddiyo wode, intte Qeena asati xayana" yaagiis.

English Sentences: And he took up his parable, and said, Alas, who shall live when God doeth this!
Wolaitta Sentences: Hegaappe guyyiyan, Balaami ba hiraagaa hagaadan yaagidi yootiis; "Aayye7ana! Xoossai hagaa oottiyo wode ooni de7ana danddayii?

English Sentences: And ships shall come from the coast of Chittim, and shall afflict Asshur, and shall afflict Eber, and he also shall perish for ever.
Wolaitta Sentences: Markkabeti Kitiima haruuruwaappe yaana; eti Asooretanne Ebeerata huqqunnana; shin qassi etikka xayana" yaagiis.

English Sentences: And Balaam rose up, and went and returned to his place: and Balak also went his way.
Wolaitta Sentences: Hegaappe guyyiyan, Balaami denddidi, ba soo simmiis; Baalaaqikka ba ogiyaa biis.

English Sentences: And Israel abode in Shittim, and the people began to commit whoredom with the daughters of Moab.
Wolaitta Sentences: Israa7eelati SHiixima giyoosan dunkkaanido wode, asai Moo7aaba biittaa maccaasatuura shaaramuxettaa doommiis.

English Sentences: And they called the people unto the sacrifices of their gods: and the people did eat, and bowed down to their gods.
Wolaitta Sentences: He maccaasati bantta xoossatu yarshshuwaa maanau eta shoobbidosona; shoobbin eti miidi, eta xoossatuyyo goinnidosona.

English Sentences: And Israel joined himself unto Baalpeor: and the anger of the LORD was kindled against Israel.
Wolaitta Sentences: Israa7eelati Pa7oora Ba7aala giyo eeqaa kaallido gishshau, GODAA hanqqoi eta bollan eexxi kiyiis.

English Sentences: And the LORD said unto Moses, Take all the heads of the people, and hang them up before the LORD against the sun, that the fierce anger of the LORD may be turned away from Israel.
Wolaitta Sentences: Yaatin GODAI Muusa, "GODAA hanqqoi Israa7eelappe wora simmana mala, ha asaa kaalettiyaageeta ubbaa efaada, seeta gallassi GODAA sinttan kaqqa" yaagiis.

English Sentences: And Moses said unto the judges of Israel, Slay ye every one his men that were joined unto Baalpeor.
Wolaitta Sentences: Yaagin Muusee Israa7eela daannata, "Pa7oora Ba7aala giyo eeqaayyo goinnida intte asaa ubbaa intte huuphiyan huuphiyan worite" yaagiis.

English Sentences: And, behold, one of the children of Israel came and brought unto his brethren a Midianitish woman in the sight of Moses, and in the sight of all the congregation of the children of Israel, who were weeping before the door of the tabernacle of the congregation.
Wolaitta Sentences: Muuseenne Israa7eela maabarai ubbai Xoossaa Dunkkaaniyaa penggen yeekkishin, Israa7eelatuppe issoi Midiyaama biittaa maccaasiyo eta sinttaara aattidi, ba keettaa asaakko ehiis.

English Sentences: And when Phinehas, the son of Eleazar, the son of Aaron the priest, saw it, he rose up from among the congregation, and took a javelin in his hand;
Wolaitta Sentences: Qeesiyaa Aaroona na7aa El77aazara na7ai Piinihaasi hegaa be7ido wode, maabaraa giddoppe denddidi, tooraa ba kushiyan oiqqidi,

English Sentences: And he went after the man of Israel into the tent, and thrust both of them through, the man of Israel, and the woman through her belly. So the plague was stayed from the children of Israel.
Wolaitta Sentences: he Israa7eela bitaniyaa kaallidi, dunkkaaniyaa giddo geliis. Gelidi Israa7eela bitaniyaanne mishiriyoonne naa77aakka tooran caddidi, kantti kessiis. Hegaadan hanin, boshai Israa7eelatuppe qaarettiis;

English Sentences: And those that died in the plague were twenty and four thousand.
Wolaitta Sentences: shin he boshan haiqqida asai laatamanne oiddu sha7a.

English Sentences: And the LORD spake unto Moses, saying,
Wolaitta Sentences: Hegaappe guyyiyan, GODAI Muusa hagaadan yaagiis;

English Sentences: Phinehas, the son of Eleazar, the son of Aaron the priest, hath turned my wrath away from the children of Israel, while he was zealous for my sake among them, that I consumed not the children of Israel in my jealousy.
Wolaitta Sentences: "Qeesiyaa Aaroona na7aa El77aazara na7ai Piinihaasi Israa7eela asaa giddon taani ta bonchchuwau mishettiyoogaadan mishettido gishshau, eta bolli taani hanqqettido hanqqoi dochchiis; taanikka eta ta hanqquwan xaissabeikke.

English Sentences: Wherefore say, Behold, I give unto him my covenant of peace:
Wolaitta Sentences: Hegaa gishshau, taani ta sarotettaa maachchaa aara maacettiyoogaa Piinihaasayyo neeni oda.

English Sentences: And he shall have it, and his seed after him, even the covenant of an everlasting priesthood; because he was zealous for his God, and made an atonement for the children of Israel.
Wolaitta Sentences: I ba Xoossaa bonchchuwau mishettido gishshaunne Israa7eela asaayyo atto giissido gishshau, inne a zerettati merinau qeese gidana" yaagiis.

English Sentences: Now the name of the Israelite that was slain, even that was slain with the Midianitish woman, was Zimri, the son of Salu, a prince of a chief house among the Simeonites.
Wolaitta Sentences: Midiyaama biittaa mishireera worido Israa7eela bitaniyaa sunttai Saalu na7aa Zimira; Saalu Simoona zaretun issi yaraa halaqaa.

English Sentences: And the name of the Midianitish woman that was slain was Cozbi, the daughter of Zur; he was head over a people, and of a chief house in Midian.
Wolaitta Sentences: Haiqqida Midiyaama biittaa mishiree sunttai Kozibo; i aawai Xuuri Midiyaamatu yaraa halaqaa.

English Sentences: And the LORD spake unto Moses, saying,
Wolaitta Sentences: GODAI Muusa hagaadan yaagiis;

English Sentences: Vex the Midianites, and smite them:
Wolaitta Sentences: "Midiyaama biittaa asata morkkite; morkkidi eta worite.

English Sentences: For they vex you with their wiles, wherewith they have beguiled you in the matter of Peor, and in the matter of Cozbi, the daughter of a prince of Midian, their sister, which was slain in the day of the plague for Peor's sake.
Wolaitta Sentences: Aissi giikko, eti inttena Pa7ooran cimmidi, inttessi morkke gididosona; qassi boshaa gallassi Pa7ooran worido mishiree, Midiyaamatu yaraa halaqaa na7ee Kozibi gaasuwan eti inttena morkkidosona" yaagiis.

English Sentences: And it came to pass after the plague, that the LORD spake unto Moses and unto Eleazar the son of Aaron the priest, saying,
Wolaitta Sentences: Boshaappe guyyiyan, GODAI Muusanne qeesiyaa Aaroona na7aa El77aazara,

English Sentences: Take the sum of all the congregation of the children of Israel, from twenty years old and upward, throughout their fathers' house, all that are able to go to war in Israel.
Wolaitta Sentences: "Yelettoosappe laatamu laittanne hegaappe bollaara de7iya Israa7eelata, olau baanau danddayiyaageeta ubbata, eta keettan keettan qoodite" yaagiis.

English Sentences: And Moses and Eleazar the priest spake with them in the plains of Moab by Jordan near Jericho, saying,
Wolaitta Sentences: Yaagin Muuseenne qeesee El77aazari Yorddaanoosa SHaafaappe hefintta baggaara, Yarkko matan, Moo7aaba Dembban etaara haasayiiddi,

English Sentences: Take the sum of the people, from twenty years old and upward; as the LORD commanded Moses and the children of Israel, which went forth out of the land of Egypt.
Wolaitta Sentences: "GODAI Muusa azazidoogaadan, yelettoosappe laatamu laittanne hegaappe bollaara de7iya asaa qoodite" yaagidosona. Gibxxeppe kiyida Israa7eelati hageeta:

English Sentences: Reuben, the eldest son of Israel: the children of Reuben; Hanoch, of whom cometh the family of the Hanochites: of Pallu, the family of the Palluites:
Wolaitta Sentences: Israa7eela baira na7aa Roobeela zareti: Hanooka yarata, Paalu yarata,

English Sentences: Of Hezron, the family of the Hezronites: of Carmi, the family of the Carmites.
Wolaitta Sentences: Hexiroona yaratanne Karmma yarata.

English Sentences: These are the families of the Reubenites: and they that were numbered of them were forty and three thousand and seven hundred and thirty.
Wolaitta Sentences: Hageeti Roobeela zareta; eti muleera 43,730.

English Sentences: And the sons of Pallu; Eliab.
Wolaitta Sentences: Paalu na7ai Eli7aaba;

English Sentences: And the sons of Eliab; Nemuel, and Dathan, and Abiram. This is that Dathan and Abiram, which were famous in the congregation, who strove against Moses and against Aaron in the company of Korah, when they strove against the LORD:
Wolaitta Sentences: Eli7aaba attuma naati Nemu7eela, Daataananne Abiiraama; ha Daataaninne Abiiraami maabarai dooridoogeeta. Eti Qoraahaaranne a kaalliyaageetuura zuppetidi, Muuse bolli, Aaroona bollinne GODAA bolli makkalidosona.

English Sentences: And the earth opened her mouth, and swallowed them up together with Korah, when that company died, what time the fire devoured two hundred and fifty men: and they became a sign.
Wolaitta Sentences: Biittai dooyettidi, eta Qoraahaara issippe mittiis; eta kaalliya naa77u xeetanne ishatamu asaa tamai min haiqqidosona. Yaatin eti asi be7idi duuxxiyo malaata gididosona.

English Sentences: Notwithstanding the children of Korah died not.
Wolaitta Sentences: SHin Qoraaha attuma naati he gallassi haiqqibookkona.

English Sentences: The sons of Simeon after their families: of Nemuel, the family of the Nemuelites: of Jamin, the family of the Jaminites: of Jachin, the family of the Jachinites:
Wolaitta Sentences: Simoona zareti bantta yaran yaran: Nemu7eela yarata, Yaamiina yarata, Yaakiina yarata,

English Sentences: Of Zerah, the family of the Zarhites: of Shaul, the family of the Shaulites.
Wolaitta Sentences: Zaraaha yaratanne SHaa7ula yarata.

English Sentences: These are the families of the Simeonites, twenty and two thousand and two hundred.
Wolaitta Sentences: Hageeti Simoona zareta; eti muleera 22,200.

English Sentences: The children of Gad after their families: of Zephon, the family of the Zephonites: of Haggi, the family of the Haggites: of Shuni, the family of the Shunites:
Wolaitta Sentences: Gaada zareti bantta yaran yaran: Xafoona yarata, Hagga yarata, SHuuna yarata,

English Sentences: Of Ozni, the family of the Oznites: of Eri, the family of the Erites:
Wolaitta Sentences: Oozina yarata, Eera yarata,

English Sentences: Of Arod, the family of the Arodites: of Areli, the family of the Arelites.
Wolaitta Sentences: Arooda yaratanne Ar77eela yarata.

English Sentences: These are the families of the children of Gad according to those that were numbered of them, forty thousand and five hundred.
Wolaitta Sentences: Hageeti Gaada zareta; eti muleera 40,500.

English Sentences: The sons of Judah were Er and Onan: and Er and Onan died in the land of Canaan.
Wolaitta Sentences: Yihudaa attuma naati Eeranne Oonaana; shin eti Kanaane biittan haiqqidosona.

English Sentences: And the sons of Judah after their families were; of Shelah, the family of the Shelanites: of Pharez, the family of the Pharzites: of Zerah, the family of the Zarhites.
Wolaitta Sentences: Yihudaa zareti bantta yaran yaran: SHeela yarata, Paareesa yaratanne Zaraaha yarata.

English Sentences: And the sons of Pharez were; of Hezron, the family of the Hezronites: of Hamul, the family of the Hamulites.
Wolaitta Sentences: Paareesa zareti Hexiroona yaratanne Hamuula yarata.

English Sentences: These are the families of Judah according to those that were numbered of them, threescore and sixteen thousand and five hundred.
Wolaitta Sentences: Hageeti Yihudaa zareta; eti muleera 76,500.

English Sentences: Of the sons of Issachar after their families: of Tola, the family of the Tolaites: of Pua, the family of the Punites:
Wolaitta Sentences: Yisaakoora zareti bantta yaran yaran: Tolaa7a yarata, Puuwa yarata,

English Sentences: Of Jashub, the family of the Jashubites: of Shimron, the family of the Shimronites.
Wolaitta Sentences: Yaashuuba yaratanne SHimiroona yarata.

English Sentences: These are the families of Issachar according to those that were numbered of them, threescore and four thousand and three hundred.
Wolaitta Sentences: Hageeti Yisaakoora zareta; eti muleera 64,300.

English Sentences: Of the sons of Zebulun after their families: of Sered, the family of the Sardites: of Elon, the family of the Elonites: of Jahleel, the family of the Jahleelites.
Wolaitta Sentences: Zaabiloona zareti bantta yaran yaran: Sereeda yarata, Eloona yaratanne Yaahila7eela yarata.

English Sentences: These are the families of the Zebulunites according to those that were numbered of them, threescore thousand and five hundred.
Wolaitta Sentences: Hageeti Zaabiloona zareta; eti muleera 60,500.

English Sentences: The sons of Joseph after their families were Manasseh and Ephraim.
Wolaitta Sentences: Minaasenne Efireema aawaa Yooseefa zareti hagaappe kaallidi xaafettidosona.

English Sentences: Of the sons of Manasseh: of Machir, the family of the Machirites: and Machir begat Gilead: of Gilead come the family of the Gileadites.
Wolaitta Sentences: Minaase zareti Minaase na7aa Maakiira yarata, Maakiiri na7aa Gala7aade yaratanne Gala7aade naatu yarata.

English Sentences: These are the sons of Gilead: of Jeezer, the family of the Jeezerites: of Helek, the family of the Helekites:
Wolaitta Sentences: Gala7aade zareti I7eezera yarata, Heleeqa yarata,

English Sentences: And of Asriel, the family of the Asrielites: and of Shechem, the family of the Shechemites:
Wolaitta Sentences: Asiri7eela yarata, SHekeema yarata,

English Sentences: And of Shemida, the family of the Shemidaites: and of Hepher, the family of the Hepherites.
Wolaitta Sentences: SHamidaa7a yaratanne Hefeera yarata.

English Sentences: And Zelophehad the son of Hepher had no sons, but daughters: and the names of the daughters of Zelophehad were Mahlah, and Noah, Hoglah, Milcah, and Tirzah.
Wolaitta Sentences: Hefeera na7ai Xalofihaadi macca naatu xalaalaa yeliis; ayyo attuma na7i baawa. Xalofihaada macca naatu sunttai Maahilo, No7o, Hoogilo, Milkkonne Tirxxo.

English Sentences: These are the families of Manasseh, and those that were numbered of them, fifty and two thousand and seven hundred.
Wolaitta Sentences: Hageeti Minaase zareta; eti muleera 52,700.

English Sentences: These are the sons of Ephraim after their families: of Shuthelah, the family of the Shuthalhites: of Becher, the family of the Bachrites: of Tahan, the family of the Tahanites.
Wolaitta Sentences: Efireema zareti bantta yaran yaran: SHutelaaha yarata, Bekeera yarata, Tahaana yaratanne

English Sentences: And these are the sons of Shuthelah: of Eran, the family of the Eranites.
Wolaitta Sentences: SHutelaaha na7aa Eraana yarata.

English Sentences: These are the families of the sons of Ephraim according to those that were numbered of them, thirty and two thousand and five hundred. These are the sons of Joseph after their families.
Wolaitta Sentences: Hageeti Efireema zareta; eti muleera 32,500. Yooseefa zareti bantta yaran yaran hegeeta.

English Sentences: The sons of Benjamin after their families: of Bela, the family of the Belaites: of Ashbel, the family of the Ashbelites: of Ahiram, the family of the Ahiramites:
Wolaitta Sentences: Biniyaama zareti bantta yaran yaran: Belaa7a yarata, Ashibeela yarata, Ahiraama yarata,

English Sentences: Of Shupham, the family of the Shuphamites: of Hupham, the family of the Huphamites.
Wolaitta Sentences: SHafufaama yarata, Hufaama yarata,

English Sentences: And the sons of Bela were Ard and Naaman: of Ard, the family of the Ardites: and of Naaman, the family of the Naamites.
Wolaitta Sentences: Belaa7a na7aa Arada yaratanne Belaa7a na7aa Naa7imaana yarata.

English Sentences: These are the sons of Benjamin after their families: and they that were numbered of them were forty and five thousand and six hundred.
Wolaitta Sentences: Hageeti Biniyaama zareta; eti muleera 45,600.

English Sentences: These are the sons of Dan after their families: of Shuham, the family of the Shuhamites. These are the families of Dan after their families.
Wolaitta Sentences: Daana zareti SHuhaama yarata.

English Sentences: All the families of the Shuhamites, according to those that were numbered of them, were threescore and four thousand and four hundred.
Wolaitta Sentences: SHuhaama yarati muleera 64,400.

English Sentences: Of the children of Asher after their families: of Jimna, the family of the Jimnites: of Jesui, the family of the Jesuites: of Beriah, the family of the Beriites.
Wolaitta Sentences: Aseera zareti bantta yaran yaran: Yimina yarata, Yishiwaaha yarata, Barii7a yarata,

English Sentences: Of the sons of Beriah: of Heber, the family of the Heberites: of Malchiel, the family of the Malchielites.
Wolaitta Sentences: Barii7a na7aa Hebeera yaratanne Barii7a na7aa Malkki7eela yarata.

English Sentences: And the name of the daughter of Asher was Sarah.
Wolaitta Sentences: Aseerau Seraaho giyo macca na7iyaa de7ausu.

English Sentences: These are the families of the sons of Asher according to those that were numbered of them; who were fifty and three thousand and four hundred.
Wolaitta Sentences: Hageeti Aseera zareta; eti muleera 53,400.

English Sentences: Of the sons of Naphtali after their families: of Jahzeel, the family of the Jahzeelites: of Guni, the family of the Gunites:
Wolaitta Sentences: Nifttaaleema zareti bantta yaran yaran: Yaa7izi7eela yarata, Guuna yarata,

English Sentences: Of Jezer, the family of the Jezerites: of Shillem, the family of the Shillemites.
Wolaitta Sentences: Yexeera yaratanne SHilleema yarata.

English Sentences: These are the families of Naphtali according to their families: and they that were numbered of them were forty and five thousand and four hundred.
Wolaitta Sentences: Hageeti Nifttaaleema zareta; eti muleera 45,400.

English Sentences: These were the numbered of the children of Israel, six hundred thousand and a thousand seven hundred and thirty.
Wolaitta Sentences: Qoodettida Israa7eela attuma asai muleera 601,730.

English Sentences: And the LORD spake unto Moses, saying,
Wolaitta Sentences: Qassikka GODAI Muusa,

English Sentences: Unto these the land shall be divided for an inheritance according to the number of names.
Wolaitta Sentences: "Ha zaretuyyo eta sunttaa sunttaa qoodaadan biittai shaahettidi, laata gididi etau imetto.

English Sentences: To many thou shalt give the more inheritance, and to few thou shalt give the less inheritance: to every one shall his inheritance be given according to those that were numbered of him.
Wolaitta Sentences: Qoodan coratuyyo eta coratettaa keenaa, qoodan guuttatuyyo eta guuttatettaa keenaa shaakkada imma. Ubbaikka xaafettida bantta qoodaa keenaa keenaa ekkona.

English Sentences: Notwithstanding the land shall be divided by lot: according to the names of the tribes of their fathers they shall inherit.
Wolaitta Sentences: SHin biittai saaman shaahetto; issi issi zaree laattiyo biittai eta aawaa zariyaa sunttaadan gido.

English Sentences: According to the lot shall the possession thereof be divided between many and few.
Wolaitta Sentences: Laata ubbai qoodan coratuppenne qoodan guuttatuppe gidduwan saaman shaahetto" yaagiis.

English Sentences: And these are they that were numbered of the Levites after their families: of Gershon, the family of the Gershonites: of Kohath, the family of the Kohathites: of Merari, the family of the Merarites.
Wolaitta Sentences: Bantta yaran yaran qoodettida Leewati hageeta: Gershshoona yarata, Qahaata yaratanne Maraara yarata.

English Sentences: These are the families of the Levites: the family of the Libnites, the family of the Hebronites, the family of the Mahlites, the family of the Mushites, the family of the Korathites. And Kohath begat Amram.
Wolaitta Sentences: Hageetikka qassi Leewatu yarata: Liibina yarata, Kebroona yarata, Maahila yarata, Musha yaratanne Qoraaha yarata. Qahaati Amiraama yeliis.

English Sentences: And the name of Amram's wife was Jochebed, the daughter of Levi, whom her mother bare to Levi in Egypt: and she bare unto Amram Aaron and Moses, and Miriam their sister.
Wolaitta Sentences: Amiraama keettaayee sunttai Yokebeedo; a Gibxxen Leewayyo yelettida na7iyo. A Amiraamayyo Aaroona, Muusanne eta michchiyo Miiriyaamo yelaasu.

English Sentences: And unto Aaron was born Nadab, and Abihu, Eleazar, and Ithamar.
Wolaitta Sentences: Aarooni Nadaaba, Abiiha, El77aazaranne Itaamaara yeliis.

English Sentences: And Nadab and Abihu died, when they offered strange fire before the LORD.
Wolaitta Sentences: SHin GODAI azazibeenna tamaa a sinttan yarshshido wode, Nadaabinne Abiihu haiqqidosona.

English Sentences: And those that were numbered of them were twenty and three thousand, all males from a month old and upward: for they were not numbered among the children of Israel, because there was no inheritance given them among the children of Israel.
Wolaitta Sentences: Yelettoosappe issi aginanne hegaappe bollaara de7iya qoodettida attuma Leewati muleera laatamanne heezzu sha7a. Israa7eelatu gidduwan etau laattiyo biittai imettibeenna gishshau, eti Israa7eelatuura qoodettibookkona.

English Sentences: These are they that were numbered by Moses and Eleazar the priest, who numbered the children of Israel in the plains of Moab by Jordan near Jericho.
Wolaitta Sentences: Yorddaanoosa SHaafaappe hefintta baggaara, Yarkko matan, Moo7aaba Dembban Muuseenne qeesee El77aazari Israa7eelata qoodido wode, qoodettida asai hagaa.

English Sentences: But among these there was not a man of them whom Moses and Aaron the priest numbered, when they numbered the children of Israel in the wilderness of Sinai.
Wolaitta Sentences: Muuseenne qeesee Aarooni kase Siinaa Bazzuwan Israa7eelata qoodido wode, qoodettida asaappe harai atto mexi issi asinne attibeenna.

English Sentences: For the LORD had said of them, They shall surely die in the wilderness. And there was not left a man of them, save Caleb the son of Jephunneh, and Joshua the son of Nun.
Wolaitta Sentences: Aissi giikko, GODAI he Israa7eelatubaa odiiddi, "Eti bazzuwan tumu haiqqana" yaagi wottiis. Yifune na7aa Kaaleebappenne Nawe na7aa Yaasuppe attin, harai issi asinne attibeenna.

English Sentences: Then came the daughters of Zelophehad, the son of Hepher, the son of Gilead, the son of Machir, the son of Manasseh, of the families of Manasseh the son of Joseph: and these are the names of his daughters; Mahlah, Noah, and Hoglah, and Milcah, and Tirzah.
Wolaitta Sentences: Xalofihaada macca naati Maahilo, No7o, Hoogilo, Milkkonne Tirxxo. Xalofihaadi Hefeera na7aa; Hefeeri Gala7aade na7aa; Gala7aadee Maakira na7aa; Maakiri Minaase na7aa; Minaasee Yooseefa na7aa.

English Sentences: And they stood before Moses, and before Eleazar the priest, and before the princes and all the congregation, by the door of the tabernacle of the congregation, saying,
Wolaitta Sentences: Ha macca naati Xoossaa Dunkkaaniyaa penggen Muuse sinttan, qeesiyaa El77aazara sinttan, halaqatu sinttaaninne maabaraa ubbaa sinttan eqqidi, hagaadan yaagidosona;

English Sentences: Our father died in the wilderness, and he was not in the company of them that gathered themselves together against the LORD in the company of Korah; but died in his own sin, and had no sons.
Wolaitta Sentences: "Nu aawai bazzuwan haiqqiis; i ba nagaran haiqqiisippe attin, GODAA bolli denddida Qoraaha kaalliyaageetu giddon de7enna. Ayyo attuma na7i baawa.

English Sentences: Why should the name of our father be done away from among his family, because he hath no son? Give unto us therefore a possession among the brethren of our father.
Wolaitta Sentences: Attuma na7i ayyo bainnabaa gidikkonne, nu aawaa sunttai a dabbotu gidduwaappe aissi xayii? Nu aawaa ishanttu giddon nuuyyo laattiyo biittaa imma" yaagidosona.

English Sentences: And Moses brought their cause before the LORD.
Wolaitta Sentences: Yaagin Muusee eta oishaa GODAA sintti shiishshiis.

English Sentences: And the LORD spake unto Moses, saying,
Wolaitta Sentences: SHiishshin GODAI Muusa,

English Sentences: The daughters of Zelophehad speak right: thou shalt surely give them a possession of an inheritance among their father's brethren; and thou shalt cause the inheritance of their father to pass unto them.
Wolaitta Sentences: "Xalofihaada macca naati oichchidoogee likke; eta aawaa ishanttu giddon neeni etayyo laattiyo biittaa imma; a laatai eta gakko.

English Sentences: And thou shalt speak unto the children of Israel, saying, If a man die, and have no son, then ye shall cause his inheritance to pass unto his daughter.
Wolaitta Sentences: Qassi neeni Israa7eelata hagaadan yaaga; Issi asi attuma na7i bainnan haiqqiyaabaa gidikko, a biittaa a macca na7i laatto;

English Sentences: And if he have no daughter, then ye shall give his inheritance unto his brethren.
Wolaitta Sentences: macca na7ikka ayyo bainnabaa gidikko, a biittaa a ishantti laattona;

English Sentences: And if he have no brethren, then ye shall give his inheritance unto his father's brethren.
Wolaitta Sentences: ayyo ishantti bainnabaa gidikko, a aawaa ishantti laattona;

English Sentences: And if his father have no brethren, then ye shall give his inheritance unto his kinsman that is next to him of his family, and he shall possess it: and it shall be unto the children of Israel a statute of judgment, as the LORD commanded Moses.
Wolaitta Sentences: a aawaa ishanttikka bainnabaa gidikko, a zariyaappe ubbaappe matattiya dabbuwaa laatissa. Taani GODAI nena Muusa azazidoogaadan, hagee Israa7eelatuyyo higge gido yaaga" yaagiis.

English Sentences: And the LORD said unto Moses, Get thee up into this mount Abarim, and see the land which I have given unto the children of Israel.
Wolaitta Sentences: Hegaappe guyyiyan, GODAI Muusa, "Pude Abaarima Dereta kiyada, taani Israa7eela asaayyo immido biittaa be7a.

English Sentences: And when thou hast seen it, thou also shalt be gathered unto thy people, as Aaron thy brother was gathered.
Wolaitta Sentences: Be7idoogaappe guyyiyan, ne ishaa Aaroonadan neenikka haiqqada, ne maizzan gaittana.

English Sentences: For ye rebelled against my commandment in the desert of Zin, in the strife of the congregation, to sanctify me at the water before their eyes: that is the water of Meribah in Kadesh in the wilderness of Zin.
Wolaitta Sentences: Aissi giikko, Xiina Bazzuwan de7iya haattan asai ubbai makkalido wode, intte naa77aikka eta sinttan tana geeshshadan bonchchanau taayyo azazettibeekketa" yaagiis. Hegee haattai Xiina Bazzuwan, Qaadeesan de7iya Mariiba haattaa.

English Sentences: And Moses spake unto the LORD, saying,
Wolaitta Sentences: Muusee GODAA hagaadan yaagiis;

English Sentences: Let the LORD, the God of the spirits of all flesh, set a man over the congregation,
Wolaitta Sentences: "Abeet GODAU, asa ubbau de7uwaa immiya Xoossau, ne asai, GODAA asai henttanchchi bainna wude mala gidennaadan,

English Sentences: Which may go out before them, and which may go in before them, and which may lead them out, and which may bring them in; that the congregation of the LORD be not as sheep which have no shepherd.
Wolaitta Sentences: ha asaa sinttan kiyiyaanne geliya, etakka kaalettidi kessiyaanne gelissiya, issi asa ha maabaraa bolli sunttarkkii" yaagiis.

English Sentences: And the LORD said unto Moses, Take thee Joshua the son of Nun, a man in whom is the spirit, and lay thine hand upon him;
Wolaitta Sentences: Yaagin GODAI Muusa, "Ayyaanai an de7iyo Nawe na7aa Yaasa ekkada, ne kushiyaa a bolli wotta;

English Sentences: And set him before Eleazar the priest, and before all the congregation; and give him a charge in their sight.
Wolaitta Sentences: yaatada qeesiyaa El77aazara sinttaaninne maabara ubbaa sinttan essada, eti be7ishin suntta.

English Sentences: And thou shalt put some of thine honour upon him, that all the congregation of the children of Israel may be obedient.
Wolaitta Sentences: Israa7eelatu maabara ubbai ayyo azazettanaadan, ne maataappe ayyo shaakkada imma.

English Sentences: And he shall stand before Eleazar the priest, who shall ask counsel for him after the judgment of Urim before the LORD: at his word shall they go out, and at his word they shall come in, both he, and all the children of Israel with him, even all the congregation.
Wolaitta Sentences: Immin qeesiyaa El77aazara sinttan i eqqo; eqqin El77aazari Uriimiyan ayyo GODAA sheniyaa oichcho. Yaasunne Israa7eela maabarai ubbai El77aazara azazuwan kiyonanne a azazuwan gelona" yaagiis.

English Sentences: And Moses did as the LORD commanded him: and he took Joshua, and set him before Eleazar the priest, and before all the congregation:
Wolaitta Sentences: GODAI azazidoogaadan Muusee oottiis; Yaasa efiidi, qeesiyaa El77aazara sinttaaninne maabaraa ubbaa sinttan essiis.

English Sentences: And he laid his hands upon him, and gave him a charge, as the LORD commanded by the hand of Moses.
Wolaitta Sentences: GODAI azazidoogaadan, Muusee ba kushiyaa a bolli wottidi, a sunttiis.

English Sentences: And the LORD spake unto Moses, saying,
Wolaitta Sentences: GODAI Muusa,

English Sentences: Command the children of Israel, and say unto them, My offering, and my bread for my sacrifices made by fire, for a sweet savour unto me, shall ye observe to offer unto me in their due season.
Wolaitta Sentences: "Israa7eelata hagaadan yaagada azaza; Ta qumaa, tana tonggu giidi sawana mala, taman yarshshiyo ta yarshshuwaa keerido wodiyan wodiyan taayyo naagidi immite yaaga.

English Sentences: And thou shalt say unto them, This is the offering made by fire which ye shall offer unto the LORD; two lambs of the first year without spot day by day, for a continual burnt offering.
Wolaitta Sentences: Qassi neeni eta, GODAAYYO taman yarshshiyo yarshshoi hagaa: tilla bollaara de7iya, issi laitta gidido naa77u dorssa orggeta hachchi hachchi xuuggiyo yarshshuwaayyo yarshshite;

English Sentences: The one lamb shalt thou offer in the morning, and the other lamb shalt thou offer at even;
Wolaitta Sentences: dorssa orggetuppe issuwaa maallado, naa77anttuwaa omarssi yarshshite.

English Sentences: And a tenth part of an ephah of flour for a meat offering, mingled with the fourth part of an hin of beaten oil.
Wolaitta Sentences: Qassi hegaara issi litiro gidiya zaitiyan munaqettida issi kilo giraame muruta gisttiyaa xiilliyaa kattaa yarshshuwaassi yarshshite.

English Sentences: It is a continual burnt offering, which was ordained in mount Sinai for a sweet savour, a sacrifice made by fire unto the LORD.
Wolaitta Sentences: Hagee GODAA tonggu giidi sawana mala, Siinaa Deriyaa bollan azazettida, hachchi hachchi taman xuuggiyo yarshsho.

English Sentences: And the drink offering thereof shall be the fourth part of an hin for the one lamb: in the holy place shalt thou cause the strong wine to be poured unto the LORD for a drink offering.
Wolaitta Sentences: Hegaara yarshshiyo ushshaa yarshshoi issi dorssa orggiyaayyo issi litiro gidiya woine eessa. Ushshaa yarshshuwaa Geeshsha Sohuwan GODAAYYO gussite.

English Sentences: And the other lamb shalt thou offer at even: as the meat offering of the morning, and as the drink offering thereof, thou shalt offer it, a sacrifice made by fire, of a sweet savour unto the LORD.
Wolaitta Sentences: Omarssi naa77antto dorssa orggiyaa, maalladoogaa oottidoogaadan oottidi, kattaa yarshshuwaaranne ushshaa yarshshuwaara GODAA tonggu giidi sawana mala, taman yarshshite.

English Sentences: And on the sabbath day two lambs of the first year without spot, and two tenth deals of flour for a meat offering, mingled with oil, and the drink offering thereof:
Wolaitta Sentences: "Sambbata gallassan, tilla bollaara de7iya issi laitta gidido naa77u dorssaanne zaitiyan munaqettida naa77u kilo giraame gidiya muruta xiilliyaa kattaa yarshshonne ushshaa yarshsho oottidi yarshshite.

English Sentences: This is the burnt offering of every sabbath, beside the continual burnt offering, and his drink offering.
Wolaitta Sentences: Hachchi hachchi xuuggiyo yarshshuwaanne a ushshaa yarshshuwaa bolli, Sambbata gallassa ubban intte yarshshiyo xuuggiyo yarshshoi hagaa.

English Sentences: And in the beginnings of your months ye shall offer a burnt offering unto the LORD; two young bullocks, and one ram, seven lambs of the first year without spot;
Wolaitta Sentences: "Aginai xeeriyo gallassa ubban, naa77u mirggota, issi dorssa orggiyaanne issi laitta gidido laappun dorssa orggeta, ubbaikka tilla bollaara de7iyaageeta, xuuggiyo yarshsho oottidi, GODAAYYO yarshshite.

English Sentences: And three tenth deals of flour for a meat offering, mingled with oil, for one bullock; and two tenth deals of flour for a meat offering, mingled with oil, for one ram;
Wolaitta Sentences: Issi issi mirgguwaara zaitiyan munaqettida heezzu kilo giraame gidiya muruta gisttiyaa xiilliyaa, issi dorssa orggiyaara zaitiyan munaqettida naa77u kilo giraame gidiya muruta gisttiyaa xiilliyaanne

English Sentences: And a several tenth deal of flour mingled with oil for a meat offering unto one lamb; for a burnt offering of a sweet savour, a sacrifice made by fire unto the LORD.
Wolaitta Sentences: laappun dorssa maratuppe issi issi dorssa maraara zaitiyan munaqettida issi kilo giraame gidiya muruta gisttiyaa xiilliyaa kattaa yarshsho oottidi, GODAA tonggu giidi sawana mala, taman yarshshiyo yarshshuwaa yarshshite.

English Sentences: And their drink offerings shall be half an hin of wine unto a bullock, and the third part of an hin unto a ram, and a fourth part of an hin unto a lamb: this is the burnt offering of every month throughout the months of the year.
Wolaitta Sentences: Qassi ushshaa yarshshuwaayyo issi issi mirgguwaara naa77u litiro gidiya woine eessaa, issi dorssa orggiyaara issi litironne bagga woine eessaanne issi issi dorssa maraara issi litiro gidiya woine eessaa shiishshite. Hagee laittaa giddon aginai xeeriyo gallassa ubban yarshshiyo xuuggiyo yarshsho.

English Sentences: And one kid of the goats for a sin offering unto the LORD shall be offered, beside the continual burnt offering, and his drink offering.
Wolaitta Sentences: Hachchi hachchi xuuggiyo yarshshuwaanne a ushshaa yarshshuwaa bolli, issi deeshsha orggiyaa nagaraa yarshsho oottidi, GODAAYYO yarshshite.

English Sentences: And in the fourteenth day of the first month is the passover of the LORD.
Wolaitta Sentences: "Koiro aginan tammanne oiddantta gallassai GODAA Paasikaa bonchchiyo gallassa gido.

English Sentences: And in the fifteenth day of this month is the feast: seven days shall unleavened bread be eaten.
Wolaitta Sentences: Qassi he aginankka tammanne ichchashantta gallassan doommidi, Oittaa Baalai bonchchettees; hegaa gishshau, laappun gallassatun irshshoi gelibeenna oittaa miite.

English Sentences: In the first day shall be an holy convocation; ye shall do no manner of servile work therein:
Wolaitta Sentences: He gallassatuppe koiro gallassan geeshsha yaa7aa shiiqite; daafurssiya ooso aibanne oottoppite.

English Sentences: But ye shall offer a sacrifice made by fire for a burnt offering unto the LORD; two young bullocks, and one ram, and seven lambs of the first year: they shall be unto you without blemish:
Wolaitta Sentences: Naa77u mirggota, issi dorssa orggiyaanne issi laitta gidido laappun dorssa orggeta, ubbaikka tilla bollaara de7iyaageeta, taman yarshshiyo yarshsho oottidi, GODAAYYO yarshshite.

English Sentences: And their meat offering shall be of flour mingled with oil: three tenth deals shall ye offer for a bullock, and two tenth deals for a ram;
Wolaitta Sentences: Kattaa yarshshuwaayyo issi mirgguwaara zaitiyan munaqettida heezzu kilo giraame gidiya muruta gisttiyaa xiilliyaa, issi dorssa orggiyaara naa77u kilo giraame gidiya xiilliyaanne

English Sentences: A several tenth deal shalt thou offer for every lamb, throughout the seven lambs:
Wolaitta Sentences: laappun dorssa maratuppe issi issi maraara issi kilo giraame xiilliyaa yarshshite.

English Sentences: And one goat for a sin offering, to make an atonement for you.
Wolaitta Sentences: Qassi issi deeshsha orggiyaa nagaraa yarshshuwaassi, intte nagaraa atto giissanau yarshshite.

English Sentences: Ye shall offer these beside the burnt offering in the morning, which is for a continual burnt offering.
Wolaitta Sentences: Hachchi hachchi maallado xuuggiyo yarshshuwaanne a kattaa yarshshuwaa bolli,

English Sentences: After this manner ye shall offer daily, throughout the seven days, the meat of the sacrifice made by fire, of a sweet savour unto the LORD: it shall be offered beside the continual burnt offering, and his drink offering.
Wolaitta Sentences: sawuwaa tonggu giya qumaa taman yarshshiyo yarshshuwaa gujjidi, GODAAYYO yarshshite. Laappun gallassaayyo hegaadan oottite.

English Sentences: And on the seventh day ye shall have an holy convocation; ye shall do no servile work.
Wolaitta Sentences: Laappuntta gallassan qassi geeshsha yaa7aa shiiqite; daafurssiya ooso aibanne oottoppite.

English Sentences: Also in the day of the firstfruits, when ye bring a new meat offering unto the LORD, after your weeks be out, ye shall have an holy convocation; ye shall do no servile work:
Wolaitta Sentences: "Saaminttatu Baalaa gallassan intte GODAAYYO ooratta kattaa shiishshiyo wode, geeshsha yaa7aa shiiqite; daafurssiya ooso aibanne oottoppite.

English Sentences: But ye shall offer the burnt offering for a sweet savour unto the LORD; two young bullocks, one ram, seven lambs of the first year;
Wolaitta Sentences: Naa77u mirggota, issi dorssa orggiyaanne issi laitta gidido laappun dorssa orggeta sawuwaa tonggu giya xuuggiyo yarshsho oottidi, GODAAYYO yarshshite.

English Sentences: And their meat offering of flour mingled with oil, three tenth deals unto one bullock, two tenth deals unto one ram,
Wolaitta Sentences: Issi issi mirgguwaara zaitiyan munaqettida heezzu kilo giraame gidiya muruta gisttiyaa xiilliyaa, issi dorssa orggiyaara naa77u kilo giraame xiilliyaanne

English Sentences: A several tenth deal unto one lamb, throughout the seven lambs;
Wolaitta Sentences: laappun dorssa maratuppe issi issi maraara issi kilo giraame xiilliyaa kattaa yarshshuwaayyo yarshshite.

English Sentences: And her father hear her vow, and her bond wherewith she hath bound her soul, and her father shall hold his peace at her: then all her vows shall stand, and every bond wherewith she hath bound her soul shall stand.

English Sentences: And her husband heard it, and held his peace at her, and disallowed her not: then all her vows shall stand, and every bond wherewith she bound her soul shall stand.

English Sentences: Every vow, and every binding oath to afflict the soul, her husband may establish it, or her husband may make it void.

English Sentences: But if her husband altogether hold his peace at her from day to day; then he establisheth all her vows, or all her bonds, which are upon her: he confirmeth them, because he held his peace at her in the day that he heard them.

Wolaitta Sentences: GODAI Muusa,

English Sentences: So there were delivered out of the thousands of Israel, a thousand of every tribe, twelve thousand armed for war.

English Sentences: And they warred against the Midianites, as the LORD commanded Moses; and they slew all the males.

English Sentences: And they took all the spoil, and all the prey, both of men and of beasts.

English Sentences: And they brought the captives, and the prey, and the spoil, unto Moses, and Eleazar the priest, and unto the congregation of the children of Israel, unto the camp at the plains of Moab, which are by Jordan near Jericho.

English Sentences: And Moses, and Eleazar the priest, and all the princes of the congregation, went forth to meet them without the camp.
Wolaitta Sentences: Muusee, qeesee El77aazarinne maabaraa halaqati ubbai dunkkaanidosaappe gaxi etaara gaittanau kiyidosona.

English Sentences: And Moses was wroth with the officers of the host, with the captains over thousands, and captains over hundreds, which came from the battle.

English Sentences: And Moses said unto them, Have ye saved all the women alive?

English Sentences: Behold, these caused the children of Israel, through the counsel of Balaam, to commit trespass against the LORD in the matter of Peor, and there was a plague among the congregation of the LORD.
