English Sentences: Now therefore kill every male among the little ones, and kill every woman that hath known man by lying with him.
Wolaitta Sentences: Hegaa gishshau, ha77i attuma naata ubbaa worite; qassi attuma asaara zin77ida maccaasa ubbaa worite.

English Sentences: But all the women children, that have not known a man by lying with him, keep alive for yourselves.
Wolaitta Sentences: SHin attuma asaara zin77ibeenna macca naata ubbaa intteyyo ashshite.

English Sentences: And do ye abide without the camp seven days: whosoever hath killed any person, and whosoever hath touched any slain, purify both yourselves and your captives on the third day, and on the seventh day.
Wolaitta Sentences: Intte giddoppe asa worida uri woikko ahaa bochchida uri ooninne dunkkaanidosaappe gaxan laappun gallassaa utto; heezzantta gallassinne laappuntta gallassi inttenanne intte omooddidoogeeta geeshshite.

English Sentences: And purify all your raiment, and all that is made of skins, and all work of goats' hair, and all things made of wood.
Wolaitta Sentences: Qassi maayo ubbaanne galbbappe, deeshsha ikiseppenne mittappe oosettidabata ubbaa geeshshite" yaagiis.

English Sentences: And Eleazar the priest said unto the men of war which went to the battle, This is the ordinance of the law which the LORD commanded Moses;
Wolaitta Sentences: Yaagin qeesee El77aazari olaappe simmida olanchchata hagaadan yaagiis; "GODAI Muuseyyo immido higgiyaa maarai hagaa:

English Sentences: Only the gold, and the silver, the brass, the iron, the tin, and the lead,
Wolaitta Sentences: Worqqaa, biraa, nahaasiyaa, birataa, qorqqoruwaanne irssaasiyaa giyo birataa

English Sentences: Every thing that may abide the fire, ye shall make it go through the fire, and it shall be clean: nevertheless it shall be purified with the water of separation: and all that abideth not the fire ye shall make go through the water.
Wolaitta Sentences: taman meetettennabata ubbaa tama giddoora aattin, hegee geeyana. SHin hegee qassi tunatettaappe geeyiyo haattan geeyanau koshshees. Qassi taman meetettiyaabata ubbaa tunatettaappe geeyiyo haattan geeshshanau koshshees.

English Sentences: And ye shall wash your clothes on the seventh day, and ye shall be clean, and afterward ye shall come into the camp.
Wolaitta Sentences: Laappuntta gallassi intte maayuwaa meeccite; meeccidi inttekka geeyite. Hegaappe guyyiyan, dunkkaanidosaa gelite" yaagiis.

English Sentences: And the LORD spake unto Moses, saying,
Wolaitta Sentences: GODAI Muusa hagaadan yaagiis;

English Sentences: Take the sum of the prey that was taken, both of man and of beast, thou, and Eleazar the priest, and the chief fathers of the congregation:
Wolaitta Sentences: "Neeni, qeesee El77aazarinne maabaraa halaqati omoodettida asaanne mehiyaa ubbaa qoodite.

English Sentences: And divide the prey into two parts; between them that took the war upon them, who went out to battle, and between all the congregation:
Wolaitta Sentences: Qoodidi olan olettida olanchchatuyyoonne attida maabaraayyo naa77u kessidi shaakkite.

English Sentences: And levy a tribute unto the Lord of the men of war which went out to battle: one soul of five hundred, both of the persons, and of the beeves, and of the asses, and of the sheep:
Wolaitta Sentences: Olettida olanchchata gakkida shaahuwaappe, asa gidin, miizza gidin, hareta, dorssata woikko deeshshata gidin, ichchashu xeetaappe issuwaa GODAAYYO giiraa giirite.

English Sentences: Take it of their half, and give it unto Eleazar the priest, for an heave offering of the LORD.
Wolaitta Sentences: Eta gakkida baggaappe ekkido giiraa GODAA gishshaadan qeesiyaa El77aazarayyo immite.

English Sentences: And of the children of Israel's half, thou shalt take one portion of fifty, of the persons, of the beeves, of the asses, and of the flocks, of all manner of beasts, and give them unto the Levites, which keep the charge of the tabernacle of the LORD.
Wolaitta Sentences: Hinkko Israa7eelata gakkida shaahuwaappe, asa gidin, miizza gidin, hareta, dorssata, woikko deeshshata gidin, mehetu ubbaappe ishatamaappe issuwaa ekkite; ekkidi hegaa GODAA Dunkkaaniyau aawatiya Leewatuyyo immite" yaagiis.

English Sentences: And Moses and Eleazar the priest did as the LORD commanded Moses.
Wolaitta Sentences: Yaagin Muuseenne qeesee El77aazari GODAI azazidoogaadan oottidosona.

English Sentences: Even of the children of Israel's half, Moses took one portion of fifty, both of man and of beast, and gave them unto the Levites, which kept the charge of the tabernacle of the LORD; as the LORD commanded Moses.
Wolaitta Sentences: Israa7eela maabaraa gakkida shaahuwaappe ishatamu ishatamu asaappe issuwaanne ishatamu ishatamu mehiyaappe issuwaa Muusee ekkidi, GODAI bana azazidoogaadan, Xoossaa Dunkkaaniyau aawatiya Leewatuyyo immiis.

English Sentences: And the officers which were over thousands of the host, the captains of thousands, and captains of hundreds, came near unto Moses:
Wolaitta Sentences: Hegaappe guyyiyan, ola gadaawati, shaalaqatinne mato halaqati Muusekko yiidosona.

English Sentences: And they said unto Moses, Thy servants have taken the sum of the men of war which are under our charge, and there lacketh not one man of us.
Wolaitta Sentences: Yiidi eti Muusa, "Nuuni ne ashkkarati nu azazuwaa garssan de7iya olanchchata qoodin, issoinne paccibeenna.

English Sentences: We have therefore brought an oblation for the LORD, what every man hath gotten, of jewels of gold, chains, and bracelets, rings, earrings, and tablets, to make an atonement for our souls before the LORD.
Wolaitta Sentences: GODAI nu shemppuwaa ashshido gishshau, nuuni huuphiyan huuphiyan ekkido worqqa alleeqota, kushe sagaayota, toho albbota, migidota, haitta gutichchatanne qooriyan aattiyo gujjumata GODAAYYO imuwaa ehiida" yaagidosona.

English Sentences: And Moses and Eleazar the priest took the gold of them, even all wrought jewels.
Wolaitta Sentences: Muuseenne qeesee El77aazari worqqa alleeqota ubbaa etappe ekkidosona.

English Sentences: And all the gold of the offering that they offered up to the LORD, of the captains of thousands, and of the captains of hundreds, was sixteen thousand seven hundred and fifty shekels.
Wolaitta Sentences: SHaalaqatinne mato halaqati ehiidi GODAAYYO immido worqqai ubbai naa77u xeetu kilo giraame gidiyaagaa.

English Sentences: (For the men of war had taken spoil, every man for himself.)
Wolaitta Sentences: SHin hara olanchchati ubbai bantta omooduwaa omooduwaa banttau ekkidosona.

English Sentences: And Moses and Eleazar the priest took the gold of the captains of thousands and of hundreds, and brought it into the tabernacle of the congregation, for a memorial for the children of Israel before the LORD.
Wolaitta Sentences: Muuseenne qeesee El77aazari shaalaqatuppenne mato halaqatuppe ekkido worqqaa GODAA sinttan Israa7eela asaa hassayissana mala, Xoossaa Dunkkaaniyaa giddo gelissidosona.

English Sentences: Now the children of Reuben and the children of Gad had a very great multitude of cattle: and when they saw the land of Jazer, and the land of Gilead, that, behold, the place was a place for cattle;
Wolaitta Sentences: Roobeela zaretuyyoonne Gaada zaretuyyo keehi daro mehee de7ees. Eti Yaa7izeera biittainne Gala7aade biittai meheyyo injje gidiyoogaa be7idosona.

English Sentences: The children of Gad and the children of Reuben came and spake unto Moses, and to Eleazar the priest, and unto the princes of the congregation, saying,
Wolaitta Sentences: Be7idi eti Muusekko, qeesiyaa El77aazarakkonne maabaraa halaqatukko yiidi, eta hagaadan yaagidosona;

English Sentences: Ataroth, and Dibon, and Jazer, and Nimrah, and Heshbon, and Elealeh, and Shebam, and Nebo, and Beon,
Wolaitta Sentences: "GODAI Israa7eela asan xoonissido biittati, Axaarooti, Dibooni, Yaa7izeeri, Niimiri, Hasebooni, Eli7aali, Seebimi, Naboinne Ba7ooni mehiyaayyo injje biitta;

English Sentences: Even the country which the LORD smote before the congregation of Israel, is a land for cattle, and thy servants have cattle:
Wolaitta Sentences: nuuyyo intte ashkkaratuyyo mehee de7ees.

English Sentences: Wherefore, said they, if we have found grace in thy sight, let this land be given unto thy servants for a possession, and bring us not over Jordan.
Wolaitta Sentences: Nuuni inttena ufaissidabaa gidikko, ha biittati nuussi intte ashkkaratussi laata gade gididi imettona. Nuna Yorddaanoosa SHaafaa hefintti pinttoppite" yaagidosona.

English Sentences: And Moses said unto the children of Gad and to the children of Reuben, Shall your brethren go to war, and shall ye sit here?
Wolaitta Sentences: Yaagin Muusee Gaada zaretanne Roobeela zareta hagaadan yaagiis; "Hara Israa7eela asai olaa biyo wode, intte hagan uttuuteetii?

English Sentences: And wherefore discourage ye the heart of the children of Israel from going over into the land which the LORD hath given them?
Wolaitta Sentences: GODAI etayyo immido biittaa Israa7eelati pinnennaadan, intte aibissi eta wozanaa shugisseetii?

English Sentences: Thus did your fathers, when I sent them from Kadeshbarnea to see the land.
Wolaitta Sentences: Qaadeesa Barnneppe he biittaa wochchi xeellanau intte aawata taani yeddido wode, etikka hagaadan oottidosona.

English Sentences: For when they went up unto the valley of Eshcol, and saw the land, they discouraged the heart of the children of Israel, that they should not go into the land which the LORD had given them.
Wolaitta Sentences: Waanidi giikko, eti Eshkkoola Zanggaaraa kiyidi, he biittaa xeellido wode, Israa7eelati GODAI etayyo immido biittaa gelenna mala, eti Israa7eelatu wozanaa shugissidosona.

English Sentences: And the LORD's anger was kindled the same time, and he sware, saying,
Wolaitta Sentences: GODAI he gallassi hanqquwaa eexxi kiyidi, hagaadan yaagidi caaqqiis;

English Sentences: Surely none of the men that came up out of Egypt, from twenty years old and upward, shall see the land which I sware unto Abraham, unto Isaac, and unto Jacob; because they have not wholly followed me:
Wolaitta Sentences: GODAA bantta kumetta wozanaappe kaallida Qeniiziyaa Yifune na7aa Kaaleebappenne Nawe na7aa Yaasuppe attin, yelettoosappe laatamu laittanne hegaappe bollaara de7iya attuma asan Gibxxe biittaappe kiyidaageetuppe issoinne, taani Abrahaamayyo, Yisaaqayyoonne Yaaqoobayyo immanau caaqqido biittaa be7enna.

English Sentences: Save Caleb the son of Jephunneh the Kenezite, and Joshua the son of Nun: for they have wholly followed the LORD.
Wolaitta Sentences: Aissi giikko, eti tana bantta kumetta wozanaappe kaallibookkona yaagidi caaqqiis.

English Sentences: And the LORD's anger was kindled against Israel, and he made them wander in the wilderness forty years, until all the generation, that had done evil in the sight of the LORD, was consumed.
Wolaitta Sentences: GODAA hanqqoi Israa7eela bolli eexxi kiyiis; yaatin GODAA sinttan iitaa oottida he yeleta ubbai wuri xayana gakkanaassi, bazzuwan oitamu laittaa i eta toilayiis.

English Sentences: And, behold, ye are risen up in your fathers' stead, an increase of sinful men, to augment yet the fierce anger of the LORD toward Israel.
Wolaitta Sentences: Inttenoo, nagaranchcha yeletatoo, GODAI Israa7eela bolli gujji hanqquwaa eexxi kiyanaadan, intte intte aawatu sohuwan ha77i eqqideta.

English Sentences: For if ye turn away from after him, he will yet again leave them in the wilderness; and ye shall destroy all this people.
Wolaitta Sentences: Intte GODAA kaalliyoogaa aggidi wora simmikko, i qassikka ba asaa bazzuwan aggi bayana. Yaatidi intte ha asaa ubbaa xaissana" yaagiis.

English Sentences: And they came near unto him, and said, We will build sheepfolds here for our cattle, and cities for our little ones:
Wolaitta Sentences: Yaagin eti Muuse mati yiidi, a hagaadan yaagidosona; "Nuuni hagan nu mehetuyyo dirssaa, nu naatuyyo katamata keexxana.

English Sentences: But we ourselves will go ready armed before the children of Israel, until we have brought them unto their place: and our little ones shall dwell in the fenced cities because of the inhabitants of the land.
Wolaitta Sentences: SHin nuuni ola miishshaa gixxidi, Israa7eela asaa eta sohuwaa gattana gakkanaashin olettanau baana. Hegaa keenan, ha biittan de7iya asatuppe naagettanau, nu naati gimbbettidi uttida katamatun de7ona.

English Sentences: We will not return unto our houses, until the children of Israel have inherited every man his inheritance.
Wolaitta Sentences: Israa7eelati ubbai bantta laataa laataa ekkana gakkanaassi, nuuni nu soo simmokko.

English Sentences: For we will not inherit with them on yonder side Jordan, or forward; because our inheritance is fallen to us on this side Jordan eastward.
Wolaitta Sentences: Nuuni nu laataa Yorddaanoosa SHaafaappe hafintta arshsho baggaara laattido gishshau, nuuni Yorddaanoosappe hefintta baggaara, yan etaara laataa laattokko" yaagidosona.

English Sentences: And Moses said unto them, If ye will do this thing, if ye will go armed before the LORD to war,
Wolaitta Sentences: Yaagin Muusee eta, "Intte hagaa oottikko, intte GODAA sinttan olaa baanau giigikkonne

English Sentences: And will go all of you armed over Jordan before the LORD, until he hath driven out his enemies from before him,
Wolaitta Sentences: intte olanchchati ubbai ola miishshaa gixxidi, GODAI ba morkketa ba sinttaappe yedettana gakkanaassi, Yorddaanoosa SHaafaa GODAA sinttan pinnikko,

English Sentences: And the land be subdued before the LORD: then afterward ye shall return, and be guiltless before the LORD, and before Israel; and this land shall be your possession before the LORD.
Wolaitta Sentences: GODAI he biittaa xoonidoogaappe guyyiyan, intte simmanau danddayeeta. Yaatikko, intte olettanau bessiya olaa GODAAYYOONNE Israa7eela asaayyo olettidi polideta giyoogaa. Qassi he biittai GODAA sinttan intteyyo laata biittaa gidana.

English Sentences: But if ye will not do so, behold, ye have sinned against the LORD: and be sure your sin will find you out.
Wolaitta Sentences: "SHin intte hegaadan oottennan ixxikko, GODAA bolli nagaraa ootteeta; simmi inttena intte nagarai gakkiyoogaa tumu erite.

English Sentences: Build you cities for your little ones, and folds for your sheep; and do that which hath proceeded out of your mouth.
Wolaitta Sentences: Intte intte naatuyyo katamata keexxite; intte dorssaa wudiyaayyookka birddeta giigissite; shin intte giidobaa aggennan oottite" yaagiis.

English Sentences: And the children of Gad and the children of Reuben spake unto Moses, saying, Thy servants will do as my lord commandeth.
Wolaitta Sentences: Yaagin Gaada zaretinne Roobeela zareti Muusa, "Nuuni ne ashkkarati neeni nu godai azazidoogaadan oottana.

English Sentences: Our little ones, our wives, our flocks, and all our cattle, shall be there in the cities of Gilead:
Wolaitta Sentences: Nu naatinne nu maccaasati, nu dorssatinne nu miizzati hagan Gala7aade katamatun de7ishshona.

English Sentences: But thy servants will pass over, every man armed for war, before the LORD to battle, as my lord saith.
Wolaitta Sentences: SHin nuuni ne ashkkarati, olau gixxida olanchchati ubbai, neeni nu godai giyoogaadan, olettanau GODAA sinttan Yorddaanoosa SHaafaa pinnana" yaagidosona.

English Sentences: So concerning them Moses commanded Eleazar the priest, and Joshua the son of Nun, and the chief fathers of the tribes of the children of Israel:
Wolaitta Sentences: Hegaa gishshau, Muusee qeesiyaa El77aazara, Nawe na7aa Yaasanne Israa7eela zaretu halaqata etabaa azaziis.

English Sentences: And Moses said unto them, If the children of Gad and the children of Reuben will pass with you over Jordan, every man armed to battle, before the LORD, and the land shall be subdued before you; then ye shall give them the land of Gilead for a possession:
Wolaitta Sentences: Muusee eta hagaadan yaagiis; "Gaada zaretinne Roobeela zareti ubbai ola miishshaa gixxidi, GODAA sinttan inttenaara Yorddaanoosa SHaafaa pinnikkonne intte he biittaa xoonikko, hegaappe guyyiyan, Gala7aade biittaa intte eta laatissite.

English Sentences: But if they will not pass over with you armed, they shall have possessions among you in the land of Canaan.
Wolaitta Sentences: SHin eti olaa miishshaa gixxidi, inttenaara pinnennan ixxikko, eti Kanaane biittaa inttenaara laattona" yaagiis.

English Sentences: And the children of Gad and the children of Reuben answered, saying, As the LORD hath said unto thy servants, so will we do.
Wolaitta Sentences: Yaagin Gaada zaretinne Roobeela zareti zaaridi, "Nuuni ne ashkkarati GODAI giidoogaa oottana.

English Sentences: We will pass over armed before the LORD into the land of Canaan, that the possession of our inheritance on this side Jordan may be ours.
Wolaitta Sentences: Ola miishshaa gixxidi, GODAA sinttan nuuni Kanaane biittaa gelanau pinnana; shin nuuni laattiyo laatai Yorddaanoosappe hafintta baggaara gidana" yaagidosona.

English Sentences: And Moses gave unto them, even to the children of Gad, and to the children of Reuben, and unto half the tribe of Manasseh the son of Joseph, the kingdom of Sihon king of the Amorites, and the kingdom of Og king of Bashan, the land, with the cities thereof in the coasts, even the cities of the country round about.
Wolaitta Sentences: Hegaa gishshau, Muusee Gaada zaretuyyo, Roobeela zaretuyyoonne Yooseefa na7aa Minaase zaretuppe baggaayyo Amooretu Kawuwaa Sihoona kawotettaanne Baasaane Kawuwaa Ooga kawotettaa, eta giddon de7iya katamatuura immiis.

English Sentences: And the children of Gad built Dibon, and Ataroth, and Aroer,
Wolaitta Sentences: Gaada zareti Diboona, Axaaroota, Aaro7era

English Sentences: And Atroth, Shophan, and Jaazer, and Jogbehah,
Wolaitta Sentences: Axirooti-SHofaana, Yaa7izeera, Yogibaaha,

English Sentences: And Bethnimrah, and Bethharan, fenced cities: and folds for sheep.
Wolaitta Sentences: Beeti-Niimiranne Beeti-Haaraana geetettiya gimbbiyan direttida katamata zaarettidi keexxidosona. Bantta dorssatuyyookka eti birddeta giigissidosona.

English Sentences: And the children of Reuben built Heshbon, and Elealeh, and Kirjathaim,
Wolaitta Sentences: Roobeela zaretikka Haseboona, Eli7aala, Qiriyaataimanne,

English Sentences: And Nebo, and Baalmeon, (their names being changed,) and Shibmah: and gave other names unto the cities which they builded.
Wolaitta Sentences: Naba, Ba7aali-Ma7oonanne Siibima geetettiya katamata zaaretti keexxidosona. Keexxidi he katamatuppe issootu issootu sunttaa laammidosona.

English Sentences: And the children of Machir the son of Manasseh went to Gilead, and took it, and dispossessed the Amorite which was in it.
Wolaitta Sentences: Minaase na7aa Maakira yarati Gala7aade biidi, oli oiqqidi, yan de7iya Amooreta yedettidosona.

English Sentences: And Moses gave Gilead unto Machir the son of Manasseh; and he dwelt therein.
Wolaitta Sentences: Hegaa gishshau, Minaase na7aa Maakira yaratuyyo Muusee Gala7aade biittaa immin, eti yan de7idosona.

English Sentences: And Jair the son of Manasseh went and took the small towns thereof, and called them Havothjair.
Wolaitta Sentences: Minaase zare gidiya Yaa7iiri biidi, eta oli oiqqidi, Yaa7iira katamata yaagidi sunttiis.

English Sentences: And Nobah went and took Kenath, and the villages thereof, and called it Nobah, after his own name.
Wolaitta Sentences: Nobaahi biidi, Qanaata katamaanne a yuushuwan de7iya moottata oli oiqqidi, ba sunttan Nobaaha giidi xeesiis.

English Sentences: These are the journeys of the children of Israel, which went forth out of the land of Egypt with their armies under the hand of Moses and Aaron.
Wolaitta Sentences: Israa7eelati Muuseenne Aarooni kaalettin, bantta citan citan Gibxxeppe kiyido wode, yaanidi hemettidosona.

English Sentences: And Moses wrote their goings out according to their journeys by the commandment of the LORD: and these are their journeys according to their goings out.
Wolaitta Sentences: GODAI azazin, eti baana beettaa doommido sohota Muusee xaafiis; eta beettaa maarai hagaa.

English Sentences: And they departed from Rameses in the first month, on the fifteenth day of the first month; on the morrow after the passover the children of Israel went out with an high hand in the sight of all the Egyptians.
Wolaitta Sentences: Koiro aginaayyo tammanne ichchashantta gallassi, Paasikaa bonchchiyo gallassaappe kaalliya gallassi denddidi, Gibxxe asai ubbai xeellishin, yayyennan Raamisappe kiyidosona.

English Sentences: For the Egyptians buried all their firstborn, which the LORD had smitten among them: upon their gods also the LORD executed judgments.
Wolaitta Sentences: He wode Gibxxe asai GODAI worido bantta baira naata moogoosona. Hagaadan oottidi, GODAI eta xoossatu bolli pirddaa ehiis.

English Sentences: And the children of Israel removed from Rameses, and pitched in Succoth.
Wolaitta Sentences: Israa7eelati Raamisappe denddidi, Sukkota giyo sohuwan dunkkaanidosona.

English Sentences: And they departed from Succoth, and pitched in Etham, which is in the edge of the wilderness.
Wolaitta Sentences: Sukkotappe denddidi, bazzuwaa xeeran de7iya Etaaman dunkkaanidosona.

English Sentences: And they removed from Etham, and turned again unto Pihahiroth, which is before Baalzephon: and they pitched before Migdol.
Wolaitta Sentences: Etaamappe denddidi, Ba7aali-Xafoonappe arshsho baggaara de7iya Pihaahiroota simmidi, Migidoola matan dunkkaanidosona.

English Sentences: And they departed from before Pihahiroth, and passed through the midst of the sea into the wilderness, and went three days' journey in the wilderness of Etham, and pitched in Marah.
Wolaitta Sentences: Pihaahirootappe denddidi, Zo7o Abbaa pinnidi, bazzuwaa biidosona. Etaama Bazzuwan heezzu gallassa ogiyaa hemettidi, Maaran dunkkaanidosona.

English Sentences: And they removed from Marah, and came unto Elim: and in Elim were twelve fountains of water, and threescore and ten palm trees; and they pitched there.
Wolaitta Sentences: Maarappe denddidi, tammanne naa77u pulttotinne laappun tammu zambbati de7iyo Eliima biidi, yan dunkkaanidosona.

English Sentences: And they removed from Elim, and encamped by the Red sea.
Wolaitta Sentences: Eliimappe denddidi, Zo7o Abbaa lanqqen dunkkaanidosona.

English Sentences: And they removed from the Red sea, and encamped in the wilderness of Sin.
Wolaitta Sentences: Zo7o Abbaa lanqqeppe denddidi, Siinaa Bazzuwan dunkkaanidosona.

English Sentences: And they took their journey out of the wilderness of Sin, and encamped in Dophkah.
Wolaitta Sentences: Siinaa Bazzuwaappe denddidi, Doofiqan dunkkaanidosona.

English Sentences: And they departed from Dophkah, and encamped in Alush.
Wolaitta Sentences: Doofiqappe denddidi, Aluushan dunkkaanidosona.

English Sentences: And they removed from Alush, and encamped at Rephidim, where was no water for the people to drink.
Wolaitta Sentences: Aluushappe denddidi, Rafiidiman dunkkaanidosona. Yan asaayyo uyanau haatti baawa.

English Sentences: And they departed from Rephidim, and pitched in the wilderness of Sinai.
Wolaitta Sentences: Rafiidimappe denddidi, Siinaa Bazzuwan dunkkaanidosona.

English Sentences: And they removed from the desert of Sinai, and pitched at Kibrothhattaavah.
Wolaitta Sentences: Siinaa Bazzuwaappe denddidi, Amuwaa Duufuwaa giyoosan dunkkaanidosona.

English Sentences: And they departed from Kibrothhattaavah, and encamped at Hazeroth.
Wolaitta Sentences: Amuwaa Duufuwaa giyoosaappe denddidi, Haxerootan dunkkaanidosona.

English Sentences: And they departed from Hazeroth, and pitched in Rithmah.
Wolaitta Sentences: Haxerootappe denddidi, Riitiman dunkkaanidosona.

English Sentences: And they departed from Rithmah, and pitched at Rimmonparez.
Wolaitta Sentences: Riitimappe denddidi, Rimmooni-Pereezan dunkkaanidosona.

English Sentences: And they departed from Rimmonparez, and pitched in Libnah.
Wolaitta Sentences: Rimmooni-Pereezappe denddidi, Liibinan dunkkaanidosona.

English Sentences: And they removed from Libnah, and pitched at Rissah.
Wolaitta Sentences: Liibinappe denddidi, Riissan dunkkaanidosona.

English Sentences: And they journeyed from Rissah, and pitched in Kehelathah.
Wolaitta Sentences: Riissappe denddidi, Qahelaatan dunkkaanidosona.

English Sentences: And they went from Kehelathah, and pitched in mount Shapher.
Wolaitta Sentences: Qahelaatappe denddidi, SHefaara Deriyan dunkkaanidosona.

English Sentences: And they removed from mount Shapher, and encamped in Haradah.
Wolaitta Sentences: SHefaara Deriyaappe denddidi, Haraadan dunkkaanidosona.

English Sentences: And they removed from Haradah, and pitched in Makheloth.
Wolaitta Sentences: Haraadappe denddidi, Maaqihelootan dunkkaanidosona.

English Sentences: And they removed from Makheloth, and encamped at Tahath.
Wolaitta Sentences: Maaqihelootappe denddidi, Tahaatan dunkkaanidosona.

English Sentences: And they departed from Tahath, and pitched at Tarah.
Wolaitta Sentences: Tahaatappe denddidi, Taaran dunkkaanidosona.

English Sentences: And they removed from Tarah, and pitched in Mithcah.
Wolaitta Sentences: Taarappe denddidi, Miitiqan dunkkaanidosona.

English Sentences: And they went from Mithcah, and pitched in Hashmonah.
Wolaitta Sentences: Miitiqappe denddidi, Hashimoonan dunkkaanidosona.

English Sentences: And they departed from Hashmonah, and encamped at Moseroth.
Wolaitta Sentences: Hashimoonappe denddidi, Moserootan dunkkaanidosona.

English Sentences: And they departed from Moseroth, and pitched in Benejaakan.
Wolaitta Sentences: Moserootappe denddidi, Bene-Yaa7iqaanan dunkkaanidosona.

English Sentences: And they removed from Benejaakan, and encamped at Horhagidgad.
Wolaitta Sentences: Bene-Yaa7iqaanappe denddidi, Hoori-Hagidigaadan dunkkaanidosona.

English Sentences: And they went from Horhagidgad, and pitched in Jotbathah.
Wolaitta Sentences: Hoori-Hagidigaadappe denddidi, Yoxibaatan dunkkaanidosona.

English Sentences: And they removed from Jotbathah, and encamped at Ebronah.
Wolaitta Sentences: Yoxibaatappe denddidi, Abroonan dunkkaanidosona.

English Sentences: And they departed from Ebronah, and encamped at Eziongaber.
Wolaitta Sentences: Abroonappe denddidi, Eexiyooni-Gaabiran dunkkaanidosona.

English Sentences: And they removed from Eziongaber, and pitched in the wilderness of Zin, which is Kadesh.
Wolaitta Sentences: Eexiyooni-Gaabirappe denddidi, Xiina Bazzuwan de7iya Qaadeesan dunkkaanidosona.

English Sentences: And they removed from Kadesh, and pitched in mount Hor, in the edge of the land of Edom.
Wolaitta Sentences: Qaadeesappe denddidi, Eedooma biittaa zawan de7iya Hoora Deriyan dunkkaanidosona.

English Sentences: And Aaron the priest went up into mount Hor at the commandment of the LORD, and died there, in the fortieth year after the children of Israel were come out of the land of Egypt, in the first day of the fifth month.
Wolaitta Sentences: Qeesee Aarooni GODAI azazin, Hoora Deriyaa huuphiyaa kiyiis; kiyidi Israa7eelati Gibxxe biittaappe kiyido oitamantta laittan, ichchashantta aginan, aginaayyo koiro gallassan yan haiqqiis.

English Sentences: And Aaron was an hundred and twenty and three years old when he died in mount Hor.
Wolaitta Sentences: Aarooni Hoora Deriyaa huuphiyan haiqqiyo wode, a laittai xeetanne laatammanne heezza.

English Sentences: And king Arad the Canaanite, which dwelt in the south in the land of Canaan, heard of the coming of the children of Israel.
Wolaitta Sentences: Neegeeba Bazzuwan, Kanaanen de7iya Araada giyoosaa kawoi Israa7eela asaa yuussaa siyiis.

English Sentences: And they departed from mount Hor, and pitched in Zalmonah.
Wolaitta Sentences: Israa7eelati Hoora Deriyaappe denddidi, Xalmmoonan dunkkaanidosona.

English Sentences: And they departed from Zalmonah, and pitched in Punon.
Wolaitta Sentences: Xalmmoonappe denddidi, Punoonan dunkkaanidosona.

English Sentences: And they departed from Punon, and pitched in Oboth.
Wolaitta Sentences: Punoonappe denddidi, Obootan dunkkaanidosona.

English Sentences: And they departed from Oboth, and pitched in Ijeabarim, in the border of Moab.
Wolaitta Sentences: Obootappe denddidi, Moo7aaba biittaa zawan de7iya Abaariman dunkkaanidosona.

English Sentences: And they departed from Iim, and pitched in Dibongad.
Wolaitta Sentences: Abaarimappe denddidi, Diboona-Gaadan dunkkaanidosona.

English Sentences: And they removed from Dibongad, and encamped in Almondiblathaim.
Wolaitta Sentences: Diboona-Gaadappe denddidi, Almmoona-Dibilaataiman dunkkaanidosona.

English Sentences: And they removed from Almondiblathaim, and pitched in the mountains of Abarim, before Nebo.
Wolaitta Sentences: Almmoona-Dibilaataimappe denddidi, Nabo Deriyaa matan Abaarima deretun dunkkaanidosona.

English Sentences: And they departed from the mountains of Abarim, and pitched in the plains of Moab by Jordan near Jericho.
Wolaitta Sentences: Abaarima deretuppe denddidi, Yarkkoppe hefinttaara, Yorddaanoosa SHaafaa matan de7iya Moo7aaba Dembban dunkkaanidosona.

English Sentences: And they pitched by Jordan, from Bethjesimoth even unto Abelshittim in the plains of Moab.
Wolaitta Sentences: Yorddaanoosa SHaafaa matan de7iya Moo7aaba Dembban, Beeti-Yashimootappenne SHiixima Zanggaaraappe gidduwan dunkkaanidosona.

English Sentences: And the LORD spake unto Moses in the plains of Moab by Jordan near Jericho, saying,
Wolaitta Sentences: Yarkko hefinttaara, Yorddaanoosa SHaafaa matan de7iya Moo7aaba Dembban GODAI Muusa hagaadan yaagiis;

English Sentences: Speak unto the children of Israel, and say unto them, When ye are passed over Jordan into the land of Canaan;
Wolaitta Sentences: "Israa7eelata neeni yaaga; Yorddaanoosa SHaafaa pinnidi, Kanaane biitti intte geliyo wode,

English Sentences: Then ye shall drive out all the inhabitants of the land from before you, and destroy all their pictures, and destroy all their molten images, and quite pluck down all their high places:
Wolaitta Sentences: he biittan de7iya asaa ubbaa intte sinttappe yedettite; yedettidi shuchchaappe masettida eta misileta ubbaanne seerissidi medhdhido eeqata ubbaa xaissite. Eti goinniyo xoqqa sohota ubbaakka laalite.

English Sentences: And ye shall dispossess the inhabitants of the land, and dwell therein: for I have given you the land to possess it.
Wolaitta Sentences: Taani intteyyo he biittaa laatau immido gishshau, he biittaa laattidi, an de7ite.

English Sentences: And ye shall divide the land by lot for an inheritance among your families: and to the more ye shall give the more inheritance, and to the fewer ye shall give the less inheritance: every man's inheritance shall be in the place where his lot falleth; according to the tribes of your fathers ye shall inherit.
Wolaitta Sentences: Intte zariyan zariyan saamaa kessidi, biittaa shaakkite. Qoodan corattiya zaretuyyo daro laataa immite; qoodan guuxxiya zaretuyyo guutta laataa immite. Saaman eta gakkida augeenne etaagaa gidana. Biittaa intte maizza aawatu zariyan zariyan shaakki ekkite.

English Sentences: But if ye will not drive out the inhabitants of the land from before you; then it shall come to pass, that those which ye let remain of them shall be pricks in your eyes, and thorns in your sides, and shall vex you in the land wherein ye dwell.
Wolaitta Sentences: "SHin he biittan de7iya asaa intte yedettennan aggikko, intte ashshidoogeeti intteyyo intte aifiyaayyo pincco, intte miyyiyaayyo aguntta gidana; intte de7ana biittan eti inttena waayissana.

English Sentences: Moreover it shall come to pass, that I shall do unto you, as I thought to do unto them.
Wolaitta Sentences: Intte eta yedettennan aggikko, eta bolli taani oottanau halchchidobaa intte bolli oottana yaagada yoota" yaagiis.

English Sentences: And the LORD spake unto Moses, saying,
Wolaitta Sentences: GODAI Muusa hagaadan yaagiis;

English Sentences: Command the children of Israel, and say unto them, When ye come into the land of Canaan; (this is the land that shall fall unto you for an inheritance, even the land of Canaan with the coasts thereof:)
Wolaitta Sentences: "Neeni Israa7eelata hagaadan yaagada azaza; Laatadan inttena gakkiya Kanaane biittaa zawai hagaa.

English Sentences: Then your south quarter shall be from the wilderness of Zin along by the coast of Edom, and your south border shall be the outmost coast of the salt sea eastward:
Wolaitta Sentences: Tohossa baggaara intte zawai Xiina Bazzuwaanne Eedooma zawaa gidana. Intte tohossa zawai Maxine Abbaa tohossaappe doommees;

English Sentences: And your border shall turn from the south to the ascent of Akrabbim, and pass on to Zin: and the going forth thereof shall be from the south to Kadeshbarnea, and shall go on to Hazaraddar, and pass on to Azmon:
Wolaitta Sentences: doommidi Aqirabiima pudettaara tohossa baggaara simmidi, Xiina Bazzuwaa kanttidi, Qaadeesa-Barnne tohossi gakkees; hegaappe Hadaari-Adaara kanttidi, Aximoona gakkees.

English Sentences: And the border shall fetch a compass from Azmon unto the river of Egypt, and the goings out of it shall be at the sea.
Wolaitta Sentences: Aximoonappe Gibxxe SHaafaakko simmidi, Meediteraane Abbaa gakkees.

English Sentences: And as for the western border, ye shall even have the great sea for a border: this shall be your west border.
Wolaitta Sentences: "Arggo baggaara intte zawai Meediteraane Abbaa gaxaa gidana.

English Sentences: And this shall be your north border: from the great sea ye shall point out for you mount Hor:
Wolaitta Sentences: "Huuphessa baggaara intte zawai Meediteraane Abbaappe Hoora Deriyaa sitti ootti malaatidi,

English Sentences: From mount Hor ye shall point out your border unto the entrance of Hamath; and the goings forth of the border shall be to Zedad:
Wolaitta Sentences: Hoora Deriyaappe Hamaata Pinuwaa gakkanaassa; hegaappe Xadaadan zawatees.

English Sentences: And the border shall go on to Ziphron, and the goings out of it shall be at Hazarenan: this shall be your north border.
Wolaitta Sentences: Qassi Zifiroona biidi, Haxaari-Enaana gakkees. Huuphessa baggaara intte zawai hagaa gidana.

English Sentences: And ye shall point out your east border from Hazarenan to Shepham:
Wolaitta Sentences: "Arshsho baggaara intte zawai Haxaari-Enaanappe SHafaama gakkanaassi sitti ootti malaatidi,

English Sentences: And the coast shall go down from Shepham to Riblah, on the east side of Ain; and the border shall descend, and shall reach unto the side of the sea of Chinnereth eastward:
Wolaitta Sentences: SHafaamappe biidi, Ainappe arshsho baggaara de7iya Ribila wodhdhidi, Galiila Abbaappe arshsho baggaara de7iya keraa gakkees.

English Sentences: And the border shall go down to Jordan, and the goings out of it shall be at the salt sea: this shall be your land with the coasts thereof round about.
Wolaitta Sentences: Hegaappe duge Yorddaanoosa SHaafaa wodhdhi zawatidi, Maxine Abbaa gakkees. Intte biittaa zawai ubba baggaarakka hagaa yaaga" yaagiis.

English Sentences: And Moses commanded the children of Israel, saying, This is the land which ye shall inherit by lot, which the LORD commanded to give unto the nine tribes, and to the half tribe:
Wolaitta Sentences: Yaagin Muusee Israa7eelata hagaadan yaagidi azaziis; "Saamaa yeggidi, intte laattana mala, uddufun zaretuyyoonne bagga zaretuyyo he biittai imettanaadan GODAI azaziis.

English Sentences: And the LORD spake unto Moses, saying,
Wolaitta Sentences: GODAI Muusa hagaadan yaagiis;

English Sentences: These are the names of the men which shall divide the land unto you: Eleazar the priest, and Joshua the son of Nun.
Wolaitta Sentences: "He biittaa intteyyo laata oottidi, shaakki immana asatu sunttai hagaa; qeesiyaa El77aazaranne Nawe na7aa Yaasa.

English Sentences: And ye shall take one prince of every tribe, to divide the land by inheritance.
Wolaitta Sentences: Qassi biittaa shaakkanau maaddana mala, zare ubbaappe issi issi halaqaa sunttite.

English Sentences: And the names of the men are these: Of the tribe of Judah, Caleb the son of Jephunneh.
Wolaitta Sentences: Eta sunttai hagaappe kaallidi de7iyaagaa. Zariyaa Halaqaa Yihudaa Yifune na7aa Kaaleeba

English Sentences: And of the tribe of the children of Simeon, Shemuel the son of Ammihud.
Wolaitta Sentences: Simoona Amihuuda na7aa SHalumi7eela

English Sentences: Of the tribe of Benjamin, Elidad the son of Chislon.
Wolaitta Sentences: Biniyaama Kisiloona na7aa Elddaada

English Sentences: And the prince of the tribe of the children of Dan, Bukki the son of Jogli.
Wolaitta Sentences: Daana Yoogila na7aa Buuqa

English Sentences: The prince of the children of Joseph, for the tribe of the children of Manasseh, Hanniel the son of Ephod.
Wolaitta Sentences: Yooseefa na7aa Minaase Efooda na7aa Hani7eela

English Sentences: And the prince of the tribe of the children of Ephraim, Kemuel the son of Shiphtan.
Wolaitta Sentences: Yooseefa na7aa Efireema SHifxxaana na7aa Qamu7eela

English Sentences: And the prince of the tribe of the children of Zebulun, Elizaphan the son of Parnach.
Wolaitta Sentences: Zaabiloona Parnnaaka na7aa Elxxaafaana

English Sentences: And the prince of the tribe of the children of Issachar, Paltiel the son of Azzan.
Wolaitta Sentences: Yisaakoora Azzaana na7aa Palxxi7eela

English Sentences: And the prince of the tribe of the children of Asher, Ahihud the son of Shelomi.
Wolaitta Sentences: Aseera SHalooma na7aa Ahihuuda

English Sentences: And the prince of the tribe of the children of Naphtali, Pedahel the son of Ammihud.
Wolaitta Sentences: Nifttaaleema Amihuuda na7aa Padaahi7eela

English Sentences: These are they whom the LORD commanded to divide the inheritance unto the children of Israel in the land of Canaan.
Wolaitta Sentences: Kanaane biittan Israa7eelatuyyo laataa shaakki immana mala, GODAI azazido asati hageeta" yaagiis.

English Sentences: And the LORD spake unto Moses in the plains of Moab by Jordan near Jericho, saying,
Wolaitta Sentences: Yarkko hefinttaara, Yorddaanoosa SHaafaa matan de7iya Moo7aaba Dembban, GODAI Muusa hagaadan yaagiis;

English Sentences: Command the children of Israel, that they give unto the Levites of the inheritance of their possession cities to dwell in; and ye shall give also unto the Levites suburbs for the cities round about them.
Wolaitta Sentences: "Israa7eelati bantta laataappe Leewatu de7ana katamatanne eta yuushuwan de7iya hentta gadeta immana mala, neeni eta azaza.

English Sentences: And the cities shall they have to dwell in; and the suburbs of them shall be for their cattle, and for their goods, and for all their beasts.
Wolaitta Sentences: He katamatun eti de7ona; hentta gadeti eta miizzaassa, eta dorssaassanne eta hara mehe ubbaassa gidona.

English Sentences: And the suburbs of the cities, which ye shall give unto the Levites, shall reach from the wall of the city and outward a thousand cubits round about.
Wolaitta Sentences: Intte Leewatuyyo immana katamaa yuushuwan de7iya hentta gadeti katamaa gimbbe dirssaappe karekko issi sha7u wara gidona.

English Sentences: And ye shall measure from without the city on the east side two thousand cubits, and on the south side two thousand cubits, and on the west side two thousand cubits, and on the north side two thousand cubits; and the city shall be in the midst: this shall be to them the suburbs of the cities.
Wolaitta Sentences: Katamaappe kareera, arshsho baggaara naa77u sha7u waraa, tohossa baggaara naa77u sha7u waraa, arggo baggaara naa77u sha7u waraanne huuphessa baggaara naa77u sha7u waraa likkite; yaatobare katamai giddo ginan de7ana. Leewati he heeraa bantta katamaayyo hentta gade oottona.

English Sentences: And among the cities which ye shall give unto the Levites there shall be six cities for refuge, which ye shall appoint for the manslayer, that he may flee thither: and to them ye shall add forty and two cities.
Wolaitta Sentences: "Leewatuyyo intte immana katamati, asa worida uri baqatidi attiyo usuppun katamata; hegeetu bolli gujjidi, oitamanne naa77u hara katamata etayyo immite.

English Sentences: So all the cities which ye shall give to the Levites shall be forty and eight cities: them shall ye give with their suburbs.
Wolaitta Sentences: Leewatuyyo intte muleera oitamanne hosppun katamata eta hentta gadetuura issippe immite.

English Sentences: And the cities which ye shall give shall be of the possession of the children of Israel: from them that have many ye shall give many; but from them that have few ye shall give few: every one shall give of his cities unto the Levites according to his inheritance which he inheriteth.
Wolaitta Sentences: Israa7eelatu laataappe Leewatuyyo intte immana katamati issi issi zaree laattidoogaa keena gidanau koshshees; cora asai de7iyo zariyaappe cora katamata ekkite; shin qoodan guutta asai de7iyo zariyaappe guutta katamata ekkite" yaagiis.

English Sentences: And the LORD spake unto Moses, saying,
Wolaitta Sentences: Hegaappe guyyiyan, GODAI Muusa hagaadan yaagiis;

English Sentences: Speak unto the children of Israel, and say unto them, When ye be come over Jordan into the land of Canaan;
Wolaitta Sentences: "Neeni Israa7eela asaa hagaadan yaaga; Yorddaanoosa SHaafaa pinnidi, Kanaane biittaa intte geliyo wode,

English Sentences: Then ye shall appoint you cities to be cities of refuge for you; that the slayer may flee thither, which killeth any person at unawares.
Wolaitta Sentences: erennan asa worida uri baqati biidi attana mala, katamata intteyyo doorite.

English Sentences: And they shall be unto you cities for refuge from the avenger; that the manslayer die not, until he stand before the congregation in judgment.
Wolaitta Sentences: Erennan asa woridaagee yaa7aa sintti pirddau eqqana gakkanaassi, suuttaa achchiyaagee a worenna mala, he katamati baqati attiyo soho gidona.

English Sentences: And of these cities which ye shall give six cities shall ye have for refuge.
Wolaitta Sentences: Ha intte immiyo usuppun katamati intteyyo baqati attiyo katamata gidona.

English Sentences: Ye shall give three cities on this side Jordan, and three cities shall ye give in the land of Canaan, which shall be cities of refuge.
Wolaitta Sentences: Yorddaanoosa SHaafaappe hafintta baggaara heezzu katamaanne Kanaane biittan heezzu katamata intte baqati attanau immite.

English Sentences: These six cities shall be a refuge, both for the children of Israel, and for the stranger, and for the sojourner among them: that every one that killeth any person unawares may flee thither.
Wolaitta Sentences: Ha usuppun katamati erennan asa worida Israa7eelati, hara dere asatinne eta giddon de7iya beteti baqatidi attiyo soho gidona.

English Sentences: And if he smite him with an instrument of iron, so that he die, he is a murderer: the murderer shall surely be put to death.
Wolaitta Sentences: "Issi asi issi asa birata miishshan shocin, he uri haiqqikko, hegee shemppuwaa woridaagaa; shemppo woridaagee haiqqo.

English Sentences: And if he smite him with throwing a stone, wherewith he may die, and he die, he is a murderer: the murderer shall surely be put to death.
Wolaitta Sentences: Qassi worana danddayiya shuchchaa ba kushiyan oiqqida asi issi asa he shuchchan caddin, he uri haiqqikko, hegee shemppuwaa woridaagaa; shemppo woridaagee haiqqo.

English Sentences: Or if he smite him with an hand weapon of wood, wherewith he may die, and he die, he is a murderer: the murderer shall surely be put to death.
Wolaitta Sentences: Qassikka worana danddayiya mitta ba kushiyan oiqqida asi issi asa he mittan shocin, he uri haiqqikko, hegee shemppuwaa woridaagaa; shemppo woridaagee haiqqo.

English Sentences: The revenger of blood himself shall slay the murderer: when he meeteth him, he shall slay him.
Wolaitta Sentences: Suuttaa achchiyaagee he shemppuwaa woridaagaa demmikko woro.

English Sentences: But if he thrust him of hatred, or hurl at him by laying of wait, that he die;
Wolaitta Sentences: "Issi asi issi asa morkkidi caddin, woikko zuggidi issibaa a bolli olin, he urai haiqqikko,

English Sentences: Or in enmity smite him with his hand, that he die: he that smote him shall surely be put to death; for he is a murderer: the revenger of blood shall slay the murderer, when he meeteth him.
Wolaitta Sentences: woikko morkkidi ba kushiyan bubbuxin, he urai haiqqikko, i shemppuwaa woridaagaa; shemppo woridaagee haiqqo. Suuttaa achchiyaagee shemppuwaa woridaagaa demmikko woro.

English Sentences: But if he thrust him suddenly without enmity, or have cast upon him any thing without laying of wait,
Wolaitta Sentences: "SHin morkketetti bainnan, issi asi issi asa akeekennan sugikko, woikko zuggidi naagennan issibaa a bolli olikko,

English Sentences: Or with any stone, wherewith a man may die, seeing him not, and cast it upon him, that he die, and was not his enemy, neither sought his harm:
Wolaitta Sentences: woikko a worana danddayiya shuchcha i be7ennan a bolli yeggikkonne he urai haiqqikko, hegee a morkke gidenna gishshaunne a qohanau halchchibeenna gishshau,

English Sentences: Then the congregation shall judge between the slayer and the revenger of blood according to these judgments:
Wolaitta Sentences: yaa7ai erennan woridaagaappenne suuttaa achchiyaagaappe gidduwan ha wogatudan pirddo.

English Sentences: And the congregation shall deliver the slayer out of the hand of the revenger of blood, and the congregation shall restore him to the city of his refuge, whither he was fled: and he shall abide in it unto the death of the high priest, which was anointed with the holy oil.
Wolaitta Sentences: Erennan woridaagaa suuttaa achchiyaagaa kushiyaappe yaa7ai ashshidi, i baqatidi attiyo katamaa zaaro. Zaarin geeshsha zaitiyan tiyettida, qeese ubbatu halaqai haiqqana gakkanaassi, i yan de7o.

English Sentences: But if the slayer shall at any time come without the border of the city of his refuge, whither he was fled;
Wolaitta Sentences: "SHin erennan woridaagee baqatidi attiyo katamaa zawaappe kare kiyiyaabaa gidikkonne,

English Sentences: And the revenger of blood find him without the borders of the city of his refuge, and the revenger of blood kill the slayer; he shall not be guilty of blood:
Wolaitta Sentences: baqati attiyo katamaappe kareera suuttaa achchiyaagee a demmidi worikko, i woridoogau oishettenna.

English Sentences: Because he should have remained in the city of his refuge until the death of the high priest: but after the death of the high priest the slayer shall return into the land of his possession.
Wolaitta Sentences: Aissi giikko, qeese ubbatu halaqai haiqqana gakkanaassi, he erennan woridaagee ba baqatido kataman uttanaagaashin aggiis. SHin qeese ubbatu halaqai haiqqidoogaappe guyyiyan, erennan woridaagee ba laata gade simmanau danddayees.

English Sentences: So these things shall be for a statute of judgment unto you throughout your generations in all your dwellings.
Wolaitta Sentences: "Intteyyoonne biron yelettana yeletaayyo, intte de7iyoosa ubban hagee higge gido.

English Sentences: Whoso killeth any person, the murderer shall be put to death by the mouth of witnesses: but one witness shall not testify against any person to cause him to die.
Wolaitta Sentences: "Asa worida ooninne shemppo i woridoogaadan markkati markkattin haiqqo; shin issi asa xalaalai markkattin, ai asinne haiqqoppo.

English Sentences: Moreover ye shall take no satisfaction for the life of a murderer, which is guilty of death: but he shall be surely put to death.
Wolaitta Sentences: SHemppuwaa worido gishshau haiqqanau bessiya asa paxa ashshanau gumiyaa ekkoppite; i haiqqo.

English Sentences: And ye shall take no satisfaction for him that is fled to the city of his refuge, that he should come again to dwell in the land, until the death of the priest.
Wolaitta Sentences: Attiyo katamaa baqatida ooppenne qeese ubbatu halaqai haiqqanaappe kase, i guyye simmidi, ba biittan de7anaadan oottanau gumiyaa ekkoppite.

English Sentences: So ye shall not pollute the land wherein ye are: for blood it defileth the land: and the land cannot be cleansed of the blood that is shed therein, but by the blood of him that shed it.
Wolaitta Sentences: "Hegaadan oottidi, intte de7iyo biittaa tunissoppite. Aissi giikko, suuttaa gussiyoogee biittaa tunissees; suuttaa gussidaagaa suuttaanappe attin, suuttai gukkido biitti hara ogeera tunatettaappe geeyenna.

English Sentences: Defile not therefore the land which ye shall inhabit, wherein I dwell: for I the LORD dwell among the children of Israel.
Wolaitta Sentences: Taani, GODAI, Israa7eela asaa gidduwan de7iyo gishshau, intte de7iyo biittaa, taanikka de7iyo biittaa tunissoppite yaagada yoota" yaagiis.

English Sentences: And the chief fathers of the families of the children of Gilead, the son of Machir, the son of Manasseh, of the families of the sons of Joseph, came near, and spake before Moses, and before the princes, the chief fathers of the children of Israel:
Wolaitta Sentences: Yooseefa zaretuppe, Minaase na7aa Maakiira na7aa Gala7aade yaratu halaqati Muusekkonne Israa7eelatu yaratu halaqatukko yiidosona.

English Sentences: And they said, The LORD commanded my lord to give the land for an inheritance by lot to the children of Israel: and my lord was commanded by the LORD to give the inheritance of Zelophehad our brother unto his daughters.
Wolaitta Sentences: Eti yiidi, "Nu godau, Israa7eela asaayyo biittaa saaman shaakkada immana mala, GODAI nena azaziis; qassi GODAI nu ishaa Xalofihaada laataa a macca naatuyyo neeni immana mala, nena azaziis.

English Sentences: And if they be married to any of the sons of the other tribes of the children of Israel, then shall their inheritance be taken from the inheritance of our fathers, and shall be put to the inheritance of the tribe whereunto they are received: so shall it be taken from the lot of our inheritance.
Wolaitta Sentences: Leemisuwau eti hara zare gidiya Israa7eela asa gelikko, eta laatai nu aawatu laataappe ekettidi, eti geliyo zariyaayyo gujettees. Hegaa gishshau, nuuyyo saaman imettida laatai paccana.

English Sentences: And when the jubile of the children of Israel shall be, then shall their inheritance be put unto the inheritance of the tribe whereunto they are received: so shall their inheritance be taken away from the inheritance of the tribe of our fathers.
Wolaitta Sentences: Qassi Israa7eelatuyyo Ishatamantto Laittaa Baalai gakkiyo wode, eta laatai eti geliyo asa zariyaayyo gujettees; eta laatai nu aawatu zariyaa laataappe paccana" yaagiis.

English Sentences: And Moses commanded the children of Israel according to the word of the LORD, saying, The tribe of the sons of Joseph hath said well.
Wolaitta Sentences: Hegaappe guyyiyan, GODAA qaalaadan, Muusee Israa7eelata hagaadan yaagidi azaziis; "Yooseefa zareti giyoogee likke.

English Sentences: This is the thing which the LORD doth command concerning the daughters of Zelophehad, saying, Let them marry to whom they think best; only to the family of the tribe of their father shall they marry.
Wolaitta Sentences: GODAI Xalofihaada macca naatubaa azazidoogee hagaa; eti bantta dosido azinaa gelanau danddayoosona; shin bantta aawaa zariyaappe gidanau koshshees.

English Sentences: So shall not the inheritance of the children of Israel remove from tribe to tribe: for every one of the children of Israel shall keep himself to the inheritance of the tribe of his fathers.
Wolaitta Sentences: Israa7eelatu laatai issi zariyaappe hara zariyau aadhdhoppo; Israa7eela ubbai ba maizza aawatu zaree laattido biittaa minttidi oiqqo.

English Sentences: And every daughter, that possesseth an inheritance in any tribe of the children of Israel, shall be wife unto one of the family of the tribe of her father, that the children of Israel may enjoy every man the inheritance of his fathers.
Wolaitta Sentences: Israa7eela asaa giddon ai zareppe gidinkka, biitta laattiya macca na7i ubbi, Israa7eeli ubbi ba maizza aawatu laataa laattana mala, a ba aawaa zare gidiya asa gelu.

English Sentences: Neither shall the inheritance remove from one tribe to another tribe; but every one of the tribes of the children of Israel shall keep himself to his own inheritance.
Wolaitta Sentences: Hegaadan hanidi, laatai issi zariyaappe hara zariyau mulekka aadhdhennan de7ana. Hegaa gishshau, Israa7eela ubbai ba maizza aawatu zaree laattido biittaa minttidi oiqqo" yaagiis.

English Sentences: Even as the LORD commanded Moses, so did the daughters of Zelophehad:
Wolaitta Sentences: Yaagin Xalofihaada macca naati GODAI Muusa azazidoogaadan oottidosona.

English Sentences: For Mahlah, Tirzah, and Hoglah, and Milcah, and Noah, the daughters of Zelophehad, were married unto their father's brothers' sons:
Wolaitta Sentences: Xalofihaada macca naati, Maahilo, Tirxxo, Hoogilo, Milkkonne No7o geetettiyaageeti, bantta aawaa ishanttu naata gelidosona.

English Sentences: And they were married into the families of the sons of Manasseh the son of Joseph, and their inheritance remained in the tribe of the family of their father.
Wolaitta Sentences: Eti Yooseefa na7aa Minaase naatu zariyaa giddon azinaa gelidosona; gelin eta laatai eta aawaa zariyaunne yarau attiis.
